80namespace {
81
82class MipsAssemblerOptions {
83public:
84 MipsAssemblerOptions(const FeatureBitset &Features_) : Features(Features_) {}
85
86 MipsAssemblerOptions(const MipsAssemblerOptions *Opts) {
87 ATReg = Opts->getATRegIndex();
88 Reorder = Opts->isReorder();
89 Macro = Opts->isMacro();
90 Features = Opts->getFeatures();
91 }
92
93 unsigned getATRegIndex() const { return ATReg; }
94 bool setATRegIndex(unsigned Reg) {
95 if (Reg > 31)
96 return false;
97
98 ATReg = Reg;
99 return true;
100 }
101
102 bool isReorder() const { return Reorder; }
103 void setReorder() { Reorder = true; }
104 void setNoReorder() { Reorder = false; }
105
106 bool isMacro() const { return Macro; }
107 void setMacro() { Macro = true; }
108 void setNoMacro() { Macro = false; }
109
110 const FeatureBitset &getFeatures() const { return Features; }
111 void setFeatures(const FeatureBitset &Features_) { Features = Features_; }
112
113 // Set of features that are either architecture features or referenced
114 // by them (e.g.: FeatureNaN2008 implied by FeatureMips32r6).
115 // The full table can be found in MipsGenSubtargetInfo.inc (MipsFeatureKV[]).
116 // The reason we need this mask is explained in the selectArch function.
117 // FIXME: Ideally we would like TableGen to generate this information.
118 static const FeatureBitset AllArchRelatedMask;
119
120private:
121 unsigned ATReg = 1;
122 bool Reorder = true;
123 bool Macro = true;
124 FeatureBitset Features;
125};
126
127} // end anonymous namespace
128
129const FeatureBitset MipsAssemblerOptions::AllArchRelatedMask = {
130 Mips::FeatureMips1, Mips::FeatureMips2, Mips::FeatureMips3,
131 Mips::FeatureMips3_32, Mips::FeatureMips3_32r2, Mips::FeatureMips4,
132 Mips::FeatureMips4_32, Mips::FeatureMips4_32r2, Mips::FeatureMips5,
133 Mips::FeatureMips5_32r2, Mips::FeatureMips32, Mips::FeatureMips32r2,
134 Mips::FeatureMips32r3, Mips::FeatureMips32r5, Mips::FeatureMips32r6,
135 Mips::FeatureMips64, Mips::FeatureMips64r2, Mips::FeatureMips64r3,
136 Mips::FeatureMips64r5, Mips::FeatureMips64r6, Mips::FeatureCnMips,
137 Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, Mips::FeatureGP64Bit, Mips::FeatureNaN2008
138};

424 // Helper function that checks if the value of a vector index is within the
425 // boundaries of accepted values for each RegisterKind
426 // Example: INSERT.B $w0[n], $1 => 16 > n >= 0
427 bool validateMSAIndex(int Val, int RegKind);
428
429 // Selects a new architecture by updating the FeatureBits with the necessary
430 // info including implied dependencies.
431 // Internally, it clears all the feature bits related to *any* architecture
432 // and selects the new one using the ToggleFeature functionality of the
433 // MCSubtargetInfo object that handles implied dependencies. The reason we
434 // clear all the arch related bits manually is because ToggleFeature only
435 // clears the features that imply the feature being cleared and not the
436 // features implied by the feature being cleared. This is easier to see
437 // with an example:
438 // --------------------------------------------------
439 // | Feature | Implies |
440 // | -------------------------------------------------|
441 // | FeatureMips1 | None |
442 // | FeatureMips2 | FeatureMips1 |
443 // | FeatureMips3 | FeatureMips2 | FeatureMipsGP64 |
444 // | FeatureMips4 | FeatureMips3 |
445 // | ... | |
446 // --------------------------------------------------
447 //
448 // Setting Mips3 is equivalent to set: (FeatureMips3 | FeatureMips2 |
449 // FeatureMipsGP64 | FeatureMips1)
450 // Clearing Mips3 is equivalent to clear (FeatureMips3 | FeatureMips4).
451 void selectArch(StringRef ArchFeature) {
452 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
453 FeatureBitset FeatureBits = STI.getFeatureBits();
454 FeatureBits &= ~MipsAssemblerOptions::AllArchRelatedMask;
455 STI.setFeatureBits(FeatureBits);
456 setAvailableFeatures(
457 ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.ToggleFeature(ArchFeature)));
458 AssemblerOptions.back()->setFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits());
459 }
460
461 void setFeatureBits(uint64_t Feature, StringRef FeatureString) {
462 if (!(getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Feature])) {
463 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
464 setAvailableFeatures(
465 ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.ToggleFeature(FeatureString)));
466 AssemblerOptions.back()->setFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits());
467 }
468 }
469
470 void clearFeatureBits(uint64_t Feature, StringRef FeatureString) {
471 if (getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Feature]) {
472 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
473 setAvailableFeatures(
474 ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.ToggleFeature(FeatureString)));
475 AssemblerOptions.back()->setFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits());
476 }
477 }
478
479 void setModuleFeatureBits(uint64_t Feature, StringRef FeatureString) {
480 setFeatureBits(Feature, FeatureString);
481 AssemblerOptions.front()->setFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits());
482 }
483
484 void clearModuleFeatureBits(uint64_t Feature, StringRef FeatureString) {
485 clearFeatureBits(Feature, FeatureString);
486 AssemblerOptions.front()->setFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits());
487 }
488
489public:
490 enum MipsMatchResultTy {
491 Match_RequiresDifferentSrcAndDst = FIRST_TARGET_MATCH_RESULT_TY,
492 Match_RequiresDifferentOperands,
493 Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister,
494 Match_RequiresSameSrcAndDst,
495 Match_NoFCCRegisterForCurrentISA,
496 Match_NonZeroOperandForSync,
497 Match_NonZeroOperandForMTCX,
498 Match_RequiresPosSizeRange0_32,
499 Match_RequiresPosSizeRange33_64,
500 Match_RequiresPosSizeUImm6,
501#define GET_OPERAND_DIAGNOSTIC_TYPES
502#include "MipsGenAsmMatcher.inc"
503#undef GET_OPERAND_DIAGNOSTIC_TYPES
504 };
505
506 MipsAsmParser(const MCSubtargetInfo &sti, MCAsmParser &parser,
507 const MCInstrInfo &MII, const MCTargetOptions &Options)
508 : MCTargetAsmParser(Options, sti, MII),
509 ABI(MipsABIInfo::computeTargetABI(Triple(sti.getTargetTriple()),
510 sti.getCPU(), Options)) {
511 MCAsmParserExtension::Initialize(parser);
512
513 parser.addAliasForDirective(".asciiz", ".asciz");
514 parser.addAliasForDirective(".hword", ".2byte");
515 parser.addAliasForDirective(".word", ".4byte");
516 parser.addAliasForDirective(".dword", ".8byte");
517
518 // Initialize the set of available features.
519 setAvailableFeatures(ComputeAvailableFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits()));
520
521 // Remember the initial assembler options. The user can not modify these.
522 AssemblerOptions.push_back(
523 llvm::make_unique<MipsAssemblerOptions>(getSTI().getFeatureBits()));
524
525 // Create an assembler options environment for the user to modify.
526 AssemblerOptions.push_back(
527 llvm::make_unique<MipsAssemblerOptions>(getSTI().getFeatureBits()));
528
529 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
530
531 // HACK: Update the default CFA register for CHERI purecap
532 ABI.updateCheriInitialFrameStateHack(*getContext().getAsmInfo(),
533 *getContext().getRegisterInfo());
534
535 if (!isABI_O32() && !useOddSPReg() != 0)
536 report_fatal_error("-mno-odd-spreg requires the O32 ABI");
537
538 CurrentFn = nullptr;
539
540 IsPicEnabled = getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->isPositionIndependent();
541
542 IsCpRestoreSet = false;
543 AreCheriSysRegsAccessible = false;
544 CpRestoreOffset = -1;
545
546 const Triple &TheTriple = sti.getTargetTriple();
547 IsLittleEndian = TheTriple.isLittleEndian();
548
549 if (getSTI().getCPU() == "mips64r6" && inMicroMipsMode())
550 report_fatal_error("microMIPS64R6 is not supported", false);
551
552 if (!isABI_O32() && inMicroMipsMode())
553 report_fatal_error("microMIPS64 is not supported", false);
554 }
555
556 /// True if all of $fcc0 - $fcc7 exist for the current ISA.
557 bool hasEightFccRegisters() const { return hasMips4() || hasMips32(); }
558
559 bool isGP64bit() const {
560 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureGP64Bit];
561 }
562
563 bool isFP64bit() const {
564 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureFP64Bit];
565 }
566
567 const MipsABIInfo &getABI() const { return ABI; }
568 bool isABI_N32() const { return ABI.IsN32(); }
569 bool isABI_N64() const { return ABI.IsN64(); }
570 bool isABI_O32() const { return ABI.IsO32(); }
571 bool isABI_FPXX() const {
572 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureFPXX];
573 }
574
575 bool useOddSPReg() const {
576 return !(getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureNoOddSPReg]);
577 }

633 }
634
635 bool hasMips32r6() const {
636 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMips32r6];
637 }
638
639 bool hasMips64r6() const {
640 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMips64r6];
641 }
642
643 bool hasDSP() const {
644 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureDSP];
645 }
646
647 bool hasDSPR2() const {
648 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureDSPR2];
649 }
650
651 bool hasDSPR3() const {
652 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureDSPR3];
653 }
654
655 bool hasMSA() const {
656 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMSA];
657 }
658
659 bool hasCnMips() const {
660 return (getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureCnMips]);
661 }
662
663 bool inPicMode() {
664 return IsPicEnabled;
665 }
666
667 bool inMips16Mode() const {
668 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMips16];
669 }
670
671 bool useTraps() const {
672 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureUseTCCInDIV];
673 }
674
675 bool useSoftFloat() const {
676 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureSoftFloat];
677 }
678 bool hasMT() const {
679 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMT];
680 }
681
682 bool isCheri() const override {
683 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMipsCheri];
684 }
685
686 unsigned getCheriCapabilitySize() const override {
687 if (getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMipsCheri256])
688 return 32;
689 if (getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMipsCheri128])
690 return 16;
691 if (getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureMipsCheri64])
692 return 8;
693 llvm_unreachable("Should not have been called without checking isCheri()!");
694 }
695
696 bool hasCRC() const {
697 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureCRC];
698 }
699
700 bool hasVirt() const {
701 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureVirt];
702 }
703
704 bool hasGINV() const {
705 return getSTI().getFeatureBits()[Mips::FeatureGINV];
706 }
707
708 /// Warn if RegIndex is the same as the current AT.
709 void warnIfRegIndexIsAT(unsigned RegIndex, SMLoc Loc);
710
711 void warnIfNoMacro(SMLoc Loc);
712
713 /// Avoid another error message if we already have one pending
714 bool ErrorIfNotPending(SMLoc L, const Twine& Msg, SMRange Range = SMRange()) {
715 return getParser().hasPendingError() ? true : Error(L, Msg, Range);
716 }
717
718 bool isLittle() const { return IsLittleEndian; }
719
720 const MCExpr *createTargetUnaryExpr(const MCExpr *E,
721 AsmToken::TokenKind OperatorToken,
722 MCContext &Ctx) override {
723 switch(OperatorToken) {
724 default:
725 llvm_unreachable("Unknown token");
726 return nullptr;
727 case AsmToken::PercentCall16:
728 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_CALL, E, Ctx);
729 case AsmToken::PercentCall_Hi:
730 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CALL_HI16, E, Ctx);
731 case AsmToken::PercentCall_Lo:
732 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CALL_LO16, E, Ctx);
733 case AsmToken::PercentDtprel_Hi:
734 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_DTPREL_HI, E, Ctx);
735 case AsmToken::PercentDtprel_Lo:
736 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_DTPREL_LO, E, Ctx);
737 case AsmToken::PercentGot:
738 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT, E, Ctx);
739 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Disp:
740 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_DISP, E, Ctx);
741 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Hi:
742 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_HI16, E, Ctx);
743 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Lo:
744 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_LO16, E, Ctx);
745 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Ofst:
746 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_OFST, E, Ctx);
747 case AsmToken::PercentGot_Page:
748 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_PAGE, E, Ctx);
749 case AsmToken::PercentGottprel:
750 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOTTPREL, E, Ctx);
751 case AsmToken::PercentGp_Rel:
752 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GPREL, E, Ctx);
753 case AsmToken::PercentCapTab_Rel:
754 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTABLEREL, E, Ctx);
755 case AsmToken::PercentHi:
756 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HI, E, Ctx);
757 case AsmToken::PercentHigher:
758 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HIGHER, E, Ctx);
759 case AsmToken::PercentHighest:
760 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HIGHEST, E, Ctx);
761 case AsmToken::PercentLo:
762 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, E, Ctx);
763 case AsmToken::PercentNeg:
764 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_NEG, E, Ctx);
765 case AsmToken::PercentPcrel_Hi:
766 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_PCREL_HI16, E, Ctx);
767 case AsmToken::PercentPcrel_Lo:
768 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_PCREL_LO16, E, Ctx);
769 case AsmToken::PercentTlsgd:
770 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_TLSGD, E, Ctx);
771 case AsmToken::PercentTlsldm:
772 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_TLSLDM, E, Ctx);
773 case AsmToken::PercentTprel_Hi:
774 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_TPREL_HI, E, Ctx);
775 case AsmToken::PercentTprel_Lo:
776 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_TPREL_LO, E, Ctx);
777 case AsmToken::PercentCapTab11:
778 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTABLE11, E, Ctx);
779 case AsmToken::PercentCapTab20:
780 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTABLE20, E, Ctx);
781 case AsmToken::PercentCapTab_Hi:
782 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTABLE_HI16, E, Ctx);
783 case AsmToken::PercentCapTab_Lo:
784 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTABLE_LO16, E, Ctx);
785 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabCall11:
786 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPCALL11, E, Ctx);
787 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabCall20:
788 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPCALL20, E, Ctx);
789 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabCall_Hi:
790 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPCALL_HI16, E, Ctx);
791 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabCall_Lo:
792 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPCALL_LO16, E, Ctx);
793 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTlsgd_Hi:
794 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTAB_TLSGD_HI16, E, Ctx);
795 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTlsgd_Lo:
796 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTAB_TLSGD_LO16, E, Ctx);
797 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTlsldm_Hi:
798 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTAB_TLSLDM_HI16, E, Ctx);
799 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTlsldm_Lo:
800 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTAB_TLSLDM_LO16, E, Ctx);
801 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTprel_Hi:
802 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTAB_TPREL_HI16, E, Ctx);
803 case AsmToken::PercentCapTabTprel_Lo:
804 return MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTAB_TPREL_LO16, E, Ctx);
805 }
806 }
807};
808
809/// MipsOperand - Instances of this class represent a parsed Mips machine
810/// instruction.
811class MipsOperand : public MCParsedAsmOperand {
812public:
813 /// Broad categories of register classes
814 /// The exact class is finalized by the render method.
815 enum RegKind {
816 RegKind_GPR = 1, /// GPR32 and GPR64 (depending on isGP64bit())
817 RegKind_FGR = 2, /// FGR32, FGR64, AFGR64 (depending on context and
818 /// isFP64bit())
819 RegKind_FCC = 4, /// FCC
820 RegKind_MSA128 = 8, /// MSA128[BHWD] (makes no difference which)
821 RegKind_MSACtrl = 16, /// MSA control registers
822 RegKind_COP2 = 32, /// COP2
823 RegKind_ACC = 64, /// HI32DSP, LO32DSP, and ACC64DSP (depending on
824 /// context).
825 RegKind_CCR = 128, /// CCR
826 RegKind_HWRegs = 256, /// HWRegs
827 RegKind_COP3 = 512, /// COP3
828 RegKind_COP0 = 1024, /// COP0
829 RegKind_Cheri = 2048,
830 RegKind_CheriHWRegs = 4096,
831 /// Potentially any (e.g. $1)
832 /// XXXAR: but not CHERI since those should always be prefixed
833 RegKind_Numeric = RegKind_GPR | RegKind_FGR | RegKind_FCC | RegKind_MSA128 |
834 RegKind_MSACtrl | RegKind_COP2 | RegKind_ACC |
835 RegKind_CCR | RegKind_HWRegs | RegKind_COP3 | RegKind_COP0
836 /* | RegKind_Cheri */ | RegKind_CheriHWRegs
837 };
838
839private:
840 enum KindTy {
841 k_Immediate, /// An immediate (possibly involving symbol references)
842 k_Memory, /// Base + Offset Memory Address
843 k_RegisterIndex, /// A register index in one or more RegKind.
844 k_Token, /// A simple token
845 k_RegList, /// A physical register list
846 } Kind;
847
848public:
849 MipsOperand(KindTy K, MipsAsmParser &Parser)
850 : MCParsedAsmOperand(), Kind(K), AsmParser(Parser) {}
851
852 ~MipsOperand() override {
853 switch (Kind) {
854 case k_Memory:
855 delete Mem.Base;
856 break;
857 case k_RegList:
858 delete RegList.List;
859 break;
860 case k_Immediate:
861 case k_RegisterIndex:
862 case k_Token:
863 break;
864 }
865 }
866
867private:
868 /// For diagnostics, and checking the assembler temporary
869 MipsAsmParser &AsmParser;
870
871 struct Token {
872 const char *Data;
873 unsigned Length;
874 };
875
876 struct RegIdxOp {
877 unsigned Index; /// Index into the register class
878 RegKind Kind; /// Bitfield of the kinds it could possibly be
879 struct Token Tok; /// The input token this operand originated from.
880 const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo;
881 unsigned RealRegister; // The real underlying register (if already known)
882 };
883
884 struct ImmOp {
885 const MCExpr *Val;
886 };
887
888 struct MemOp {
889 MipsOperand *Base;
890 const MCExpr *Off;
891 };
892
893 struct RegListOp {
894 SmallVector<unsigned, 10> *List;
895 };
896
897 union {
898 struct Token Tok;
899 struct RegIdxOp RegIdx;
900 struct ImmOp Imm;
901 struct MemOp Mem;
902 struct RegListOp RegList;
903 };
904
905 SMLoc StartLoc, EndLoc;
906
907 /// Internal constructor for register kinds
908 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
909 CreateReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, RegKind RegKind,
910 const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo, SMLoc S, SMLoc E,
911 MipsAsmParser &Parser, unsigned RealRegister = Mips::NoRegister) {
912 auto Op = llvm::make_unique<MipsOperand>(k_RegisterIndex, Parser);
913 Op->RegIdx.Index = Index;
914 Op->RegIdx.RegInfo = RegInfo;
915 Op->RegIdx.Kind = RegKind;
916 Op->RegIdx.Tok.Data = Str.data();
917 Op->RegIdx.Tok.Length = Str.size();
918 Op->RegIdx.RealRegister = RealRegister;
919 Op->StartLoc = S;
920 Op->EndLoc = E;
921 return Op;
922 }
923
924public:
925 /// Coerce the register to GPR32 and return the real register for the current
926 /// target.
927 unsigned getGPR32Reg() const {
928 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR) && "Invalid access!");
929 AsmParser.warnIfRegIndexIsAT(RegIdx.Index, StartLoc);
930 unsigned ClassID = Mips::GPR32RegClassID;
931 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
932 }
933
934 /// Coerce the register to GPR32 and return the real register for the current
935 /// target.
936 unsigned getGPRMM16Reg() const {
937 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR) && "Invalid access!");
938 unsigned ClassID = Mips::GPR32RegClassID;
939 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
940 }
941
942 /// Coerce the register to GPR64 and return the real register for the current
943 /// target.
944 unsigned getGPR64Reg() const {
945 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR) && "Invalid access!");
946 unsigned ClassID = Mips::GPR64RegClassID;
947 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
948 }
949
950private:
951 /// Coerce the register to AFGR64 and return the real register for the current
952 /// target.
953 unsigned getAFGR64Reg() const {
954 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FGR) && "Invalid access!");
955 if (RegIdx.Index % 2 != 0)
956 AsmParser.Warning(StartLoc, "Float register should be even.");
957 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(Mips::AFGR64RegClassID)
958 .getRegister(RegIdx.Index / 2);
959 }
960
961 /// Coerce the register to FGR64 and return the real register for the current
962 /// target.
963 unsigned getFGR64Reg() const {
964 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FGR) && "Invalid access!");
965 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(Mips::FGR64RegClassID)
966 .getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
967 }
968
969 /// Coerce the register to FGR32 and return the real register for the current
970 /// target.
971 unsigned getFGR32Reg() const {
972 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FGR) && "Invalid access!");
973 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(Mips::FGR32RegClassID)
974 .getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
975 }
976
977 /// Coerce the register to FCC and return the real register for the current
978 /// target.
979 unsigned getFCCReg() const {
980 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FCC) && "Invalid access!");
981 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(Mips::FCCRegClassID)
982 .getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
983 }
984
985 /// Coerce the register to MSA128 and return the real register for the current
986 /// target.
987 unsigned getMSA128Reg() const {
988 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_MSA128) && "Invalid access!");
989 // It doesn't matter which of the MSA128[BHWD] classes we use. They are all
990 // identical
991 unsigned ClassID = Mips::MSA128BRegClassID;
992 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
993 }
994
995 /// Coerce the register to MSACtrl and return the real register for the
996 /// current target.
997 unsigned getMSACtrlReg() const {
998 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_MSACtrl) && "Invalid access!");
999 unsigned ClassID = Mips::MSACtrlRegClassID;
1000 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1001 }
1002
1003 /// Coerce the register to COP0 and return the real register for the
1004 /// current target.
1005 unsigned getCOP0Reg() const {
1006 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_COP0) && "Invalid access!");
1007 unsigned ClassID = Mips::COP0RegClassID;
1008 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1009 }
1010
1011 /// Coerce the register to COP2 and return the real register for the
1012 /// current target.
1013 unsigned getCOP2Reg() const {
1014 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_COP2) && "Invalid access!");
1015 unsigned ClassID = Mips::COP2RegClassID;
1016 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1017 }
1018
1019 /// Coerce the register to COP3 and return the real register for the
1020 /// current target.
1021 unsigned getCOP3Reg() const {
1022 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_COP3) && "Invalid access!");
1023 unsigned ClassID = Mips::COP3RegClassID;
1024 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1025 }
1026
1027 /// Coerce the register to ACC64DSP and return the real register for the
1028 /// current target.
1029 unsigned getACC64DSPReg() const {
1030 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_ACC) && "Invalid access!");
1031 unsigned ClassID = Mips::ACC64DSPRegClassID;
1032 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1033 }
1034
1035 /// Coerce the register to HI32DSP and return the real register for the
1036 /// current target.
1037 unsigned getHI32DSPReg() const {
1038 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_ACC) && "Invalid access!");
1039 unsigned ClassID = Mips::HI32DSPRegClassID;
1040 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1041 }
1042
1043 /// Coerce the register to LO32DSP and return the real register for the
1044 /// current target.
1045 unsigned getLO32DSPReg() const {
1046 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_ACC) && "Invalid access!");
1047 unsigned ClassID = Mips::LO32DSPRegClassID;
1048 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1049 }
1050
1051 /// Coerce the register to CCR and return the real register for the
1052 /// current target.
1053 unsigned getCCRReg() const {
1054 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_CCR) && "Invalid access!");
1055 unsigned ClassID = Mips::CCRRegClassID;
1056 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1057 }
1058
1059 /// Coerce the register to HWRegs and return the real register for the
1060 /// current target.
1061 unsigned getHWRegsReg() const {
1062 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_HWRegs) && "Invalid access!");
1063 unsigned ClassID = Mips::HWRegsRegClassID;
1064 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1065 }
1066 /// Coerce the register to CheriHWRegs and return the real register for the
1067 /// current target.
1068 unsigned getCheriHWRegsReg() const {
1069 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_CheriHWRegs) && "Invalid access!");
1070 unsigned ClassID = Mips::CheriHWRegsRegClassID;
1071 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1072 }
1073public:
1074 /// Coerce the register to Cheri capability register and return the real
1075 /// register for the current target.
1076 unsigned getCheriReg() const {
1077 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_Cheri) && "Invalid access!");
1078 unsigned ClassID = Mips::CheriGPROrCNullRegClassID;
1079 assert(
1080 RegIdx.RealRegister == Mips::CNULL ||
1081 (RegIdx.RealRegister >= Mips::C1 && RegIdx.RealRegister <= Mips::C31));
1082 assert(RegIdx.Index <= 31);
1083 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1084 }
1085 unsigned getCheriReg0IsDDC() const {
1086 assert(isRegIdx() && (RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_Cheri) && "Invalid access!");
1087 unsigned ClassID = Mips::CheriGPROrDDCRegClassID;
1088 assert(
1089 RegIdx.RealRegister == Mips::DDC ||
1090 (RegIdx.RealRegister >= Mips::C1 && RegIdx.RealRegister <= Mips::C31));
1091 assert(RegIdx.Index <= 31);
1092 return RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(ClassID).getRegister(RegIdx.Index);
1093 }
1094
1095 void addExpr(MCInst &Inst, const MCExpr *Expr) const {
1096 // Add as immediate when possible. Null MCExpr = 0.
1097 if (!Expr)
1098 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0));
1099 else if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Expr))
1100 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(CE->getValue()));
1101 else
1102 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr));
1103 }

1105 void addRegOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1106 llvm_unreachable("Use a custom parser instead");
1107 }

1111 /// is not a k_RegisterIndex compatible with RegKind_GPR

1113 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1114 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(getGPR32Reg()));
1115 }

1184 // FIXME: We ought to do this for -integrated-as without -via-file-asm too.
1185 // FIXME: This should propagate failure up to parseStatement.
1186 if (!AsmParser.useOddSPReg() && RegIdx.Index & 1)

1191
1192 void addStrictlyFGR32AsmRegOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1193 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1194 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(getFGR32Reg()));
1195 // FIXME: We ought to do this for -integrated-as without -via-file-asm too.
1196 if (!AsmParser.useOddSPReg() && RegIdx.Index & 1)
1197 AsmParser.Error(StartLoc, "-mno-odd-spreg prohibits the use of odd FPU "
1198 "registers");
1199 }

1271 template <unsigned Bits, int Offset = 0, int AdjustOffset = 0>
1272 void addConstantUImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1273 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1274 uint64_t Imm = getConstantImm() - Offset;
1275 Imm &= (1ULL << Bits) - 1;
1276 Imm += Offset;
1277 Imm += AdjustOffset;
1278 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm));
1279 }
1280
1281 template <unsigned Bits>
1282 void addSImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1283 if (isImm() && !isConstantImm()) {
1284 addExpr(Inst, getImm());
1285 return;
1286 }
1287 addConstantSImmOperands<Bits, 0, 0>(Inst, N);
1288 }
1289
1290 template <unsigned Bits>
1291 void addUImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1292 if (isImm() && !isConstantImm()) {
1293 addExpr(Inst, getImm());
1294 return;
1295 }
1296 addConstantUImmOperands<Bits, 0, 0>(Inst, N);
1297 }
1298
1299 template <unsigned Bits, int Offset = 0, int AdjustOffset = 0>
1300 void addConstantSImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1301 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1302 int64_t Imm = getConstantImm() - Offset;
1303 Imm = SignExtend64<Bits>(Imm);
1304 Imm += Offset;
1305 Imm += AdjustOffset;
1306 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm));
1307 }
1308
1309 void addImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1310 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1311 const MCExpr *Expr = getImm();
1312 addExpr(Inst, Expr);
1313 }
1314
1315 void addMemOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1316 assert(N == 2 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1317
1318 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AsmParser.getABI().ArePtrs64bit()
1319 ? getMemBase()->getGPR64Reg()
1320 : getMemBase()->getGPR32Reg()));
1321
1322 const MCExpr *Expr = getMemOff();
1323 addExpr(Inst, Expr);
1324 }
1325
1326 void addMicroMipsMemOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1327 assert(N == 2 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1328
1329 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(getMemBase()->getGPRMM16Reg()));
1330
1331 const MCExpr *Expr = getMemOff();
1332 addExpr(Inst, Expr);
1333 }

1335 void addRegListOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1336 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
1337
1338 for (auto RegNo : getRegList())
1339 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(RegNo));
1340 }

1342 bool isReg() const override {
1343 // As a special case until we sort out the definition of div/divu, accept
1344 // $0/$zero here so that MCK_ZERO works correctly.
1345 return isGPRAsmReg() && RegIdx.Index == 0;
1346 }
1347
1348 bool isRegIdx() const { return Kind == k_RegisterIndex; }
1349 bool isImm() const override { return Kind == k_Immediate; }
1350
1351 bool isConstantImm() const {
1352 int64_t Res;
1353 return isImm() && getImm()->evaluateAsAbsolute(Res);
1354 }
1355
1356 bool isConstantImmz() const {
1357 return isConstantImm() && getConstantImm() == 0;
1358 }
1359
1360 template <unsigned Bits, int Offset = 0> bool isConstantUImm() const {
1361 return isConstantImm() && isUInt<Bits>(getConstantImm() - Offset);
1362 }
1363
1364 template <unsigned Bits> bool isSImm() const {
1365 return isConstantImm() ? isInt<Bits>(getConstantImm()) : isImm();
1366 }
1367
1368 template <unsigned Bits> bool isUImm() const {
1369 return isConstantImm() ? isUInt<Bits>(getConstantImm()) : isImm();
1370 }
1371
1372 template <unsigned Bits> bool isAnyImm() const {
1373 return isConstantImm() ? (isInt<Bits>(getConstantImm()) ||
1374 isUInt<Bits>(getConstantImm()))
1375 : isImm();
1376 }
1377
1378 template <unsigned Bits, int Offset = 0> bool isConstantSImm() const {
1379 return isConstantImm() && isInt<Bits>(getConstantImm() - Offset);
1380 }
1381
1382 template <unsigned Bottom, unsigned Top> bool isConstantUImmRange() const {
1383 return isConstantImm() && getConstantImm() >= Bottom &&
1384 getConstantImm() <= Top;
1385 }
1386
1387 bool isToken() const override {
1388 // Note: It's not possible to pretend that other operand kinds are tokens.
1389 // The matcher emitter checks tokens first.
1390 return Kind == k_Token;
1391 }
1392
1393 bool isMem() const override { return Kind == k_Memory; }
1394
1395 bool isConstantMemOff() const {
1396 return isMem() && isa<MCConstantExpr>(getMemOff());
1397 }
1398
1399 // Allow relocation operators.
1400 // FIXME: This predicate and others need to look through binary expressions
1401 // and determine whether a Value is a constant or not.
1402 template <unsigned Bits, unsigned ShiftAmount = 0>
1403 bool isMemWithSimmOffset() const {
1404 if (!isMem())
1405 return false;
1406 if (!getMemBase()->isGPRAsmReg())
1407 return false;
1408 if (isa<MCTargetExpr>(getMemOff()) ||
1409 (isConstantMemOff() &&
1410 isShiftedInt<Bits, ShiftAmount>(getConstantMemOff())))
1411 return true;
1412 MCValue Res;
1413 bool IsReloc = getMemOff()->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, nullptr);
1414 return IsReloc && isShiftedInt<Bits, ShiftAmount>(Res.getConstant());
1415 }
1416
1417 bool isMemWithPtrSizeOffset() const {
1418 if (!isMem())
1419 return false;
1420 if (!getMemBase()->isGPRAsmReg())
1421 return false;
1422 const unsigned PtrBits = AsmParser.getABI().ArePtrs64bit() ? 64 : 32;
1423 if (isa<MCTargetExpr>(getMemOff()) ||
1424 (isConstantMemOff() && isIntN(PtrBits, getConstantMemOff())))
1425 return true;
1426 MCValue Res;
1427 bool IsReloc = getMemOff()->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, nullptr);
1428 return IsReloc && isIntN(PtrBits, Res.getConstant());
1429 }
1430
1431 bool isMemWithGRPMM16Base() const {
1432 return isMem() && getMemBase()->isMM16AsmReg();
1433 }
1434
1435 template <unsigned Bits> bool isMemWithUimmOffsetSP() const {
1436 return isMem() && isConstantMemOff() && isUInt<Bits>(getConstantMemOff())
1437 && getMemBase()->isRegIdx() && (getMemBase()->getGPR32Reg() == Mips::SP);
1438 }
1439
1440 template <unsigned Bits> bool isMemWithUimmWordAlignedOffsetSP() const {
1441 return isMem() && isConstantMemOff() && isUInt<Bits>(getConstantMemOff())
1442 && (getConstantMemOff() % 4 == 0) && getMemBase()->isRegIdx()
1443 && (getMemBase()->getGPR32Reg() == Mips::SP);
1444 }
1445
1446 template <unsigned Bits> bool isMemWithSimmWordAlignedOffsetGP() const {
1447 return isMem() && isConstantMemOff() && isInt<Bits>(getConstantMemOff())
1448 && (getConstantMemOff() % 4 == 0) && getMemBase()->isRegIdx()
1449 && (getMemBase()->getGPR32Reg() == Mips::GP);
1450 }
1451
1452 template <unsigned Bits, unsigned ShiftLeftAmount>
1453 bool isScaledUImm() const {
1454 return isConstantImm() &&
1455 isShiftedUInt<Bits, ShiftLeftAmount>(getConstantImm());
1456 }
1457
1458 template <unsigned Bits, unsigned ShiftLeftAmount>
1459 bool isScaledSImm() const {
1460 if (isConstantImm() &&
1461 isShiftedInt<Bits, ShiftLeftAmount>(getConstantImm()))
1462 return true;
1463 // Operand can also be a symbol or symbol plus
1464 // offset in case of relocations.
1465 if (Kind != k_Immediate)
1466 return false;
1467 MCValue Res;
1468 // FIXME: it would be nice to somehow get at the MCFixup here and check the size
1469 // using MCAsmBackend::getFixupKindInfo()
1470 bool Success = getImm()->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, nullptr);
1471 // FIXME: how can we get at the MCFixup object (to check size generically)?
1472 if (auto Expr = dyn_cast<MipsMCExpr>(getImm())) {
1473 // HACK: Check that only %captab and %capcall are allowed in clc / csc
1474 if (ShiftLeftAmount == 4) {
1475 if (Bits == 11) {
1476 if (Expr->getKind() != MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTABLE11 &&
1477 Expr->getKind() != MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPCALL11)
1478 return false;
1479 } else if (Bits == 16) {
1480 if (Expr->getKind() != MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTABLE20 &&
1481 Expr->getKind() != MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPCALL20)
1482 return false;
1483 }
1484 }
1485 }
1486 return Success && isShiftedInt<Bits, ShiftLeftAmount>(Res.getConstant());
1487 }
1488
1489 bool isRegList16() const {
1490 if (!isRegList())
1491 return false;
1492
1493 int Size = RegList.List->size();
1494 if (Size < 2 || Size > 5)
1495 return false;
1496
1497 unsigned R0 = RegList.List->front();
1498 unsigned R1 = RegList.List->back();
1499 if (!((R0 == Mips::S0 && R1 == Mips::RA) ||
1500 (R0 == Mips::S0_64 && R1 == Mips::RA_64)))
1501 return false;
1502
1503 int PrevReg = *RegList.List->begin();
1504 for (int i = 1; i < Size - 1; i++) {
1505 int Reg = (*(RegList.List))[i];
1506 if ( Reg != PrevReg + 1)
1507 return false;
1508 PrevReg = Reg;
1509 }
1510
1511 return true;
1512 }
1513
1514 bool isInvNum() const { return Kind == k_Immediate; }
1515
1516 bool isLSAImm() const {
1517 if (!isConstantImm())
1518 return false;
1519 int64_t Val = getConstantImm();
1520 return 1 <= Val && Val <= 4;
1521 }
1522
1523 bool isRegList() const { return Kind == k_RegList; }
1524
1525 StringRef getToken() const {
1526 assert(Kind == k_Token && "Invalid access!");
1527 return StringRef(Tok.Data, Tok.Length);
1528 }
1529
1530 unsigned getReg() const override {
1531 // As a special case until we sort out the definition of div/divu, accept
1532 // $0/$zero here so that MCK_ZERO works correctly.
1533 if (Kind == k_RegisterIndex && RegIdx.Index == 0 &&
1534 RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR)
1535 return getGPR32Reg(); // FIXME: GPR64 too
1536
1537 llvm_unreachable("Invalid access!");
1538 return 0;
1539 }
1540
1541 const MCExpr *getImm() const {
1542 assert((Kind == k_Immediate) && "Invalid access!");
1543 return Imm.Val;
1544 }
1545
1546 int64_t getConstantImm() const {
1547 const MCExpr *Val = getImm();
1548 int64_t Value = 0;
1549 (void)Val->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value);
1550 return Value;
1551 }
1552
1553 MipsOperand *getMemBase() const {
1554 assert((Kind == k_Memory) && "Invalid access!");
1555 return Mem.Base;
1556 }
1557
1558 const MCExpr *getMemOff() const {
1559 assert((Kind == k_Memory) && "Invalid access!");
1560 return Mem.Off;
1561 }
1562
1563 int64_t getConstantMemOff() const {
1564 return static_cast<const MCConstantExpr *>(getMemOff())->getValue();
1565 }
1566
1567 const SmallVectorImpl<unsigned> &getRegList() const {
1568 assert((Kind == k_RegList) && "Invalid access!");
1569 return *(RegList.List);
1570 }

1572 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand> CreateToken(StringRef Str, SMLoc S,
1573 MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1574 auto Op = llvm::make_unique<MipsOperand>(k_Token, Parser);
1575 Op->Tok.Data = Str.data();
1576 Op->Tok.Length = Str.size();
1577 Op->StartLoc = S;
1578 Op->EndLoc = S;
1579 return Op;
1580 }

1582 /// Create a numeric register (e.g. $1). The exact register remains
1583 /// unresolved until an instruction successfully matches
1584 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1585 createNumericReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
1586 SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1587 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "createNumericReg(" << Index << ", ...)\n");
1588 return CreateReg(Index, Str, RegKind_Numeric, RegInfo, S, E, Parser);
1589 }

1652
1653 /// Create a register that is definitely an Cheri register.
1654 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1655 CreateCheriReg(unsigned Index, StringRef Str, const MCRegisterInfo *RegInfo,
1656 SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1657 // Turn the index into a real register index
1658 unsigned EncodedNumber = -1;
1659 // Pass along whether it was DDC or CNULL:
1660 if (Index == Mips::DDC) {
1661 EncodedNumber = 0;
1662 } else if (Index == Mips::CNULL) {
1663 EncodedNumber = 0;
1664 } else {
1665 assert(Index >= Mips::C1 && Index <= Mips::C31);
1666 EncodedNumber = Index - Mips::C1 + 1;
1667 }
1668 assert(EncodedNumber <= 31);
1669 return CreateReg(EncodedNumber, Str, RegKind_Cheri, RegInfo, S, E, Parser,
1670 Index);
1671 }
1672
1673 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1674 CreateImm(const MCExpr *Val, SMLoc S, SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1675 auto Op = llvm::make_unique<MipsOperand>(k_Immediate, Parser);
1676 Op->Imm.Val = Val;
1677 Op->StartLoc = S;
1678 Op->EndLoc = E;
1679 return Op;
1680 }
1681
1682 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1683 CreateMem(std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand> Base, const MCExpr *Off, SMLoc S,
1684 SMLoc E, MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1685 auto Op = llvm::make_unique<MipsOperand>(k_Memory, Parser);
1686 Op->Mem.Base = Base.release();
1687 Op->Mem.Off = Off;
1688 Op->StartLoc = S;
1689 Op->EndLoc = E;
1690 return Op;
1691 }
1692
1693 static std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand>
1694 CreateRegList(SmallVectorImpl<unsigned> &Regs, SMLoc StartLoc, SMLoc EndLoc,
1695 MipsAsmParser &Parser) {
1696 assert(Regs.size() > 0 && "Empty list not allowed");
1697
1698 auto Op = llvm::make_unique<MipsOperand>(k_RegList, Parser);
1699 Op->RegList.List = new SmallVector<unsigned, 10>(Regs.begin(), Regs.end());
1700 Op->StartLoc = StartLoc;
1701 Op->EndLoc = EndLoc;
1702 return Op;
1703 }
1704
1705 bool isGPRZeroAsmReg() const {
1706 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR && RegIdx.Index == 0;
1707 }
1708
1709 bool isGPRNonZeroAsmReg() const {
1710 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR && RegIdx.Index > 0 &&
1711 RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1712 }
1713
1714 bool isGPRAsmReg() const {
1715 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_GPR && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1716 }
1717 static_assert(Mips::CNULL != Mips::DDC, "DDC must not be CNULL");
1718 static_assert(Mips::C31 - Mips::C1 == 30, "Need 31 contiguous GPRS");
1719 bool isCheriAsmReg() const {
1720 bool Result = isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_Cheri &&
1721 RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(Mips::CheriGPROrCNullRegClassID)
1722 .contains(RegIdx.RealRegister);
1723 if (isRegIdx())
1724 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << __func__ << " CheriGPROrCNullRegClassID contains("
1725 << (RegIdx.RealRegister
1726 ? RegIdx.RegInfo->getName(RegIdx.RealRegister)
1727 : "<NULL>")
1728 << "=" << RegIdx.RealRegister << "): " << Result
1729 << "\n");
1730 return Result;
1731 }
1732 bool isCheriAsmReg0IsDDC() const {
1733 bool Result = isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_Cheri &&
1734 RegIdx.RegInfo->getRegClass(Mips::CheriGPROrDDCRegClassID)
1735 .contains(RegIdx.RealRegister);
1736 if (isRegIdx())
1737 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << __func__ << " CheriGPROrDDCRegClassID contains("
1738 << RegIdx.RegInfo->getName(RegIdx.RealRegister) << "="
1739 << RegIdx.RealRegister << "): " << Result << "\n");
1740 return Result;
1741 }
1742 bool isCheriHWAsmReg() const {
1743 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_CheriHWRegs && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1744 }
1745 bool isMM16AsmReg() const {
1746 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind))
1747 return false;
1748 return ((RegIdx.Index >= 2 && RegIdx.Index <= 7)
1749 || RegIdx.Index == 16 || RegIdx.Index == 17);
1750
1751 }
1752 bool isMM16AsmRegZero() const {
1753 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind))
1754 return false;
1755 return (RegIdx.Index == 0 ||
1756 (RegIdx.Index >= 2 && RegIdx.Index <= 7) ||
1757 RegIdx.Index == 17);
1758 }
1759
1760 bool isMM16AsmRegMoveP() const {
1761 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind))
1762 return false;
1763 return (RegIdx.Index == 0 || (RegIdx.Index >= 2 && RegIdx.Index <= 3) ||
1764 (RegIdx.Index >= 16 && RegIdx.Index <= 20));
1765 }
1766
1767 bool isMM16AsmRegMovePPairFirst() const {
1768 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind))
1769 return false;
1770 return RegIdx.Index >= 4 && RegIdx.Index <= 6;
1771 }
1772
1773 bool isMM16AsmRegMovePPairSecond() const {
1774 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind))
1775 return false;
1776 return (RegIdx.Index == 21 || RegIdx.Index == 22 ||
1777 (RegIdx.Index >= 5 && RegIdx.Index <= 7));
1778 }
1779
1780 bool isFGRAsmReg() const {
1781 // AFGR64 is $0-$15 but we handle this in getAFGR64()
1782 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FGR && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1783 }
1784
1785 bool isStrictlyFGRAsmReg() const {
1786 // AFGR64 is $0-$15 but we handle this in getAFGR64()
1787 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind == RegKind_FGR && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1788 }
1789
1790 bool isHWRegsAsmReg() const {
1791 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_HWRegs && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1792 }
1793
1794 bool isCheriHWRegsAsmReg() const {
1795 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_CheriHWRegs && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1796 }
1797
1798 bool isCCRAsmReg() const {
1799 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_CCR && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1800 }
1801
1802 bool isFCCAsmReg() const {
1803 if (!(isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_FCC))
1804 return false;
1805 return RegIdx.Index <= 7;
1806 }
1807
1808 bool isACCAsmReg() const {
1809 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_ACC && RegIdx.Index <= 3;
1810 }
1811
1812 bool isCOP0AsmReg() const {
1813 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_COP0 && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1814 }
1815
1816 bool isCOP2AsmReg() const {
1817 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_COP2 && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1818 }
1819
1820 bool isCOP3AsmReg() const {
1821 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_COP3 && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1822 }
1823
1824 bool isMSA128AsmReg() const {
1825 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_MSA128 && RegIdx.Index <= 31;
1826 }
1827
1828 bool isMSACtrlAsmReg() const {
1829 return isRegIdx() && RegIdx.Kind & RegKind_MSACtrl && RegIdx.Index <= 7;
1830 }
1831
1832 /// getStartLoc - Get the location of the first token of this operand.
1833 SMLoc getStartLoc() const override { return StartLoc; }
1834 /// getEndLoc - Get the location of the last token of this operand.
1835 SMLoc getEndLoc() const override { return EndLoc; }
1836
1837 void print(raw_ostream &OS) const override {
1838 switch (Kind) {
1839 case k_Immediate:
1840 OS << "Imm<";
1841 OS << *Imm.Val;
1842 OS << ">";
1843 break;
1844 case k_Memory:
1845 OS << "Mem<";
1846 Mem.Base->print(OS);
1847 OS << ", ";
1848 OS << *Mem.Off;
1849 OS << ">";
1850 break;
1851 case k_RegisterIndex:
1852 OS << "RegIdx<" << RegIdx.Index << ":" << RegIdx.Kind << ", "
1853 << StringRef(RegIdx.Tok.Data, RegIdx.Tok.Length) << ">";
1854 break;
1855 case k_Token:
1856 OS << getToken();
1857 break;
1858 case k_RegList:
1859 OS << "RegList< ";
1860 for (auto Reg : (*RegList.List))
1861 OS << Reg << " ";
1862 OS << ">";
1863 break;
1864 }
1865 }
1866
1867 bool isValidForTie(const MipsOperand &Other) const {
1868 if (Kind != Other.Kind)
1869 return false;
1870
1871 switch (Kind) {
1872 default:
1873 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected kind");
1874 return false;
1875 case k_RegisterIndex: {
1876 StringRef Token(RegIdx.Tok.Data, RegIdx.Tok.Length);
1877 StringRef OtherToken(Other.RegIdx.Tok.Data, Other.RegIdx.Tok.Length);
1878 return Token == OtherToken;
1879 }
1880 }
1881 }
1882}; // class MipsOperand
1883
1884} // end anonymous namespace
1885
1886namespace llvm {
1887
1888extern const MCInstrDesc MipsInsts[];
1889
1890} // end namespace llvm
1891
1892static const MCInstrDesc &getInstDesc(unsigned Opcode) {
1893 return MipsInsts[Opcode];
1894}
1895
1896static bool hasShortDelaySlot(MCInst &Inst) {
1897 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
1898 case Mips::BEQ_MM:
1899 case Mips::BNE_MM:
1900 case Mips::BLTZ_MM:
1901 case Mips::BGEZ_MM:
1902 case Mips::BLEZ_MM:
1903 case Mips::BGTZ_MM:
1904 case Mips::JRC16_MM:
1905 case Mips::JALS_MM:
1906 case Mips::JALRS_MM:
1907 case Mips::JALRS16_MM:
1908 case Mips::BGEZALS_MM:
1909 case Mips::BLTZALS_MM:
1910 return true;
1911 case Mips::J_MM:
1912 return !Inst.getOperand(0).isReg();
1913 default:
1914 return false;
1915 }
1916}
1917
1918static const MCSymbol *getSingleMCSymbol(const MCExpr *Expr) {
1919 if (const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRExpr = dyn_cast<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Expr)) {
1920 return &SRExpr->getSymbol();
1921 }
1922
1923 if (const MCBinaryExpr *BExpr = dyn_cast<MCBinaryExpr>(Expr)) {
1924 const MCSymbol *LHSSym = getSingleMCSymbol(BExpr->getLHS());
1925 const MCSymbol *RHSSym = getSingleMCSymbol(BExpr->getRHS());
1926
1927 if (LHSSym)
1928 return LHSSym;
1929
1930 if (RHSSym)
1931 return RHSSym;
1932
1933 return nullptr;
1934 }
1935
1936 if (const MCUnaryExpr *UExpr = dyn_cast<MCUnaryExpr>(Expr))
1937 return getSingleMCSymbol(UExpr->getSubExpr());
1938
1939 return nullptr;
1940}
1941
1942static unsigned countMCSymbolRefExpr(const MCExpr *Expr) {
1943 if (isa<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Expr))
1944 return 1;
1945
1946 if (const MCBinaryExpr *BExpr = dyn_cast<MCBinaryExpr>(Expr))
1947 return countMCSymbolRefExpr(BExpr->getLHS()) +
1948 countMCSymbolRefExpr(BExpr->getRHS());
1949
1950 if (const MCUnaryExpr *UExpr = dyn_cast<MCUnaryExpr>(Expr))
1951 return countMCSymbolRefExpr(UExpr->getSubExpr());
1952
1953 return 0;
1954}
1955
1956bool MipsAsmParser::processInstruction(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
1957 MCStreamer &Out,
1958 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
1959 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
1960 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = getInstDesc(Inst.getOpcode());
1961 bool ExpandedJalSym = false;
1962
1963 Inst.setLoc(IDLoc);
1964
1965 if (MCID.isBranch() || MCID.isCall()) {
1966 const unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
1967 MCOperand Offset;
1968
1969 switch (Opcode) {
1970 default:
1971 break;
1972 case Mips::BBIT0:
1973 case Mips::BBIT032:
1974 case Mips::BBIT1:
1975 case Mips::BBIT132:
1976 assert(hasCnMips() && "instruction only valid for octeon cpus");
1977 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1978
1979 case Mips::BEQ:
1980 case Mips::BNE:
1981 case Mips::BEQ_MM:
1982 case Mips::BNE_MM:
1983 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 3 && "unexpected number of operands");
1984 Offset = Inst.getOperand(2);
1985 if (!Offset.isImm())
1986 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
1987 if (!isIntN(inMicroMipsMode() ? 17 : 18, Offset.getImm()))
1988 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
1989 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(),
1990 1LL << (inMicroMipsMode() ? 1 : 2)))
1991 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
1992 break;
1993 case Mips::BGEZ:
1994 case Mips::BGTZ:
1995 case Mips::BLEZ:
1996 case Mips::BLTZ:
1997 case Mips::BGEZAL:
1998 case Mips::BLTZAL:
1999 case Mips::BC1F:
2000 case Mips::BC1T:
2001 case Mips::BGEZ_MM:
2002 case Mips::BGTZ_MM:
2003 case Mips::BLEZ_MM:
2004 case Mips::BLTZ_MM:
2005 case Mips::BGEZAL_MM:
2006 case Mips::BLTZAL_MM:
2007 case Mips::BC1F_MM:
2008 case Mips::BC1T_MM:
2009 case Mips::BC1EQZC_MMR6:
2010 case Mips::BC1NEZC_MMR6:
2011 case Mips::BC2EQZC_MMR6:
2012 case Mips::BC2NEZC_MMR6:
2013 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 2 && "unexpected number of operands");
2014 Offset = Inst.getOperand(1);
2015 if (!Offset.isImm())
2016 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
2017 if (!isIntN(inMicroMipsMode() ? 17 : 18, Offset.getImm()))
2018 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
2019 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(),
2020 1LL << (inMicroMipsMode() ? 1 : 2)))
2021 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
2022 break;
2023 case Mips::BGEC: case Mips::BGEC_MMR6:
2024 case Mips::BLTC: case Mips::BLTC_MMR6:
2025 case Mips::BGEUC: case Mips::BGEUC_MMR6:
2026 case Mips::BLTUC: case Mips::BLTUC_MMR6:
2027 case Mips::BEQC: case Mips::BEQC_MMR6:
2028 case Mips::BNEC: case Mips::BNEC_MMR6:
2029 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 3 && "unexpected number of operands");
2030 Offset = Inst.getOperand(2);
2031 if (!Offset.isImm())
2032 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
2033 if (!isIntN(18, Offset.getImm()))
2034 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
2035 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(), 1LL << 2))
2036 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
2037 break;
2038 case Mips::BLEZC: case Mips::BLEZC_MMR6:
2039 case Mips::BGEZC: case Mips::BGEZC_MMR6:
2040 case Mips::BGTZC: case Mips::BGTZC_MMR6:
2041 case Mips::BLTZC: case Mips::BLTZC_MMR6:
2042 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 2 && "unexpected number of operands");
2043 Offset = Inst.getOperand(1);
2044 if (!Offset.isImm())
2045 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
2046 if (!isIntN(18, Offset.getImm()))
2047 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
2048 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(), 1LL << 2))
2049 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
2050 break;
2051 case Mips::BEQZC: case Mips::BEQZC_MMR6:
2052 case Mips::BNEZC: case Mips::BNEZC_MMR6:
2053 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 2 && "unexpected number of operands");
2054 Offset = Inst.getOperand(1);
2055 if (!Offset.isImm())
2056 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
2057 if (!isIntN(23, Offset.getImm()))
2058 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
2059 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(), 1LL << 2))
2060 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
2061 break;
2062 case Mips::BEQZ16_MM:
2063 case Mips::BEQZC16_MMR6:
2064 case Mips::BNEZ16_MM:
2065 case Mips::BNEZC16_MMR6:
2066 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 2 && "unexpected number of operands");
2067 Offset = Inst.getOperand(1);
2068 if (!Offset.isImm())
2069 break; // We'll deal with this situation later on when applying fixups.
2070 if (!isInt<8>(Offset.getImm()))
2071 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
2072 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(), 2LL))
2073 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
2074 break;
2075 }
2076 }
2077
2078 // SSNOP is deprecated on MIPS32r6/MIPS64r6
2079 // We still accept it but it is a normal nop.
2080 if (hasMips32r6() && Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::SSNOP) {
2081 std::string ISA = hasMips64r6() ? "MIPS64r6" : "MIPS32r6";
2082 Warning(IDLoc, "ssnop is deprecated for " + ISA + " and is equivalent to a "
2083 "nop instruction");
2084 }
2085
2086 if (hasCnMips()) {
2087 const unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
2088 MCOperand Opnd;
2089 int Imm;
2090
2091 switch (Opcode) {
2092 default:
2093 break;
2094
2095 case Mips::BBIT0:
2096 case Mips::BBIT032:
2097 case Mips::BBIT1:
2098 case Mips::BBIT132:
2099 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 3 && "unexpected number of operands");
2100 // The offset is handled above
2101 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(1);
2102 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2103 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2104 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2105 if (Imm < 0 || Imm > (Opcode == Mips::BBIT0 ||
2106 Opcode == Mips::BBIT1 ? 63 : 31))
2107 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2108 if (Imm > 31) {
2109 Inst.setOpcode(Opcode == Mips::BBIT0 ? Mips::BBIT032
2110 : Mips::BBIT132);
2111 Inst.getOperand(1).setImm(Imm - 32);
2112 }
2113 break;
2114
2115 case Mips::SEQi:
2116 case Mips::SNEi:
2117 assert(MCID.getNumOperands() == 3 && "unexpected number of operands");
2118 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2119 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2120 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2121 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2122 if (!isInt<10>(Imm))
2123 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2124 break;
2125 }
2126 }
2127
2128 // Warn on division by zero. We're checking here as all instructions get
2129 // processed here, not just the macros that need expansion.
2130 //
2131 // The MIPS backend models most of the divison instructions and macros as
2132 // three operand instructions. The pre-R6 divide instructions however have
2133 // two operands and explicitly define HI/LO as part of the instruction,
2134 // not in the operands.
2135 unsigned FirstOp = 1;
2136 unsigned SecondOp = 2;
2137 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
2138 default:
2139 break;
2140 case Mips::SDivIMacro:
2141 case Mips::UDivIMacro:
2142 case Mips::DSDivIMacro:
2143 case Mips::DUDivIMacro:
2144 if (Inst.getOperand(2).getImm() == 0) {
2145 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
2146 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
2147 Warning(IDLoc, "dividing zero by zero");
2148 else
2149 Warning(IDLoc, "division by zero");
2150 }
2151 break;
2152 case Mips::DSDIV:
2153 case Mips::SDIV:
2154 case Mips::UDIV:
2155 case Mips::DUDIV:
2156 case Mips::UDIV_MM:
2157 case Mips::SDIV_MM:
2158 FirstOp = 0;
2159 SecondOp = 1;
2160 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2161 case Mips::SDivMacro:
2162 case Mips::DSDivMacro:
2163 case Mips::UDivMacro:
2164 case Mips::DUDivMacro:
2165 case Mips::DIV:
2166 case Mips::DIVU:
2167 case Mips::DDIV:
2168 case Mips::DDIVU:
2169 case Mips::DIVU_MMR6:
2170 case Mips::DIV_MMR6:
2171 if (Inst.getOperand(SecondOp).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
2172 Inst.getOperand(SecondOp).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64) {
2173 if (Inst.getOperand(FirstOp).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
2174 Inst.getOperand(FirstOp).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
2175 Warning(IDLoc, "dividing zero by zero");
2176 else
2177 Warning(IDLoc, "division by zero");
2178 }
2179 break;
2180 }
2181
2182 // For PIC code convert unconditional jump to unconditional branch.
2183 if ((Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::J || Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::J_MM) &&
2184 inPicMode()) {
2185 MCInst BInst;
2186 BInst.setOpcode(inMicroMipsMode() ? Mips::BEQ_MM : Mips::BEQ);
2187 BInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO));
2188 BInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO));
2189 BInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
2190 Inst = BInst;
2191 }
2192
2193 // This expansion is not in a function called by tryExpandInstruction()
2194 // because the pseudo-instruction doesn't have a distinct opcode.
2195 if ((Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::JAL || Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::JAL_MM) &&
2196 inPicMode()) {
2197 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
2198
2199 const MCExpr *JalExpr = Inst.getOperand(0).getExpr();
2200
2201 // We can do this expansion if there's only 1 symbol in the argument
2202 // expression.
2203 if (countMCSymbolRefExpr(JalExpr) > 1)
2204 return Error(IDLoc, "jal doesn't support multiple symbols in PIC mode");
2205
2206 // FIXME: This is checking the expression can be handled by the later stages
2207 // of the assembler. We ought to leave it to those later stages.
2208 const MCSymbol *JalSym = getSingleMCSymbol(JalExpr);
2209
2210 // FIXME: Add support for label+offset operands (currently causes an error).
2211 // FIXME: Add support for forward-declared local symbols.
2212 // FIXME: Add expansion for when the LargeGOT option is enabled.
2213 if (JalSym->isInSection() || JalSym->isTemporary() ||
2214 (JalSym->isELF() &&
2215 cast<MCSymbolELF>(JalSym)->getBinding() == ELF::STB_LOCAL)) {
2216 if (isABI_O32()) {
2217 // If it's a local symbol and the O32 ABI is being used, we expand to:
2218 // lw $25, 0($gp)
2219 // R_(MICRO)MIPS_GOT16 label
2220 // addiu $25, $25, 0
2221 // R_(MICRO)MIPS_LO16 label
2222 // jalr $25
2223 const MCExpr *Got16RelocExpr =
2224 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT, JalExpr, getContext());
2225 const MCExpr *Lo16RelocExpr =
2226 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, JalExpr, getContext());
2227
2228 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::LW, Mips::T9, Mips::GP,
2229 MCOperand::createExpr(Got16RelocExpr), IDLoc, STI);
2230 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::ADDiu, Mips::T9, Mips::T9,
2231 MCOperand::createExpr(Lo16RelocExpr), IDLoc, STI);
2232 } else if (isABI_N32() || isABI_N64()) {
2233 // If it's a local symbol and the N32/N64 ABIs are being used,
2234 // we expand to:
2235 // lw/ld $25, 0($gp)
2236 // R_(MICRO)MIPS_GOT_DISP label
2237 // jalr $25
2238 const MCExpr *GotDispRelocExpr =
2239 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_DISP, JalExpr, getContext());
2240
2241 TOut.emitRRX(ABI.ArePtrs64bit() ? Mips::LD : Mips::LW, Mips::T9,
2242 Mips::GP, MCOperand::createExpr(GotDispRelocExpr), IDLoc,
2243 STI);
2244 }
2245 } else {
2246 // If it's an external/weak symbol, we expand to:
2247 // lw/ld $25, 0($gp)
2248 // R_(MICRO)MIPS_CALL16 label
2249 // jalr $25
2250 const MCExpr *Call16RelocExpr =
2251 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_CALL, JalExpr, getContext());
2252
2253 TOut.emitRRX(ABI.ArePtrs64bit() ? Mips::LD : Mips::LW, Mips::T9, Mips::GP,
2254 MCOperand::createExpr(Call16RelocExpr), IDLoc, STI);
2255 }
2256
2257 MCInst JalrInst;
2258 if (IsCpRestoreSet && inMicroMipsMode())
2259 JalrInst.setOpcode(Mips::JALRS_MM);
2260 else
2261 JalrInst.setOpcode(inMicroMipsMode() ? Mips::JALR_MM : Mips::JALR);
2262 JalrInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::RA));
2263 JalrInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::T9));
2264
2265 if (EmitJalrReloc) {
2266 // As an optimization hint for the linker, before the JALR we add:
2267 // .reloc tmplabel, R_{MICRO}MIPS_JALR, symbol
2268 // tmplabel:
2269 MCSymbol *TmpLabel = getContext().createTempSymbol();
2270 const MCExpr *TmpExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TmpLabel, getContext());
2271 const MCExpr *RelocJalrExpr =
2272 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(JalSym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None,
2273 getContext(), IDLoc);
2274
2275 TOut.getStreamer().EmitRelocDirective(*TmpExpr,
2276 inMicroMipsMode() ? "R_MICROMIPS_JALR" : "R_MIPS_JALR",
2277 RelocJalrExpr, IDLoc, *STI);
2278 TOut.getStreamer().EmitLabel(TmpLabel);
2279 }
2280
2281 Inst = JalrInst;
2282 ExpandedJalSym = true;
2283 }
2284
2285 bool IsPCRelativeLoad = (MCID.TSFlags & MipsII::IsPCRelativeLoad) != 0;
2286 if ((MCID.mayLoad() || MCID.mayStore()) && !IsPCRelativeLoad) {
2287 // Check the offset of memory operand, if it is a symbol
2288 // reference or immediate we may have to expand instructions.
2289 for (unsigned i = 0; i < MCID.getNumOperands(); i++) {
2290 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo = MCID.OpInfo[i];
2291 if ((OpInfo.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_MEMORY) ||
2292 (OpInfo.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_UNKNOWN)) {
2293 MCOperand &Op = Inst.getOperand(i);
2294 if (Op.isImm()) {
2295 int64_t MemOffset = Op.getImm();
2296 if (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::STORECAP_BigImm ||
2297 Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::LOADCAP_BigImm) {
2298 // New clc/csc instructions can have bigger than 16-bit immediates
2299 continue;
2300 }
2301 if (MemOffset < -32768 || MemOffset > 32767) {
2302 // Offset can't exceed 16bit value.
2303 expandMemInst(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, MCID.mayLoad());
2304 return getParser().hasPendingError();
2305 }
2306 } else if (Op.isExpr()) {
2307 const MCExpr *Expr = Op.getExpr();
2308 if (Expr->getKind() == MCExpr::SymbolRef) {
2309 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SR =
2310 static_cast<const MCSymbolRefExpr *>(Expr);
2311 if (SR->getKind() == MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None) {
2312 // Expand symbol.
2313 expandMemInst(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, MCID.mayLoad());
2314 return getParser().hasPendingError();
2315 }
2316 } else if (!isEvaluated(Expr)) {
2317 expandMemInst(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, MCID.mayLoad());
2318 return getParser().hasPendingError();
2319 }
2320 }
2321 }
2322 } // for
2323 } // if load/store
2324
2325 if (inMicroMipsMode()) {
2326 if (MCID.mayLoad() && Inst.getOpcode() != Mips::LWP_MM) {
2327 // Try to create 16-bit GP relative load instruction.
2328 for (unsigned i = 0; i < MCID.getNumOperands(); i++) {
2329 const MCOperandInfo &OpInfo = MCID.OpInfo[i];
2330 if ((OpInfo.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_MEMORY) ||
2331 (OpInfo.OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_UNKNOWN)) {
2332 MCOperand &Op = Inst.getOperand(i);
2333 if (Op.isImm()) {
2334 int MemOffset = Op.getImm();
2335 MCOperand &DstReg = Inst.getOperand(0);
2336 MCOperand &BaseReg = Inst.getOperand(1);
2337 if (isInt<9>(MemOffset) && (MemOffset % 4 == 0) &&
2338 getContext().getRegisterInfo()->getRegClass(
2339 Mips::GPRMM16RegClassID).contains(DstReg.getReg()) &&
2340 (BaseReg.getReg() == Mips::GP ||
2341 BaseReg.getReg() == Mips::GP_64)) {
2342
2343 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::LWGP_MM, DstReg.getReg(), Mips::GP, MemOffset,
2344 IDLoc, STI);
2345 return false;
2346 }
2347 }
2348 }
2349 } // for
2350 } // if load
2351
2352 // TODO: Handle this with the AsmOperandClass.PredicateMethod.
2353
2354 MCOperand Opnd;
2355 int Imm;
2356
2357 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
2358 default:
2359 break;
2360 case Mips::ADDIUSP_MM:
2361 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(0);
2362 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2363 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2364 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2365 if (Imm < -1032 || Imm > 1028 || (Imm < 8 && Imm > -12) ||
2366 Imm % 4 != 0)
2367 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2368 break;
2369 case Mips::SLL16_MM:
2370 case Mips::SRL16_MM:
2371 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2372 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2373 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2374 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2375 if (Imm < 1 || Imm > 8)
2376 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2377 break;
2378 case Mips::LI16_MM:
2379 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(1);
2380 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2381 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2382 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2383 if (Imm < -1 || Imm > 126)
2384 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2385 break;
2386 case Mips::ADDIUR2_MM:
2387 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2388 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2389 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2390 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2391 if (!(Imm == 1 || Imm == -1 ||
2392 ((Imm % 4 == 0) && Imm < 28 && Imm > 0)))
2393 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2394 break;
2395 case Mips::ANDI16_MM:
2396 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2397 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2398 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2399 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2400 if (!(Imm == 128 || (Imm >= 1 && Imm <= 4) || Imm == 7 || Imm == 8 ||
2401 Imm == 15 || Imm == 16 || Imm == 31 || Imm == 32 || Imm == 63 ||
2402 Imm == 64 || Imm == 255 || Imm == 32768 || Imm == 65535))
2403 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2404 break;
2405 case Mips::LBU16_MM:
2406 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2407 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2408 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2409 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2410 if (Imm < -1 || Imm > 14)
2411 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2412 break;
2413 case Mips::SB16_MM:
2414 case Mips::SB16_MMR6:
2415 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2416 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2417 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2418 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2419 if (Imm < 0 || Imm > 15)
2420 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2421 break;
2422 case Mips::LHU16_MM:
2423 case Mips::SH16_MM:
2424 case Mips::SH16_MMR6:
2425 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2426 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2427 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2428 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2429 if (Imm < 0 || Imm > 30 || (Imm % 2 != 0))
2430 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2431 break;
2432 case Mips::LW16_MM:
2433 case Mips::SW16_MM:
2434 case Mips::SW16_MMR6:
2435 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2436 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2437 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2438 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2439 if (Imm < 0 || Imm > 60 || (Imm % 4 != 0))
2440 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2441 break;
2442 case Mips::ADDIUPC_MM:
2443 Opnd = Inst.getOperand(1);
2444 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2445 return Error(IDLoc, "expected immediate operand kind");
2446 Imm = Opnd.getImm();
2447 if ((Imm % 4 != 0) || !isInt<25>(Imm))
2448 return Error(IDLoc, "immediate operand value out of range");
2449 break;
2450 case Mips::LWP_MM:
2451 case Mips::SWP_MM:
2452 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Mips::RA)
2453 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid operand for instruction");
2454 break;
2455 case Mips::MOVEP_MM:
2456 case Mips::MOVEP_MMR6: {
2457 unsigned R0 = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
2458 unsigned R1 = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
2459 bool RegPair = ((R0 == Mips::A1 && R1 == Mips::A2) ||
2460 (R0 == Mips::A1 && R1 == Mips::A3) ||
2461 (R0 == Mips::A2 && R1 == Mips::A3) ||
2462 (R0 == Mips::A0 && R1 == Mips::S5) ||
2463 (R0 == Mips::A0 && R1 == Mips::S6) ||
2464 (R0 == Mips::A0 && R1 == Mips::A1) ||
2465 (R0 == Mips::A0 && R1 == Mips::A2) ||
2466 (R0 == Mips::A0 && R1 == Mips::A3));
2467 if (!RegPair)
2468 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid operand for instruction");
2469 break;
2470 }
2471 }
2472 }
2473
2474 // prevent invalid relocations in CHERI load/store instruction
2475 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
2476 default:
2477 break;
2478
2479 case Mips::CAPLOAD8:
2480 case Mips::CAPLOAD16:
2481 case Mips::CAPLOAD32:
2482 case Mips::CAPLOAD64:
2483 case Mips::CAPLOAD832:
2484 case Mips::CAPLOAD1632:
2485 case Mips::CAPLOAD3264:
2486 case Mips::CAPLOADU8:
2487 case Mips::CAPLOADU16:
2488 case Mips::CAPLOADU32:
2489 case Mips::CAPLOADU832:
2490 case Mips::CAPLOADU1632:
2491 case Mips::CAPSTORE8:
2492 case Mips::CAPSTORE832:
2493 case Mips::CAPSTORE16:
2494 case Mips::CAPSTORE1632:
2495 case Mips::CAPSTORE32:
2496 case Mips::CAPSTORE3264:
2497 case Mips::CAPSTORE64:
2498 // For CIncOffsetImm/CSetBoundsImm/CCallSelector we also need to check that
2499 // operand two is actually an immediate.
2500 case Mips::CIncOffsetImm:
2501 case Mips::CSetBoundsImm:
2502 case Mips::CCall:
2503 {
2504 const MCOperand &Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2505 if (!Opnd.isImm())
2506 return Error(Opnd.isExpr() ? Opnd.getExpr()->getLoc() : IDLoc,
2507 "expected immediate operand kind");
2508 break;
2509 }
2510
2511 // The clc/csc instructions can use some relocations:
2512 case Mips::STORECAP:
2513 case Mips::LOADCAP: {
2514 const MCOperand &Opnd = Inst.getOperand(2);
2515 // allow captable relocations:
2516 SMLoc ErrLoc = IDLoc;
2517 bool ValidRelocation = false;
2518 if (Opnd.isExpr()) {
2519 ErrLoc = Opnd.getExpr()->getLoc();
2520 if (auto Expr = dyn_cast<MipsMCExpr>(Opnd.getExpr()))
2521 ValidRelocation = Expr->getKind() == MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTABLE11 ||
2522 Expr->getKind() == MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPCALL11;
2523 }
2524 if (!ValidRelocation && !Opnd.isImm())
2525 return Error(ErrLoc,
2526 "expected immediate operand or valid relocation type");
2527 break;
2528 }
2529 case Mips::STORECAP_BigImm:
2530 case Mips::LOADCAP_BigImm: {
2531 const MCOperand &Opnd = Inst.getOperand(1);
2532 SMLoc ErrLoc = IDLoc;
2533 bool ValidRelocation = false;
2534 if (Opnd.isExpr()) {
2535 ErrLoc = Opnd.getExpr()->getLoc();
2536 if (auto Expr = dyn_cast<MipsMCExpr>(Opnd.getExpr()))
2537 ValidRelocation = Expr->getKind() == MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPTABLE20 ||
2538 Expr->getKind() == MipsMCExpr::MEK_CAPCALL20;
2539 }
2540 if (!ValidRelocation && !Opnd.isImm())
2541 return Error(ErrLoc,
2542 "expected immediate operand or valid relocation type");
2543 break;
2544 }
2545 }
2546
2547 bool FillDelaySlot =
2548 MCID.hasDelaySlot() && AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder();
2549 if (FillDelaySlot)
2550 TOut.emitDirectiveSetNoReorder();
2551
2552 MacroExpanderResultTy ExpandResult =
2553 tryExpandInstruction(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI);
2554 switch (ExpandResult) {
2555 case MER_NotAMacro:
2556 Out.EmitInstruction(Inst, *STI);
2557 break;
2558 case MER_Success:
2559 break;
2560 case MER_Fail:
2561 return true;
2562 }
2563
2564 // We know we emitted an instruction on the MER_NotAMacro or MER_Success path.
2565 // If we're in microMIPS mode then we must also set EF_MIPS_MICROMIPS.
2566 if (inMicroMipsMode()) {
2567 TOut.setUsesMicroMips();
2568 TOut.updateABIInfo(*this);
2569 }
2570
2571 // If this instruction has a delay slot and .set reorder is active,
2572 // emit a NOP after it.
2573 if (FillDelaySlot) {
2574 TOut.emitEmptyDelaySlot(hasShortDelaySlot(Inst), IDLoc, STI);
2575 TOut.emitDirectiveSetReorder();
2576 }
2577
2578 if ((Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::JalOneReg ||
2579 Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::JalTwoReg || ExpandedJalSym) &&
2580 isPicAndNotNxxAbi()) {
2581 if (IsCpRestoreSet) {
2582 // We need a NOP between the JALR and the LW:
2583 // If .set reorder has been used, we've already emitted a NOP.
2584 // If .set noreorder has been used, we need to emit a NOP at this point.
2585 if (!AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder())
2586 TOut.emitEmptyDelaySlot(hasShortDelaySlot(Inst), IDLoc,
2587 STI);
2588
2589 // Load the $gp from the stack.
2590 TOut.emitGPRestore(CpRestoreOffset, IDLoc, STI);
2591 } else
2592 Warning(IDLoc, "no .cprestore used in PIC mode");
2593 }
2594
2595 return false;
2596}
2597
2598MipsAsmParser::MacroExpanderResultTy
2599MipsAsmParser::tryExpandInstruction(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
2600 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2601 bool is64Bit = true;
2602 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
2603 default:
2604 return MER_NotAMacro;
2605 case Mips::LoadImm32:
2606 return expandLoadImm(Inst, true, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2607 case Mips::LoadImm64:
2608 return expandLoadImm(Inst, false, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2609 case Mips::LoadAddrImm32:
2610 case Mips::LoadAddrImm64:
2611 assert(Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
2612 assert((Inst.getOperand(1).isImm() || Inst.getOperand(1).isExpr()) &&
2613 "expected immediate operand kind");
2614
2615 return expandLoadAddress(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(), Mips::NoRegister,
2616 Inst.getOperand(1),
2617 Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::LoadAddrImm32, IDLoc,
2618 Out, STI)
2619 ? MER_Fail
2620 : MER_Success;
2621 case Mips::CLWC1:
2622 is64Bit = false;
2623 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2624 case Mips::CLDC1:
2625 return expandCapLoadC1(Inst, IDLoc, is64Bit, Out, STI);
2626 case Mips::CSWC1:
2627 is64Bit = false;
2628 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2629 case Mips::CSDC1:
2630 return expandCapStoreC1(Inst, IDLoc, is64Bit, Out, STI);
2631 case Mips::LoadAddrReg32:
2632 case Mips::LoadAddrReg64:
2633 assert(Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
2634 assert(Inst.getOperand(1).isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
2635 assert((Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() || Inst.getOperand(2).isExpr()) &&
2636 "expected immediate operand kind");
2637
2638 return expandLoadAddress(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(),
2639 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(), Inst.getOperand(2),
2640 Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::LoadAddrReg32, IDLoc,
2641 Out, STI)
2642 ? MER_Fail
2643 : MER_Success;
2644 case Mips::B_MM_Pseudo:
2645 case Mips::B_MMR6_Pseudo:
2646 return expandUncondBranchMMPseudo(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2647 : MER_Success;
2648 case Mips::SWM_MM:
2649 case Mips::LWM_MM:
2650 return expandLoadStoreMultiple(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2651 : MER_Success;
2652 case Mips::JalOneReg:
2653 case Mips::JalTwoReg:
2654 return expandJalWithRegs(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2655 case Mips::BneImm:
2656 case Mips::BeqImm:
2657 case Mips::BEQLImmMacro:
2658 case Mips::BNELImmMacro:
2659 return expandBranchImm(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2660 case Mips::BLT:
2661 case Mips::BLE:
2662 case Mips::BGE:
2663 case Mips::BGT:
2664 case Mips::BLTU:
2665 case Mips::BLEU:
2666 case Mips::BGEU:
2667 case Mips::BGTU:
2668 case Mips::BLTL:
2669 case Mips::BLEL:
2670 case Mips::BGEL:
2671 case Mips::BGTL:
2672 case Mips::BLTUL:
2673 case Mips::BLEUL:
2674 case Mips::BGEUL:
2675 case Mips::BGTUL:
2676 case Mips::BLTImmMacro:
2677 case Mips::BLEImmMacro:
2678 case Mips::BGEImmMacro:
2679 case Mips::BGTImmMacro:
2680 case Mips::BLTUImmMacro:
2681 case Mips::BLEUImmMacro:
2682 case Mips::BGEUImmMacro:
2683 case Mips::BGTUImmMacro:
2684 case Mips::BLTLImmMacro:
2685 case Mips::BLELImmMacro:
2686 case Mips::BGELImmMacro:
2687 case Mips::BGTLImmMacro:
2688 case Mips::BLTULImmMacro:
2689 case Mips::BLEULImmMacro:
2690 case Mips::BGEULImmMacro:
2691 case Mips::BGTULImmMacro:
2692 return expandCondBranches(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2693 case Mips::SDivMacro:
2694 case Mips::SDivIMacro:
2695 case Mips::SRemMacro:
2696 case Mips::SRemIMacro:
2697 return expandDivRem(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, false, true) ? MER_Fail
2698 : MER_Success;
2699 case Mips::DSDivMacro:
2700 case Mips::DSDivIMacro:
2701 case Mips::DSRemMacro:
2702 case Mips::DSRemIMacro:
2703 return expandDivRem(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, true, true) ? MER_Fail
2704 : MER_Success;
2705 case Mips::UDivMacro:
2706 case Mips::UDivIMacro:
2707 case Mips::URemMacro:
2708 case Mips::URemIMacro:
2709 return expandDivRem(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, false, false) ? MER_Fail
2710 : MER_Success;
2711 case Mips::DUDivMacro:
2712 case Mips::DUDivIMacro:
2713 case Mips::DURemMacro:
2714 case Mips::DURemIMacro:
2715 return expandDivRem(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI, true, false) ? MER_Fail
2716 : MER_Success;
2717 case Mips::PseudoTRUNC_W_S:
2718 return expandTrunc(Inst, false, false, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2719 : MER_Success;
2720 case Mips::PseudoTRUNC_W_D32:
2721 return expandTrunc(Inst, true, false, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2722 : MER_Success;
2723 case Mips::PseudoTRUNC_W_D:
2724 return expandTrunc(Inst, true, true, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2725 : MER_Success;
2726
2727 case Mips::LoadImmSingleGPR:
2728 return expandLoadImmReal(Inst, true, true, false, IDLoc, Out, STI)
2729 ? MER_Fail
2730 : MER_Success;
2731 case Mips::LoadImmSingleFGR:
2732 return expandLoadImmReal(Inst, true, false, false, IDLoc, Out, STI)
2733 ? MER_Fail
2734 : MER_Success;
2735 case Mips::LoadImmDoubleGPR:
2736 return expandLoadImmReal(Inst, false, true, false, IDLoc, Out, STI)
2737 ? MER_Fail
2738 : MER_Success;
2739 case Mips::LoadImmDoubleFGR:
2740 return expandLoadImmReal(Inst, false, false, true, IDLoc, Out, STI)
2741 ? MER_Fail
2742 : MER_Success;
2743 case Mips::LoadImmDoubleFGR_32:
2744 return expandLoadImmReal(Inst, false, false, false, IDLoc, Out, STI)
2745 ? MER_Fail
2746 : MER_Success;
2747 case Mips::Ulh:
2748 return expandUlh(Inst, true, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2749 case Mips::Ulhu:
2750 return expandUlh(Inst, false, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2751 case Mips::Ush:
2752 return expandUsh(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2753 case Mips::Ulw:
2754 case Mips::Usw:
2755 return expandUxw(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2756 case Mips::NORImm:
2757 case Mips::NORImm64:
2758 return expandAliasImmediate(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2759 case Mips::SLTImm64:
2760 if (isInt<16>(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm())) {
2761 Inst.setOpcode(Mips::SLTi64);
2762 return MER_NotAMacro;
2763 }
2764 return expandAliasImmediate(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2765 case Mips::SLTUImm64:
2766 if (isInt<16>(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm())) {
2767 Inst.setOpcode(Mips::SLTiu64);
2768 return MER_NotAMacro;
2769 }
2770 return expandAliasImmediate(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2771 case Mips::ADDi: case Mips::ADDi_MM:
2772 case Mips::ADDiu: case Mips::ADDiu_MM:
2773 case Mips::SLTi: case Mips::SLTi_MM:
2774 case Mips::SLTiu: case Mips::SLTiu_MM:
2775 if ((Inst.getNumOperands() == 3) && Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() &&
2776 Inst.getOperand(1).isReg() && Inst.getOperand(2).isImm()) {
2777 int64_t ImmValue = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
2778 if (isInt<16>(ImmValue))
2779 return MER_NotAMacro;
2780 return expandAliasImmediate(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2781 : MER_Success;
2782 }
2783 return MER_NotAMacro;
2784 case Mips::ANDi: case Mips::ANDi_MM: case Mips::ANDi64:
2785 case Mips::ORi: case Mips::ORi_MM: case Mips::ORi64:
2786 case Mips::XORi: case Mips::XORi_MM: case Mips::XORi64:
2787 if ((Inst.getNumOperands() == 3) && Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() &&
2788 Inst.getOperand(1).isReg() && Inst.getOperand(2).isImm()) {
2789 int64_t ImmValue = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
2790 if (isUInt<16>(ImmValue))
2791 return MER_NotAMacro;
2792 return expandAliasImmediate(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail
2793 : MER_Success;
2794 }
2795 return MER_NotAMacro;
2796 case Mips::ROL:
2797 case Mips::ROR:
2798 return expandRotation(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2799 case Mips::ROLImm:
2800 case Mips::RORImm:
2801 return expandRotationImm(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2802 case Mips::DROL:
2803 case Mips::DROR:
2804 return expandDRotation(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2805 case Mips::DROLImm:
2806 case Mips::DRORImm:
2807 return expandDRotationImm(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2808 case Mips::ABSMacro:
2809 return expandAbs(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2810 case Mips::MULImmMacro:
2811 case Mips::DMULImmMacro:
2812 return expandMulImm(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2813 case Mips::MULOMacro:
2814 case Mips::DMULOMacro:
2815 return expandMulO(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2816 case Mips::MULOUMacro:
2817 case Mips::DMULOUMacro:
2818 return expandMulOU(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2819 case Mips::DMULMacro:
2820 return expandDMULMacro(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2821 case Mips::LDMacro:
2822 case Mips::SDMacro:
2823 return expandLoadStoreDMacro(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI,
2824 Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::LDMacro)
2825 ? MER_Fail
2826 : MER_Success;
2827 case Mips::SDC1_M1:
2828 return expandStoreDM1Macro(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI)
2829 ? MER_Fail
2830 : MER_Success;
2831 case Mips::SEQMacro:
2832 return expandSeq(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2833 case Mips::SEQIMacro:
2834 return expandSeqI(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2835 case Mips::MFTC0: case Mips::MTTC0:
2836 case Mips::MFTGPR: case Mips::MTTGPR:
2837 case Mips::MFTLO: case Mips::MTTLO:
2838 case Mips::MFTHI: case Mips::MTTHI:
2839 case Mips::MFTACX: case Mips::MTTACX:
2840 case Mips::MFTDSP: case Mips::MTTDSP:
2841 case Mips::MFTC1: case Mips::MTTC1:
2842 case Mips::MFTHC1: case Mips::MTTHC1:
2843 case Mips::CFTC1: case Mips::CTTC1:
2844 return expandMXTRAlias(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI) ? MER_Fail : MER_Success;
2845 }
2846}
2847
2848MipsAsmParser::MacroExpanderResultTy
2849MipsAsmParser::expandCapStoreC1(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, bool is64Bit,
2850 MCStreamer &Out, const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2851 MCInst tmpInst;
2852 unsigned AtRegNum = getATReg(IDLoc);
2853 if (AtRegNum == 0)
2854 return MER_Fail; // requires $at but set noat enabled (getAtReg reports err)
2855
2856 tmpInst.setOpcode(is64Bit ? Mips::DMFC1 : Mips::MFC1);
2857 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AtRegNum));
