2858 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()));
2859 tmpInst.setLoc(IDLoc);
2860 Out.EmitInstruction(tmpInst, *STI);
2861 tmpInst.clear();
2862 tmpInst.setOpcode(is64Bit ? Mips::CAPSTORE64 : Mips::CAPSTORE32);
2863 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AtRegNum));
2864 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()));
2865 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm()));
2866 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(3).getReg()));
2867 tmpInst.setLoc(IDLoc);
2868 Out.EmitInstruction(tmpInst, *STI);
2869 return MER_Success;
2870}
2871
2872MipsAsmParser::MacroExpanderResultTy
2873MipsAsmParser::expandCapLoadC1(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, bool is64Bit,
2874 MCStreamer &Out, const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2875 MCInst tmpInst;
2876 unsigned AtRegNum = getATReg(IDLoc);
2877 if (AtRegNum == 0)
2878 return MER_Fail; // requires $at but set noat enabled (getAtReg reports err)
2879 tmpInst.setOpcode(is64Bit ? Mips::CAPLOAD64 : Mips::CAPLOAD32);
2880 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AtRegNum));
2881 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()));
2882 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm()));
2883 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(3).getReg()));
2884 tmpInst.setLoc(IDLoc);
2885 Out.EmitInstruction(tmpInst, *STI);
2886 tmpInst.clear();
2887 tmpInst.setOpcode(is64Bit ? Mips::DMTC1 : Mips::MTC1);
2888 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()));
2889 tmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AtRegNum));
2890 tmpInst.setLoc(IDLoc);
2891 Out.EmitInstruction(tmpInst, *STI);
2892 return MER_Success;
2893}
2894
2895bool MipsAsmParser::expandJalWithRegs(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
2896 MCStreamer &Out,
2897 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2898 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
2899
2900 // Create a JALR instruction which is going to replace the pseudo-JAL.
2901 MCInst JalrInst;
2902 JalrInst.setLoc(IDLoc);
2903 const MCOperand FirstRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0);
2904 const unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
2905
2906 if (Opcode == Mips::JalOneReg) {
2907 // jal $rs => jalr $rs
2908 if (IsCpRestoreSet && inMicroMipsMode()) {
2909 JalrInst.setOpcode(Mips::JALRS16_MM);
2910 JalrInst.addOperand(FirstRegOp);
2911 } else if (inMicroMipsMode()) {
2912 JalrInst.setOpcode(hasMips32r6() ? Mips::JALRC16_MMR6 : Mips::JALR16_MM);
2913 JalrInst.addOperand(FirstRegOp);
2914 } else {
2915 JalrInst.setOpcode(Mips::JALR);
2916 JalrInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::RA));
2917 JalrInst.addOperand(FirstRegOp);
2918 }
2919 } else if (Opcode == Mips::JalTwoReg) {
2920 // jal $rd, $rs => jalr $rd, $rs
2921 if (IsCpRestoreSet && inMicroMipsMode())
2922 JalrInst.setOpcode(Mips::JALRS_MM);
2923 else
2924 JalrInst.setOpcode(inMicroMipsMode() ? Mips::JALR_MM : Mips::JALR);
2925 JalrInst.addOperand(FirstRegOp);
2926 const MCOperand SecondRegOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
2927 JalrInst.addOperand(SecondRegOp);
2928 }
2929 Out.EmitInstruction(JalrInst, *STI);
2930
2931 // If .set reorder is active and branch instruction has a delay slot,
2932 // emit a NOP after it.
2933 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = getInstDesc(JalrInst.getOpcode());
2934 if (MCID.hasDelaySlot() && AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder())
2935 TOut.emitEmptyDelaySlot(hasShortDelaySlot(JalrInst), IDLoc,
2936 STI);
2937
2938 return false;
2939}
2940
2941/// Can the value be represented by a unsigned N-bit value and a shift left?
2942template <unsigned N> static bool isShiftedUIntAtAnyPosition(uint64_t x) {
2943 unsigned BitNum = findFirstSet(x);
2944
2945 return (x == x >> BitNum << BitNum) && isUInt<N>(x >> BitNum);
2946}
2947
2948/// Load (or add) an immediate into a register.
2949///
2950/// @param ImmValue The immediate to load.
2951/// @param DstReg The register that will hold the immediate.
2952/// @param SrcReg A register to add to the immediate or Mips::NoRegister
2953/// for a simple initialization.
2954/// @param Is32BitImm Is ImmValue 32-bit or 64-bit?
2955/// @param IsAddress True if the immediate represents an address. False if it
2956/// is an integer.
2957/// @param IDLoc Location of the immediate in the source file.
2958bool MipsAsmParser::loadImmediate(int64_t ImmValue, unsigned DstReg,
2959 unsigned SrcReg, bool Is32BitImm,
2960 bool IsAddress, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
2961 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
2962 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
2963
2964 if (!Is32BitImm && !isGP64bit()) {
2965 Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires a 64-bit architecture");
2966 return true;
2967 }
2968
2969 if (Is32BitImm) {
2970 if (isInt<32>(ImmValue) || isUInt<32>(ImmValue)) {
2971 // Sign extend up to 64-bit so that the predicates match the hardware
2972 // behaviour. In particular, isInt<16>(0xffff8000) and similar should be
2973 // true.
2974 ImmValue = SignExtend64<32>(ImmValue);
2975 } else {
2976 Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires a 32-bit immediate");
2977 return true;
2978 }
2979 }
2980
2981 unsigned ZeroReg = IsAddress ? ABI.GetNullPtr() : ABI.GetZeroReg();
2982 unsigned AdduOp = !Is32BitImm ? Mips::DADDu : Mips::ADDu;
2983
2984 bool UseSrcReg = false;
2985 if (SrcReg != Mips::NoRegister)
2986 UseSrcReg = true;
2987
2988 unsigned TmpReg = DstReg;
2989 if (UseSrcReg &&
2990 getContext().getRegisterInfo()->isSuperOrSubRegisterEq(DstReg, SrcReg)) {
2991 // At this point we need AT to perform the expansions and we exit if it is
2992 // not available.
2993 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
2994 if (!ATReg)
2995 return true;
2996 TmpReg = ATReg;
2997 }
2998
2999 if (isInt<16>(ImmValue)) {
3000 if (!UseSrcReg)
3001 SrcReg = ZeroReg;
3002
3003 // This doesn't quite follow the usual ABI expectations for N32 but matches
3004 // traditional assembler behaviour. N32 would normally use addiu for both
3005 // integers and addresses.
3006 if (IsAddress && !Is32BitImm) {
3007 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DADDiu, DstReg, SrcReg, ImmValue, IDLoc, STI);
3008 return false;
3009 }
3010
3011 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ADDiu, DstReg, SrcReg, ImmValue, IDLoc, STI);
3012 return false;
3013 }
3014
3015 if (isUInt<16>(ImmValue)) {
3016 unsigned TmpReg = DstReg;
3017 if (SrcReg == DstReg) {
3018 TmpReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3019 if (!TmpReg)
3020 return true;
3021 }
3022
3023 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, ZeroReg, ImmValue, IDLoc, STI);
3024 if (UseSrcReg)
3025 TOut.emitRRR(ABI.GetPtrAdduOp(), DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3026 return false;
3027 }
3028
3029 if (isInt<32>(ImmValue) || isUInt<32>(ImmValue)) {
3030 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
3031
3032 uint16_t Bits31To16 = (ImmValue >> 16) & 0xffff;
3033 uint16_t Bits15To0 = ImmValue & 0xffff;
3034 if (!Is32BitImm && !isInt<32>(ImmValue)) {
3035 // Traditional behaviour seems to special case this particular value. It's
3036 // not clear why other masks are handled differently.
3037 if (ImmValue == 0xffffffff) {
3038 TOut.emitRI(Mips::LUi, TmpReg, 0xffff, IDLoc, STI);
3039 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSRL32, TmpReg, TmpReg, 0, IDLoc, STI);
3040 if (UseSrcReg)
3041 TOut.emitRRR(AdduOp, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3042 return false;
3043 }
3044
3045 // Expand to an ORi instead of a LUi to avoid sign-extending into the
3046 // upper 32 bits.
3047 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, ZeroReg, Bits31To16, IDLoc, STI);
3048 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL, TmpReg, TmpReg, 16, IDLoc, STI);
3049 if (Bits15To0)
3050 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, TmpReg, Bits15To0, IDLoc, STI);
3051 if (UseSrcReg)
3052 TOut.emitRRR(AdduOp, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3053 return false;
3054 }
3055
3056 TOut.emitRI(Mips::LUi, TmpReg, Bits31To16, IDLoc, STI);
3057 if (Bits15To0)
3058 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, TmpReg, Bits15To0, IDLoc, STI);
3059 if (UseSrcReg)
3060 TOut.emitRRR(AdduOp, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3061 return false;
3062 }
3063
3064 if (isShiftedUIntAtAnyPosition<16>(ImmValue)) {
3065 if (Is32BitImm) {
3066 Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires a 32-bit immediate");
3067 return true;
3068 }
3069
3070 // Traditionally, these immediates are shifted as little as possible and as
3071 // such we align the most significant bit to bit 15 of our temporary.
3072 unsigned FirstSet = findFirstSet((uint64_t)ImmValue);
3073 unsigned LastSet = findLastSet((uint64_t)ImmValue);
3074 unsigned ShiftAmount = FirstSet - (15 - (LastSet - FirstSet));
3075 uint16_t Bits = (ImmValue >> ShiftAmount) & 0xffff;
3076 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, ZeroReg, Bits, IDLoc, STI);
3077 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL, TmpReg, TmpReg, ShiftAmount, IDLoc, STI);
3078
3079 if (UseSrcReg)
3080 TOut.emitRRR(AdduOp, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3081
3082 return false;
3083 }
3084
3085 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
3086
3087 // The remaining case is packed with a sequence of dsll and ori with zeros
3088 // being omitted and any neighbouring dsll's being coalesced.
3089 // The highest 32-bit's are equivalent to a 32-bit immediate load.
3090
3091 // Load bits 32-63 of ImmValue into bits 0-31 of the temporary register.
3092 if (loadImmediate(ImmValue >> 32, TmpReg, Mips::NoRegister, true, false,
3093 IDLoc, Out, STI))
3094 return false;
3095
3096 // Shift and accumulate into the register. If a 16-bit chunk is zero, then
3097 // skip it and defer the shift to the next chunk.
3098 unsigned ShiftCarriedForwards = 16;
3099 for (int BitNum = 16; BitNum >= 0; BitNum -= 16) {
3100 uint16_t ImmChunk = (ImmValue >> BitNum) & 0xffff;
3101
3102 if (ImmChunk != 0) {
3103 TOut.emitDSLL(TmpReg, TmpReg, ShiftCarriedForwards, IDLoc, STI);
3104 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, TmpReg, TmpReg, ImmChunk, IDLoc, STI);
3105 ShiftCarriedForwards = 0;
3106 }
3107
3108 ShiftCarriedForwards += 16;
3109 }
3110 ShiftCarriedForwards -= 16;
3111
3112 // Finish any remaining shifts left by trailing zeros.
3113 if (ShiftCarriedForwards)
3114 TOut.emitDSLL(TmpReg, TmpReg, ShiftCarriedForwards, IDLoc, STI);
3115
3116 if (UseSrcReg)
3117 TOut.emitRRR(AdduOp, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3118
3119 return false;
3120}
3121
3122bool MipsAsmParser::expandLoadImm(MCInst &Inst, bool Is32BitImm, SMLoc IDLoc,
3123 MCStreamer &Out, const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
3124 const MCOperand &ImmOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
3125 int64_t Imm = 0;
3126 if (ImmOp.isExpr()) {
3127 const MCExpr *Expr = ImmOp.getExpr();
3128 if (!Expr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Imm, Out)) {
3129 Out.getTargetStreamer();
3130 return Error(IDLoc, "could not evaluate operand as immediate");
3131 }
3132 } else {
3133 assert(ImmOp.isImm() && "expected immediate operand kind");
3134 Imm = ImmOp.getImm();
3135 }
3136 const MCOperand &DstRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0);
3137 assert(DstRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
3138
3139 if (loadImmediate(Imm, DstRegOp.getReg(), Mips::NoRegister, Is32BitImm, false,
3140 IDLoc, Out, STI))
3141 return true;
3142
3143 return false;
3144}
3145
3146bool MipsAsmParser::expandLoadAddress(unsigned DstReg, unsigned BaseReg,
3147 const MCOperand &Offset,
3148 bool Is32BitAddress, SMLoc IDLoc,
3149 MCStreamer &Out,
3150 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
3151 // la can't produce a usable address when addresses are 64-bit.
3152 if (Is32BitAddress && ABI.ArePtrs64bit()) {
3153 // FIXME: Demote this to a warning and continue as if we had 'dla' instead.
3154 // We currently can't do this because we depend on the equality
3155 // operator and N64 can end up with a GPR32/GPR64 mismatch.
3156 Error(IDLoc, "la used to load 64-bit address");
3157 // Continue as if we had 'dla' instead.
3158 Is32BitAddress = false;
3159 return true;
3160 }
3161
3162 // dla requires 64-bit addresses.
3163 if (!Is32BitAddress && !hasMips3()) {
3164 Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires a 64-bit architecture");
3165 return true;
3166 }
3167
3168 if (!Offset.isImm())
3169 return loadAndAddSymbolAddress(Offset.getExpr(), DstReg, BaseReg,
3170 Is32BitAddress, IDLoc, Out, STI);
3171
3172 if (!ABI.ArePtrs64bit()) {
3173 // Continue as if we had 'la' whether we had 'la' or 'dla'.
3174 Is32BitAddress = true;
3175 }
3176
3177 return loadImmediate(Offset.getImm(), DstReg, BaseReg, Is32BitAddress, true,
3178 IDLoc, Out, STI);
3179}
3180
3181bool MipsAsmParser::loadAndAddSymbolAddress(const MCExpr *SymExpr,
3182 unsigned DstReg, unsigned SrcReg,
3183 bool Is32BitSym, SMLoc IDLoc,
3184 MCStreamer &Out,
3185 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
3186 // FIXME: These expansions do not respect -mxgot.
3187 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
3188 bool UseSrcReg = SrcReg != Mips::NoRegister;
3189 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
3190
3191 if (inPicMode() && ABI.IsO32()) {
3192 MCValue Res;
3193 if (!SymExpr->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, nullptr)) {
3194 Error(IDLoc, "expected relocatable expression");
3195 return true;
3196 }
3197 if (Res.getSymB() != nullptr) {
3198 Error(IDLoc, "expected relocatable expression with only one symbol");
3199 return true;
3200 }
3201
3202 // The case where the result register is $25 is somewhat special. If the
3203 // symbol in the final relocation is external and not modified with a
3204 // constant then we must use R_MIPS_CALL16 instead of R_MIPS_GOT16.
3205 if ((DstReg == Mips::T9 || DstReg == Mips::T9_64) && !UseSrcReg &&
3206 Res.getConstant() == 0 &&
3207 !(Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isInSection() ||
3208 Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isTemporary() ||
3209 (Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isELF() &&
3210 cast<MCSymbolELF>(Res.getSymA()->getSymbol()).getBinding() ==
3211 ELF::STB_LOCAL))) {
3212 const MCExpr *CallExpr =
3213 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_CALL, SymExpr, getContext());
3214 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::LW, DstReg, ABI.GetGlobalPtr(),
3215 MCOperand::createExpr(CallExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3216 return false;
3217 }
3218
3219 // The remaining cases are:
3220 // External GOT: lw $tmp, %got(symbol+offset)($gp)
3221 // >addiu $tmp, $tmp, %lo(offset)
3222 // >addiu $rd, $tmp, $rs
3223 // Local GOT: lw $tmp, %got(symbol+offset)($gp)
3224 // addiu $tmp, $tmp, %lo(symbol+offset)($gp)
3225 // >addiu $rd, $tmp, $rs
3226 // The addiu's marked with a '>' may be omitted if they are redundant. If
3227 // this happens then the last instruction must use $rd as the result
3228 // register.
3229 const MipsMCExpr *GotExpr =
3230 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT, SymExpr, getContext());
3231 const MCExpr *LoExpr = nullptr;
3232 if (Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isInSection() ||
3233 Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isTemporary())
3234 LoExpr = MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, SymExpr, getContext());
3235 else if (Res.getConstant() != 0) {
3236 // External symbols fully resolve the symbol with just the %got(symbol)
3237 // but we must still account for any offset to the symbol for expressions
3238 // like symbol+8.
3239 LoExpr = MCConstantExpr::create(Res.getConstant(), getContext());
3240 }
3241
3242 unsigned TmpReg = DstReg;
3243 if (UseSrcReg &&
3244 getContext().getRegisterInfo()->isSuperOrSubRegisterEq(DstReg,
3245 SrcReg)) {
3246 // If $rs is the same as $rd, we need to use AT.
3247 // If it is not available we exit.
3248 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3249 if (!ATReg)
3250 return true;
3251 TmpReg = ATReg;
3252 }
3253
3254 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::LW, TmpReg, ABI.GetGlobalPtr(),
3255 MCOperand::createExpr(GotExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3256
3257 if (LoExpr)
3258 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::ADDiu, TmpReg, TmpReg, MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr),
3259 IDLoc, STI);
3260
3261 if (UseSrcReg)
3262 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::ADDu, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3263
3264 return false;
3265 }
3266
3267 if (inPicMode() && ABI.ArePtrs64bit()) {
3268 MCValue Res;
3269 if (!SymExpr->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, nullptr)) {
3270 Error(IDLoc, "expected relocatable expression");
3271 return true;
3272 }
3273 if (Res.getSymB() != nullptr) {
3274 Error(IDLoc, "expected relocatable expression with only one symbol");
3275 return true;
3276 }
3277
3278 // The case where the result register is $25 is somewhat special. If the
3279 // symbol in the final relocation is external and not modified with a
3280 // constant then we must use R_MIPS_CALL16 instead of R_MIPS_GOT_DISP.
3281 if ((DstReg == Mips::T9 || DstReg == Mips::T9_64) && !UseSrcReg &&
3282 Res.getConstant() == 0 &&
3283 !(Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isInSection() ||
3284 Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isTemporary() ||
3285 (Res.getSymA()->getSymbol().isELF() &&
3286 cast<MCSymbolELF>(Res.getSymA()->getSymbol()).getBinding() ==
3287 ELF::STB_LOCAL))) {
3288 const MCExpr *CallExpr =
3289 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_CALL, SymExpr, getContext());
3290 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTable())
3291 return Error(IDLoc, "Can't expand $gp-relative in cap-table mode");
3292 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::LD, DstReg, ABI.GetGlobalPtr(),
3293 MCOperand::createExpr(CallExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3294 return false;
3295 }
3296
3297 // The remaining cases are:
3298 // Small offset: ld $tmp, %got_disp(symbol)($gp)
3299 // >daddiu $tmp, $tmp, offset
3300 // >daddu $rd, $tmp, $rs
3301 // The daddiu's marked with a '>' may be omitted if they are redundant. If
3302 // this happens then the last instruction must use $rd as the result
3303 // register.
3304 const MipsMCExpr *GotExpr = MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT_DISP,
3305 Res.getSymA(),
3306 getContext());
3307 const MCExpr *LoExpr = nullptr;
3308 if (Res.getConstant() != 0) {
3309 // Symbols fully resolve with just the %got_disp(symbol) but we
3310 // must still account for any offset to the symbol for
3311 // expressions like symbol+8.
3312 LoExpr = MCConstantExpr::create(Res.getConstant(), getContext());
3313
3314 // FIXME: Offsets greater than 16 bits are not yet implemented.
3315 // FIXME: The correct range is a 32-bit sign-extended number.
3316 if (Res.getConstant() < -0x8000 || Res.getConstant() > 0x7fff) {
3317 Error(IDLoc, "macro instruction uses large offset, which is not "
3318 "currently supported");
3319 return true;
3320 }
3321 }
3322
3323 unsigned TmpReg = DstReg;
3324 if (UseSrcReg &&
3325 getContext().getRegisterInfo()->isSuperOrSubRegisterEq(DstReg,
3326 SrcReg)) {
3327 // If $rs is the same as $rd, we need to use AT.
3328 // If it is not available we exit.
3329 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3330 if (!ATReg)
3331 return true;
3332 TmpReg = ATReg;
3333 }
3334 if (ABI.UsesCapabilityTable())
3335 return Error(IDLoc, "Can't expand $gp-relative in cap-table mode");
3336 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::LD, TmpReg, ABI.GetGlobalPtr(),
3337 MCOperand::createExpr(GotExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3338
3339 if (LoExpr)
3340 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, TmpReg, TmpReg, MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr),
3341 IDLoc, STI);
3342
3343 if (UseSrcReg)
3344 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::DADDu, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3345
3346 return false;
3347 }
3348
3349 const MipsMCExpr *HiExpr =
3350 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HI, SymExpr, getContext());
3351 const MipsMCExpr *LoExpr =
3352 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, SymExpr, getContext());
3353
3354 // This is the 64-bit symbol address expansion.
3355 if (ABI.ArePtrs64bit() && isGP64bit()) {
3356 // We need AT for the 64-bit expansion in the cases where the optional
3357 // source register is the destination register and for the superscalar
3358 // scheduled form.
3359 //
3360 // If it is not available we exit if the destination is the same as the
3361 // source register.
3362
3363 const MipsMCExpr *HighestExpr =
3364 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HIGHEST, SymExpr, getContext());
3365 const MipsMCExpr *HigherExpr =
3366 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HIGHER, SymExpr, getContext());
3367
3368 bool RdRegIsRsReg =
3369 getContext().getRegisterInfo()->isSuperOrSubRegisterEq(DstReg, SrcReg);
3370
3371 if (canUseATReg() && UseSrcReg && RdRegIsRsReg) {
3372 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3373
3374 // If $rs is the same as $rd:
3375 // (d)la $rd, sym($rd) => lui $at, %highest(sym)
3376 // daddiu $at, $at, %higher(sym)
3377 // dsll $at, $at, 16
3378 // daddiu $at, $at, %hi(sym)
3379 // dsll $at, $at, 16
3380 // daddiu $at, $at, %lo(sym)
3381 // daddu $rd, $at, $rd
3382 TOut.emitRX(Mips::LUi, ATReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HighestExpr), IDLoc,
3383 STI);
3384 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, ATReg, ATReg,
3385 MCOperand::createExpr(HigherExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3386 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL, ATReg, ATReg, 16, IDLoc, STI);
3387 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, ATReg, ATReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HiExpr),
3388 IDLoc, STI);
3389 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL, ATReg, ATReg, 16, IDLoc, STI);
3390 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, ATReg, ATReg, MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr),
3391 IDLoc, STI);
3392 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::DADDu, DstReg, ATReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3393
3394 return false;
3395 } else if (canUseATReg() && !RdRegIsRsReg) {
3396 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3397
3398 // If the $rs is different from $rd or if $rs isn't specified and we
3399 // have $at available:
3400 // (d)la $rd, sym/sym($rs) => lui $rd, %highest(sym)
3401 // lui $at, %hi(sym)
3402 // daddiu $rd, $rd, %higher(sym)
3403 // daddiu $at, $at, %lo(sym)
3404 // dsll32 $rd, $rd, 0
3405 // daddu $rd, $rd, $at
3406 // (daddu $rd, $rd, $rs)
3407 //
3408 // Which is preferred for superscalar issue.
3409 TOut.emitRX(Mips::LUi, DstReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HighestExpr), IDLoc,
3410 STI);
3411 TOut.emitRX(Mips::LUi, ATReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HiExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3412 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, DstReg, DstReg,
3413 MCOperand::createExpr(HigherExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3414 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, ATReg, ATReg, MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr),
3415 IDLoc, STI);
3416 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL32, DstReg, DstReg, 0, IDLoc, STI);
3417 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::DADDu, DstReg, DstReg, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
3418 if (UseSrcReg)
3419 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::DADDu, DstReg, DstReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3420
3421 return false;
3422 } else if (!canUseATReg() && !RdRegIsRsReg) {
3423 // Otherwise, synthesize the address in the destination register
3424 // serially:
3425 // (d)la $rd, sym/sym($rs) => lui $rd, %highest(sym)
3426 // daddiu $rd, $rd, %higher(sym)
3427 // dsll $rd, $rd, 16
3428 // daddiu $rd, $rd, %hi(sym)
3429 // dsll $rd, $rd, 16
3430 // daddiu $rd, $rd, %lo(sym)
3431 TOut.emitRX(Mips::LUi, DstReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HighestExpr), IDLoc,
3432 STI);
3433 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, DstReg, DstReg,
3434 MCOperand::createExpr(HigherExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3435 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL, DstReg, DstReg, 16, IDLoc, STI);
3436 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, DstReg, DstReg,
3437 MCOperand::createExpr(HiExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3438 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL, DstReg, DstReg, 16, IDLoc, STI);
3439 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, DstReg, DstReg,
3440 MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3441 if (UseSrcReg)
3442 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::DADDu, DstReg, DstReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3443
3444 return false;
3445 } else {
3446 // We have a case where SrcReg == DstReg and we don't have $at
3447 // available. We can't expand this case, so error out appropriately.
3448 assert(SrcReg == DstReg && !canUseATReg() &&
3449 "Could have expanded dla but didn't?");
3450 reportParseError(IDLoc,
3451 "pseudo-instruction requires $at, which is not available");
3452 return true;
3453 }
3454 }
3455
3456 // And now, the 32-bit symbol address expansion:
3457 // If $rs is the same as $rd:
3458 // (d)la $rd, sym($rd) => lui $at, %hi(sym)
3459 // ori $at, $at, %lo(sym)
3460 // addu $rd, $at, $rd
3461 // Otherwise, if the $rs is different from $rd or if $rs isn't specified:
3462 // (d)la $rd, sym/sym($rs) => lui $rd, %hi(sym)
3463 // ori $rd, $rd, %lo(sym)
3464 // (addu $rd, $rd, $rs)
3465 unsigned TmpReg = DstReg;
3466 if (UseSrcReg &&
3467 getContext().getRegisterInfo()->isSuperOrSubRegisterEq(DstReg, SrcReg)) {
3468 // If $rs is the same as $rd, we need to use AT.
3469 // If it is not available we exit.
3470 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3471 if (!ATReg)
3472 return true;
3473 TmpReg = ATReg;
3474 }
3475
3476 TOut.emitRX(Mips::LUi, TmpReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HiExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3477 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::ADDiu, TmpReg, TmpReg, MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr),
3478 IDLoc, STI);
3479
3480 if (UseSrcReg)
3481 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::ADDu, DstReg, TmpReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
3482 else
3483 assert(
3484 getContext().getRegisterInfo()->isSuperOrSubRegisterEq(DstReg, TmpReg));
3485
3486 return false;
3487}
3488
3489// Each double-precision register DO-D15 overlaps with two of the single
3490// precision registers F0-F31. As an example, all of the following hold true:
3491// D0 + 1 == F1, F1 + 1 == D1, F1 + 1 == F2, depending on the context.
3492static unsigned nextReg(unsigned Reg) {
3493 if (MipsMCRegisterClasses[Mips::FGR32RegClassID].contains(Reg))
3494 return Reg == (unsigned)Mips::F31 ? (unsigned)Mips::F0 : Reg + 1;
3495 switch (Reg) {
3496 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown register in assembly macro expansion!");
3497 case Mips::ZERO: return Mips::AT;
3498 case Mips::AT: return Mips::V0;
3499 case Mips::V0: return Mips::V1;
3500 case Mips::V1: return Mips::A0;
3501 case Mips::A0: return Mips::A1;
3502 case Mips::A1: return Mips::A2;
3503 case Mips::A2: return Mips::A3;
3504 case Mips::A3: return Mips::T0;
3505 case Mips::T0: return Mips::T1;
3506 case Mips::T1: return Mips::T2;
3507 case Mips::T2: return Mips::T3;
3508 case Mips::T3: return Mips::T4;
3509 case Mips::T4: return Mips::T5;
3510 case Mips::T5: return Mips::T6;
3511 case Mips::T6: return Mips::T7;
3512 case Mips::T7: return Mips::S0;
3513 case Mips::S0: return Mips::S1;
3514 case Mips::S1: return Mips::S2;
3515 case Mips::S2: return Mips::S3;
3516 case Mips::S3: return Mips::S4;
3517 case Mips::S4: return Mips::S5;
3518 case Mips::S5: return Mips::S6;
3519 case Mips::S6: return Mips::S7;
3520 case Mips::S7: return Mips::T8;
3521 case Mips::T8: return Mips::T9;
3522 case Mips::T9: return Mips::K0;
3523 case Mips::K0: return Mips::K1;
3524 case Mips::K1: return Mips::GP;
3525 case Mips::GP: return Mips::SP;
3526 case Mips::SP: return Mips::FP;
3527 case Mips::FP: return Mips::RA;
3528 case Mips::RA: return Mips::ZERO;
3529 case Mips::D0: return Mips::F1;
3530 case Mips::D1: return Mips::F3;
3531 case Mips::D2: return Mips::F5;
3532 case Mips::D3: return Mips::F7;
3533 case Mips::D4: return Mips::F9;
3534 case Mips::D5: return Mips::F11;
3535 case Mips::D6: return Mips::F13;
3536 case Mips::D7: return Mips::F15;
3537 case Mips::D8: return Mips::F17;
3538 case Mips::D9: return Mips::F19;
3539 case Mips::D10: return Mips::F21;
3540 case Mips::D11: return Mips::F23;
3541 case Mips::D12: return Mips::F25;
3542 case Mips::D13: return Mips::F27;
3543 case Mips::D14: return Mips::F29;
3544 case Mips::D15: return Mips::F31;
3545 }
3546}
3547
3548// FIXME: This method is too general. In principle we should compute the number
3549// of instructions required to synthesize the immediate inline compared to
3550// synthesizing the address inline and relying on non .text sections.
3551// For static O32 and N32 this may yield a small benefit, for static N64 this is
3552// likely to yield a much larger benefit as we have to synthesize a 64bit
3553// address to load a 64 bit value.
3554bool MipsAsmParser::emitPartialAddress(MipsTargetStreamer &TOut, SMLoc IDLoc,
3555 MCSymbol *Sym) {
3556 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3557 if (!ATReg)
3558 return true;
3559
3560 if(IsPicEnabled) {
3561 const MCExpr *GotSym =
3562 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext());
3563 const MipsMCExpr *GotExpr =
3564 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_GOT, GotSym, getContext());
3565
3566 if(isABI_O32() || isABI_N32()) {
3567 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::LW, ATReg, Mips::GP, MCOperand::createExpr(GotExpr),
3568 IDLoc, STI);
3569 } else { //isABI_N64()
3570 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::LD, ATReg, Mips::GP, MCOperand::createExpr(GotExpr),
3571 IDLoc, STI);
3572 }
3573 } else { //!IsPicEnabled
3574 const MCExpr *HiSym =
3575 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext());
3576 const MipsMCExpr *HiExpr =
3577 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HI, HiSym, getContext());
3578
3579 // FIXME: This is technically correct but gives a different result to gas,
3580 // but gas is incomplete there (it has a fixme noting it doesn't work with
3581 // 64-bit addresses).
3582 // FIXME: With -msym32 option, the address expansion for N64 should probably
3583 // use the O32 / N32 case. It's safe to use the 64 address expansion as the
3584 // symbol's value is considered sign extended.
3585 if(isABI_O32() || isABI_N32()) {
3586 TOut.emitRX(Mips::LUi, ATReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HiExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3587 } else { //isABI_N64()
3588 const MCExpr *HighestSym =
3589 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext());
3590 const MipsMCExpr *HighestExpr =
3591 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HIGHEST, HighestSym, getContext());
3592 const MCExpr *HigherSym =
3593 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext());
3594 const MipsMCExpr *HigherExpr =
3595 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HIGHER, HigherSym, getContext());
3596
3597 TOut.emitRX(Mips::LUi, ATReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HighestExpr), IDLoc,
3598 STI);
3599 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, ATReg, ATReg,
3600 MCOperand::createExpr(HigherExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3601 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL, ATReg, ATReg, 16, IDLoc, STI);
3602 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, ATReg, ATReg, MCOperand::createExpr(HiExpr),
3603 IDLoc, STI);
3604 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSLL, ATReg, ATReg, 16, IDLoc, STI);
3605 }
3606 }
3607 return false;
3608}
3609
3610bool MipsAsmParser::expandLoadImmReal(MCInst &Inst, bool IsSingle, bool IsGPR,
3611 bool Is64FPU, SMLoc IDLoc,
3612 MCStreamer &Out,
3613 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
3614 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
3615 assert(Inst.getNumOperands() == 2 && "Invalid operand count");
3616 assert(Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() && Inst.getOperand(1).isImm() &&
3617 "Invalid instruction operand.");
3618
3619 unsigned FirstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
3620 uint64_t ImmOp64 = Inst.getOperand(1).getImm();
3621
3622 uint32_t HiImmOp64 = (ImmOp64 & 0xffffffff00000000) >> 32;
3623 // If ImmOp64 is AsmToken::Integer type (all bits set to zero in the
3624 // exponent field), convert it to double (e.g. 1 to 1.0)
3625 if ((HiImmOp64 & 0x7ff00000) == 0) {
3626 APFloat RealVal(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), ImmOp64);
3627 ImmOp64 = RealVal.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue();
3628 }
3629
3630 uint32_t LoImmOp64 = ImmOp64 & 0xffffffff;
3631 HiImmOp64 = (ImmOp64 & 0xffffffff00000000) >> 32;
3632
3633 if (IsSingle) {
3634 // Conversion of a double in an uint64_t to a float in a uint32_t,
3635 // retaining the bit pattern of a float.
3636 uint32_t ImmOp32;
3637 double doubleImm = BitsToDouble(ImmOp64);
3638 float tmp_float = static_cast<float>(doubleImm);
3639 ImmOp32 = FloatToBits(tmp_float);
3640
3641 if (IsGPR) {
3642 if (loadImmediate(ImmOp32, FirstReg, Mips::NoRegister, true, true, IDLoc,
3643 Out, STI))
3644 return true;
3645 return false;
3646 } else {
3647 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3648 if (!ATReg)
3649 return true;
3650 if (LoImmOp64 == 0) {
3651 if (loadImmediate(ImmOp32, ATReg, Mips::NoRegister, true, true, IDLoc,
3652 Out, STI))
3653 return true;
3654 TOut.emitRR(Mips::MTC1, FirstReg, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
3655 return false;
3656 }
3657
3658 MCSection *CS = getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly();
3659 // FIXME: Enhance this expansion to use the .lit4 & .lit8 sections
3660 // where appropriate.
3661 MCSection *ReadOnlySection = getContext().getELFSection(
3662 ".rodata", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, ELF::SHF_ALLOC);
3663
3664 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().createTempSymbol();
3665 const MCExpr *LoSym =
3666 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext());
3667 const MipsMCExpr *LoExpr =
3668 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, LoSym, getContext());
3669
3670 getStreamer().SwitchSection(ReadOnlySection);
3671 getStreamer().EmitLabel(Sym, IDLoc);
3672 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(ImmOp32, 4);
3673 getStreamer().SwitchSection(CS);
3674
3675 if(emitPartialAddress(TOut, IDLoc, Sym))
3676 return true;
3677 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::LWC1, FirstReg, ATReg,
3678 MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3679 }
3680 return false;
3681 }
3682
3683 // if(!IsSingle)
3684 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3685 if (!ATReg)
3686 return true;
3687
3688 if (IsGPR) {
3689 if (LoImmOp64 == 0) {
3690 if(isABI_N32() || isABI_N64()) {
3691 if (loadImmediate(HiImmOp64, FirstReg, Mips::NoRegister, false, true,
3692 IDLoc, Out, STI))
3693 return true;
3694 return false;
3695 } else {
3696 if (loadImmediate(HiImmOp64, FirstReg, Mips::NoRegister, true, true,
3697 IDLoc, Out, STI))
3698 return true;
3699
3700 if (loadImmediate(0, nextReg(FirstReg), Mips::NoRegister, true, true,
3701 IDLoc, Out, STI))
3702 return true;
3703 return false;
3704 }
3705 }
3706
3707 MCSection *CS = getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly();
3708 MCSection *ReadOnlySection = getContext().getELFSection(
3709 ".rodata", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, ELF::SHF_ALLOC);
3710
3711 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().createTempSymbol();
3712 const MCExpr *LoSym =
3713 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext());
3714 const MipsMCExpr *LoExpr =
3715 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, LoSym, getContext());
3716
3717 getStreamer().SwitchSection(ReadOnlySection);
3718 getStreamer().EmitLabel(Sym, IDLoc);
3719 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(HiImmOp64, 4);
3720 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(LoImmOp64, 4);
3721 getStreamer().SwitchSection(CS);
3722
3723 if(emitPartialAddress(TOut, IDLoc, Sym))
3724 return true;
3725 if(isABI_N64())
3726 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::DADDiu, ATReg, ATReg,
3727 MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3728 else
3729 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::ADDiu, ATReg, ATReg,
3730 MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3731
3732 if(isABI_N32() || isABI_N64())
3733 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::LD, FirstReg, ATReg, 0, IDLoc, STI);
3734 else {
3735 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::LW, FirstReg, ATReg, 0, IDLoc, STI);
3736 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::LW, nextReg(FirstReg), ATReg, 4, IDLoc, STI);
3737 }
3738 return false;
3739 } else { // if(!IsGPR && !IsSingle)
3740 if ((LoImmOp64 == 0) &&
3741 !((HiImmOp64 & 0xffff0000) && (HiImmOp64 & 0x0000ffff))) {
3742 // FIXME: In the case where the constant is zero, we can load the
3743 // register directly from the zero register.
3744 if (loadImmediate(HiImmOp64, ATReg, Mips::NoRegister, true, true, IDLoc,
3745 Out, STI))
3746 return true;
3747 if (isABI_N32() || isABI_N64())
3748 TOut.emitRR(Mips::DMTC1, FirstReg, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
3749 else if (hasMips32r2()) {
3750 TOut.emitRR(Mips::MTC1, FirstReg, Mips::ZERO, IDLoc, STI);
3751 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::MTHC1_D32, FirstReg, FirstReg, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
3752 } else {
3753 TOut.emitRR(Mips::MTC1, nextReg(FirstReg), ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
3754 TOut.emitRR(Mips::MTC1, FirstReg, Mips::ZERO, IDLoc, STI);
3755 }
3756 return false;
3757 }
3758
3759 MCSection *CS = getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly();
3760 // FIXME: Enhance this expansion to use the .lit4 & .lit8 sections
3761 // where appropriate.
3762 MCSection *ReadOnlySection = getContext().getELFSection(
3763 ".rodata", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, ELF::SHF_ALLOC);
3764
3765 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().createTempSymbol();
3766 const MCExpr *LoSym =
3767 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext());
3768 const MipsMCExpr *LoExpr =
3769 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, LoSym, getContext());
3770
3771 getStreamer().SwitchSection(ReadOnlySection);
3772 getStreamer().EmitLabel(Sym, IDLoc);
3773 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(HiImmOp64, 4);
3774 getStreamer().EmitIntValue(LoImmOp64, 4);
3775 getStreamer().SwitchSection(CS);
3776
3777 if(emitPartialAddress(TOut, IDLoc, Sym))
3778 return true;
3779 TOut.emitRRX(Is64FPU ? Mips::LDC164 : Mips::LDC1, FirstReg, ATReg,
3780 MCOperand::createExpr(LoExpr), IDLoc, STI);
3781 }
3782 return false;
3783}
3784
3785bool MipsAsmParser::expandUncondBranchMMPseudo(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
3786 MCStreamer &Out,
3787 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
3788 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
3789
3790 assert(getInstDesc(Inst.getOpcode()).getNumOperands() == 1 &&
3791 "unexpected number of operands");
3792
3793 MCOperand Offset = Inst.getOperand(0);
3794 if (Offset.isExpr()) {
3795 Inst.clear();
3796 Inst.setOpcode(Mips::BEQ_MM);
3797 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO));
3798 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO));
3799 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Offset.getExpr()));
3800 } else {
3801 assert(Offset.isImm() && "expected immediate operand kind");
3802 if (isInt<11>(Offset.getImm())) {
3803 // If offset fits into 11 bits then this instruction becomes microMIPS
3804 // 16-bit unconditional branch instruction.
3805 if (inMicroMipsMode())
3806 Inst.setOpcode(hasMips32r6() ? Mips::BC16_MMR6 : Mips::B16_MM);
3807 } else {
3808 if (!isInt<17>(Offset.getImm()))
3809 return Error(IDLoc, "branch target out of range");
3810 if (OffsetToAlignment(Offset.getImm(), 1LL << 1))
3811 return Error(IDLoc, "branch to misaligned address");
3812 Inst.clear();
3813 Inst.setOpcode(Mips::BEQ_MM);
3814 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO));
3815 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Mips::ZERO));
3816 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Offset.getImm()));
3817 }
3818 }
3819 Out.EmitInstruction(Inst, *STI);
3820
3821 // If .set reorder is active and branch instruction has a delay slot,
3822 // emit a NOP after it.
3823 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = getInstDesc(Inst.getOpcode());
3824 if (MCID.hasDelaySlot() && AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder())
3825 TOut.emitEmptyDelaySlot(true, IDLoc, STI);
3826
3827 return false;
3828}
3829
3830bool MipsAsmParser::expandBranchImm(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
3831 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
3832 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
3833 const MCOperand &DstRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0);
3834 assert(DstRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
3835
3836 const MCOperand &ImmOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
3837 assert(ImmOp.isImm() && "expected immediate operand kind");
3838
3839 const MCOperand &MemOffsetOp = Inst.getOperand(2);
3840 assert((MemOffsetOp.isImm() || MemOffsetOp.isExpr()) &&
3841 "expected immediate or expression operand");
3842
3843 bool IsLikely = false;
3844
3845 unsigned OpCode = 0;
3846 switch(Inst.getOpcode()) {
3847 case Mips::BneImm:
3848 OpCode = Mips::BNE;
3849 break;
3850 case Mips::BeqImm:
3851 OpCode = Mips::BEQ;
3852 break;
3853 case Mips::BEQLImmMacro:
3854 OpCode = Mips::BEQL;
3855 IsLikely = true;
3856 break;
3857 case Mips::BNELImmMacro:
3858 OpCode = Mips::BNEL;
3859 IsLikely = true;
3860 break;
3861 default:
3862 llvm_unreachable("Unknown immediate branch pseudo-instruction.");
3863 break;
3864 }
3865
3866 int64_t ImmValue = ImmOp.getImm();
3867 if (ImmValue == 0) {
3868 if (IsLikely) {
3869 TOut.emitRRX(OpCode, DstRegOp.getReg(), Mips::ZERO,
3870 MCOperand::createExpr(MemOffsetOp.getExpr()), IDLoc, STI);
3871 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SLL, Mips::ZERO, Mips::ZERO, 0, IDLoc, STI);
3872 } else
3873 TOut.emitRRX(OpCode, DstRegOp.getReg(), Mips::ZERO, MemOffsetOp, IDLoc,
3874 STI);
3875 } else {
3876 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
3877
3878 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3879 if (!ATReg)
3880 return true;
3881
3882 if (loadImmediate(ImmValue, ATReg, Mips::NoRegister, !isGP64bit(), true,
3883 IDLoc, Out, STI))
3884 return true;
3885
3886 if (IsLikely) {
3887 TOut.emitRRX(OpCode, DstRegOp.getReg(), ATReg,
3888 MCOperand::createExpr(MemOffsetOp.getExpr()), IDLoc, STI);
3889 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SLL, Mips::ZERO, Mips::ZERO, 0, IDLoc, STI);
3890 } else
3891 TOut.emitRRX(OpCode, DstRegOp.getReg(), ATReg, MemOffsetOp, IDLoc, STI);
3892 }
3893 return false;
3894}
3895
3896void MipsAsmParser::expandMemInst(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
3897 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI, bool IsLoad) {
3898
3899 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
3900 case Mips::CAPLOAD8:
3901 case Mips::CAPLOAD16:
3902 case Mips::CAPLOAD32:
3903 case Mips::CAPLOAD64:
3904 case Mips::CAPLOAD832:
3905 case Mips::CAPLOAD1632:
3906 case Mips::CAPLOAD3264:
3907 case Mips::CAPLOADU8:
3908 case Mips::CAPLOADU16:
3909 case Mips::CAPLOADU32:
3910 case Mips::CAPLOADU832:
3911 case Mips::CAPLOADU1632:
3912
3913 case Mips::CAPSTORE8:
3914 case Mips::CAPSTORE832:
3915 case Mips::CAPSTORE16:
3916 case Mips::CAPSTORE1632:
3917 case Mips::CAPSTORE32:
3918 case Mips::CAPSTORE3264:
3919 case Mips::CAPSTORE64:
3920
3921 case Mips::STORECAP:
3922 case Mips::STORECAP_BigImm:
3923 case Mips::LOADCAP:
3924 case Mips::LOADCAP_BigImm:
3925 getParser().Error(IDLoc, "Cannot expand symbol in immediate operand for this instruction");
3926 return;
3927 default:
3928 break;
3929 }
3930 const MCOperand &DstRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0);
3931 assert(DstRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
3932 const MCOperand &BaseRegOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
3933 assert(BaseRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
3934 const MCOperand &OffsetOp = Inst.getOperand(2);
3935
3936 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
3937 unsigned DstReg = DstRegOp.getReg();
3938 unsigned BaseReg = BaseRegOp.getReg();
3939 unsigned TmpReg = DstReg;
3940
3941 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = getInstDesc(Inst.getOpcode());
3942 int16_t DstRegClass = Desc.OpInfo[0].RegClass;
3943 unsigned DstRegClassID =
3944 getContext().getRegisterInfo()->getRegClass(DstRegClass).getID();
3945 bool IsGPR = (DstRegClassID == Mips::GPR32RegClassID) ||
3946 (DstRegClassID == Mips::GPR64RegClassID);
3947
3948 if (!IsLoad || !IsGPR || (BaseReg == DstReg)) {
3949 // At this point we need AT to perform the expansions
3950 // and we exit if it is not available.
3951 TmpReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
3952 if (!TmpReg)
3953 return;
3954 }
3955
3956 if (OffsetOp.isImm()) {
3957 int64_t LoOffset = OffsetOp.getImm() & 0xffff;
3958 int64_t HiOffset = OffsetOp.getImm() & ~0xffff;
3959
3960 // If msb of LoOffset is 1(negative number) we must increment
3961 // HiOffset to account for the sign-extension of the low part.
3962 if (LoOffset & 0x8000)
3963 HiOffset += 0x10000;
3964
3965 bool IsLargeOffset = HiOffset != 0;
3966
3967 if (IsLargeOffset) {
3968 bool Is32BitImm = (HiOffset >> 32) == 0;
3969 if (loadImmediate(HiOffset, TmpReg, Mips::NoRegister, Is32BitImm, true,
3970 IDLoc, Out, STI))
3971 return;
3972 }
3973
3974 if (BaseReg != Mips::ZERO && BaseReg != Mips::ZERO_64)
3975 TOut.emitRRR(isGP64bit() ? Mips::DADDu : Mips::ADDu, TmpReg, TmpReg,
3976 BaseReg, IDLoc, STI);
3977 TOut.emitRRI(Inst.getOpcode(), DstReg, TmpReg, LoOffset, IDLoc, STI);
3978 } else {
3979 assert(OffsetOp.isExpr() && "expected expression operand kind");
3980 const MCExpr *ExprOffset = OffsetOp.getExpr();
3981 MCOperand LoOperand = MCOperand::createExpr(
3982 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_LO, ExprOffset, getContext()));
3983 MCOperand HiOperand = MCOperand::createExpr(
3984 MipsMCExpr::create(MipsMCExpr::MEK_HI, ExprOffset, getContext()));
3985#if 0 // XXXAR: has this changed?
3986 // The parser currently asserts when parsing scd with symbols
3987 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
3988 case Mips::SC:
3989 case Mips::SC64:
3990 case Mips::SC64_R6:
3991 case Mips::SCD:
3992 case Mips::SCD_R6:
3993 getParser().Error(IDLoc,
3994 "cannot expand symbol reference in sc instruction yet.");
3995 return;
3996 default:
3997 break;
3998 }
3999#endif
4000 if (IsLoad)
4001 TOut.emitLoadWithSymOffset(Inst.getOpcode(), DstReg, BaseReg, HiOperand,
4002 LoOperand, TmpReg, IDLoc, STI);
4003 else
4004 TOut.emitStoreWithSymOffset(Inst.getOpcode(), DstReg, BaseReg, HiOperand,
4005 LoOperand, TmpReg, IDLoc, STI);
4006 }
4007}
4008
4009bool MipsAsmParser::expandLoadStoreMultiple(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
4010 MCStreamer &Out,
4011 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4012 unsigned OpNum = Inst.getNumOperands();
4013 unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
4014 unsigned NewOpcode = Opcode == Mips::SWM_MM ? Mips::SWM32_MM : Mips::LWM32_MM;
4015
4016 assert(Inst.getOperand(OpNum - 1).isImm() &&
4017 Inst.getOperand(OpNum - 2).isReg() &&
4018 Inst.getOperand(OpNum - 3).isReg() && "Invalid instruction operand.");
4019
4020 if (OpNum < 8 && Inst.getOperand(OpNum - 1).getImm() <= 60 &&
4021 Inst.getOperand(OpNum - 1).getImm() >= 0 &&
4022 (Inst.getOperand(OpNum - 2).getReg() == Mips::SP ||
4023 Inst.getOperand(OpNum - 2).getReg() == Mips::SP_64) &&
4024 (Inst.getOperand(OpNum - 3).getReg() == Mips::RA ||
4025 Inst.getOperand(OpNum - 3).getReg() == Mips::RA_64)) {
4026 // It can be implemented as SWM16 or LWM16 instruction.
4027 if (inMicroMipsMode() && hasMips32r6())
4028 NewOpcode = Opcode == Mips::SWM_MM ? Mips::SWM16_MMR6 : Mips::LWM16_MMR6;
4029 else
4030 NewOpcode = Opcode == Mips::SWM_MM ? Mips::SWM16_MM : Mips::LWM16_MM;
4031 }
4032
4033 Inst.setOpcode(NewOpcode);
4034 Out.EmitInstruction(Inst, *STI);
4035 return false;
4036}
4037
4038bool MipsAsmParser::expandCondBranches(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
4039 MCStreamer &Out,
4040 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4041 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4042 bool EmittedNoMacroWarning = false;
4043 unsigned PseudoOpcode = Inst.getOpcode();
4044 unsigned SrcReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
4045 const MCOperand &TrgOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
4046 const MCExpr *OffsetExpr = Inst.getOperand(2).getExpr();
4047
4048 unsigned ZeroSrcOpcode, ZeroTrgOpcode;
4049 bool ReverseOrderSLT, IsUnsigned, IsLikely, AcceptsEquality;
4050
4051 unsigned TrgReg;
4052 if (TrgOp.isReg())
4053 TrgReg = TrgOp.getReg();
4054 else if (TrgOp.isImm()) {
4055 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
4056 EmittedNoMacroWarning = true;
4057
4058 TrgReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
4059 if (!TrgReg)
4060 return true;
4061
4062 switch(PseudoOpcode) {
4063 default:
4064 llvm_unreachable("unknown opcode for branch pseudo-instruction");
4065 case Mips::BLTImmMacro:
4066 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BLT;
4067 break;
4068 case Mips::BLEImmMacro:
4069 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BLE;
4070 break;
4071 case Mips::BGEImmMacro:
4072 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BGE;
4073 break;
4074 case Mips::BGTImmMacro:
4075 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BGT;
4076 break;
4077 case Mips::BLTUImmMacro:
4078 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BLTU;
4079 break;
4080 case Mips::BLEUImmMacro:
4081 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BLEU;
4082 break;
4083 case Mips::BGEUImmMacro:
4084 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BGEU;
4085 break;
4086 case Mips::BGTUImmMacro:
4087 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BGTU;
4088 break;
4089 case Mips::BLTLImmMacro:
4090 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BLTL;
4091 break;
4092 case Mips::BLELImmMacro:
4093 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BLEL;
4094 break;
4095 case Mips::BGELImmMacro:
4096 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BGEL;
4097 break;
4098 case Mips::BGTLImmMacro:
4099 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BGTL;
4100 break;
4101 case Mips::BLTULImmMacro:
4102 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BLTUL;
4103 break;
4104 case Mips::BLEULImmMacro:
4105 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BLEUL;
4106 break;
4107 case Mips::BGEULImmMacro:
4108 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BGEUL;
4109 break;
4110 case Mips::BGTULImmMacro:
4111 PseudoOpcode = Mips::BGTUL;
4112 break;
4113 }
4114
4115 if (loadImmediate(TrgOp.getImm(), TrgReg, Mips::NoRegister, !isGP64bit(),
4116 false, IDLoc, Out, STI))
4117 return true;
4118 }
4119
4120 switch (PseudoOpcode) {
4121 case Mips::BLT:
4122 case Mips::BLTU:
4123 case Mips::BLTL:
4124 case Mips::BLTUL:
4125 AcceptsEquality = false;
4126 ReverseOrderSLT = false;
4127 IsUnsigned =
4128 ((PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLTU) || (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLTUL));
4129 IsLikely = ((PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLTL) || (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLTUL));
4130 ZeroSrcOpcode = Mips::BGTZ;
4131 ZeroTrgOpcode = Mips::BLTZ;
4132 break;
4133 case Mips::BLE:
4134 case Mips::BLEU:
4135 case Mips::BLEL:
4136 case Mips::BLEUL:
4137 AcceptsEquality = true;
4138 ReverseOrderSLT = true;
4139 IsUnsigned =
4140 ((PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLEU) || (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLEUL));
4141 IsLikely = ((PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLEL) || (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLEUL));
4142 ZeroSrcOpcode = Mips::BGEZ;
4143 ZeroTrgOpcode = Mips::BLEZ;
4144 break;
4145 case Mips::BGE:
4146 case Mips::BGEU:
4147 case Mips::BGEL:
4148 case Mips::BGEUL:
4149 AcceptsEquality = true;
4150 ReverseOrderSLT = false;
4151 IsUnsigned =
4152 ((PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGEU) || (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGEUL));
4153 IsLikely = ((PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGEL) || (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGEUL));
4154 ZeroSrcOpcode = Mips::BLEZ;
4155 ZeroTrgOpcode = Mips::BGEZ;
4156 break;
4157 case Mips::BGT:
4158 case Mips::BGTU:
4159 case Mips::BGTL:
4160 case Mips::BGTUL:
4161 AcceptsEquality = false;
4162 ReverseOrderSLT = true;
4163 IsUnsigned =
4164 ((PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGTU) || (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGTUL));
4165 IsLikely = ((PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGTL) || (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGTUL));
4166 ZeroSrcOpcode = Mips::BLTZ;
4167 ZeroTrgOpcode = Mips::BGTZ;
4168 break;
4169 default:
4170 llvm_unreachable("unknown opcode for branch pseudo-instruction");
4171 }
4172
4173 bool IsTrgRegZero = (TrgReg == Mips::ZERO);
4174 bool IsSrcRegZero = (SrcReg == Mips::ZERO);
4175 if (IsSrcRegZero && IsTrgRegZero) {
4176 // FIXME: All of these Opcode-specific if's are needed for compatibility
4177 // with GAS' behaviour. However, they may not generate the most efficient
4178 // code in some circumstances.
4179 if (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLT) {
4180 TOut.emitRX(Mips::BLTZ, Mips::ZERO, MCOperand::createExpr(OffsetExpr),
4181 IDLoc, STI);
4182 return false;
4183 }
4184 if (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLE) {
4185 TOut.emitRX(Mips::BLEZ, Mips::ZERO, MCOperand::createExpr(OffsetExpr),
4186 IDLoc, STI);
4187 Warning(IDLoc, "branch is always taken");
4188 return false;
4189 }
4190 if (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGE) {
4191 TOut.emitRX(Mips::BGEZ, Mips::ZERO, MCOperand::createExpr(OffsetExpr),
4192 IDLoc, STI);
4193 Warning(IDLoc, "branch is always taken");
4194 return false;
4195 }
4196 if (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGT) {
4197 TOut.emitRX(Mips::BGTZ, Mips::ZERO, MCOperand::createExpr(OffsetExpr),
4198 IDLoc, STI);
4199 return false;
4200 }
4201 if (PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGTU) {
4202 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::BNE, Mips::ZERO, Mips::ZERO,
4203 MCOperand::createExpr(OffsetExpr), IDLoc, STI);
4204 return false;
4205 }
4206 if (AcceptsEquality) {
4207 // If both registers are $0 and the pseudo-branch accepts equality, it
4208 // will always be taken, so we emit an unconditional branch.
4209 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::BEQ, Mips::ZERO, Mips::ZERO,
4210 MCOperand::createExpr(OffsetExpr), IDLoc, STI);
4211 Warning(IDLoc, "branch is always taken");
4212 return false;
4213 }
4214 // If both registers are $0 and the pseudo-branch does not accept
4215 // equality, it will never be taken, so we don't have to emit anything.
4216 return false;
4217 }
4218 if (IsSrcRegZero || IsTrgRegZero) {
4219 if ((IsSrcRegZero && PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGTU) ||
4220 (IsTrgRegZero && PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLTU)) {
4221 // If the $rs is $0 and the pseudo-branch is BGTU (0 > x) or
4222 // if the $rt is $0 and the pseudo-branch is BLTU (x < 0),
4223 // the pseudo-branch will never be taken, so we don't emit anything.
4224 // This only applies to unsigned pseudo-branches.
4225 return false;
4226 }
4227 if ((IsSrcRegZero && PseudoOpcode == Mips::BLEU) ||
4228 (IsTrgRegZero && PseudoOpcode == Mips::BGEU)) {
4229 // If the $rs is $0 and the pseudo-branch is BLEU (0 <= x) or
4230 // if the $rt is $0 and the pseudo-branch is BGEU (x >= 0),
4231 // the pseudo-branch will always be taken, so we emit an unconditional
4232 // branch.
4233 // This only applies to unsigned pseudo-branches.
4234 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::BEQ, Mips::ZERO, Mips::ZERO,
4235 MCOperand::createExpr(OffsetExpr), IDLoc, STI);
4236 Warning(IDLoc, "branch is always taken");
4237 return false;
4238 }
4239 if (IsUnsigned) {
4240 // If the $rs is $0 and the pseudo-branch is BLTU (0 < x) or
4241 // if the $rt is $0 and the pseudo-branch is BGTU (x > 0),
4242 // the pseudo-branch will be taken only when the non-zero register is
4243 // different from 0, so we emit a BNEZ.
4244 //
4245 // If the $rs is $0 and the pseudo-branch is BGEU (0 >= x) or
4246 // if the $rt is $0 and the pseudo-branch is BLEU (x <= 0),
4247 // the pseudo-branch will be taken only when the non-zero register is
4248 // equal to 0, so we emit a BEQZ.
4249 //
4250 // Because only BLEU and BGEU branch on equality, we can use the
4251 // AcceptsEquality variable to decide when to emit the BEQZ.
4252 TOut.emitRRX(AcceptsEquality ? Mips::BEQ : Mips::BNE,
4253 IsSrcRegZero ? TrgReg : SrcReg, Mips::ZERO,
4254 MCOperand::createExpr(OffsetExpr), IDLoc, STI);
4255 return false;
4256 }
4257 // If we have a signed pseudo-branch and one of the registers is $0,
4258 // we can use an appropriate compare-to-zero branch. We select which one
4259 // to use in the switch statement above.
4260 TOut.emitRX(IsSrcRegZero ? ZeroSrcOpcode : ZeroTrgOpcode,
4261 IsSrcRegZero ? TrgReg : SrcReg,
4262 MCOperand::createExpr(OffsetExpr), IDLoc, STI);
4263 return false;
4264 }
4265
4266 // If neither the SrcReg nor the TrgReg are $0, we need AT to perform the
4267 // expansions. If it is not available, we return.
4268 unsigned ATRegNum = getATReg(IDLoc);
4269 if (!ATRegNum)
4270 return true;
4271
4272 if (!EmittedNoMacroWarning)
4273 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
4274
4275 // SLT fits well with 2 of our 4 pseudo-branches:
4276 // BLT, where $rs < $rt, translates into "slt $at, $rs, $rt" and
4277 // BGT, where $rs > $rt, translates into "slt $at, $rt, $rs".
4278 // If the result of the SLT is 1, we branch, and if it's 0, we don't.
4279 // This is accomplished by using a BNEZ with the result of the SLT.
4280 //
4281 // The other 2 pseudo-branches are opposites of the above 2 (BGE with BLT
4282 // and BLE with BGT), so we change the BNEZ into a BEQZ.
4283 // Because only BGE and BLE branch on equality, we can use the
4284 // AcceptsEquality variable to decide when to emit the BEQZ.
4285 // Note that the order of the SLT arguments doesn't change between
4286 // opposites.
4287 //
4288 // The same applies to the unsigned variants, except that SLTu is used
4289 // instead of SLT.
4290 TOut.emitRRR(IsUnsigned ? Mips::SLTu : Mips::SLT, ATRegNum,
4291 ReverseOrderSLT ? TrgReg : SrcReg,
4292 ReverseOrderSLT ? SrcReg : TrgReg, IDLoc, STI);
4293
4294 TOut.emitRRX(IsLikely ? (AcceptsEquality ? Mips::BEQL : Mips::BNEL)
4295 : (AcceptsEquality ? Mips::BEQ : Mips::BNE),
4296 ATRegNum, Mips::ZERO, MCOperand::createExpr(OffsetExpr), IDLoc,
4297 STI);
4298 return false;
4299}
4300
4301// Expand a integer division macro.
4302//
4303// Notably we don't have to emit a warning when encountering $rt as the $zero
4304// register, or 0 as an immediate. processInstruction() has already done that.
4305//
4306// The destination register can only be $zero when expanding (S)DivIMacro or
4307// D(S)DivMacro.
4308
4309bool MipsAsmParser::expandDivRem(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
4310 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI, const bool IsMips64,
4311 const bool Signed) {
4312 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4313
4314 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
4315
4316 const MCOperand &RdRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0);
4317 assert(RdRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
4318 unsigned RdReg = RdRegOp.getReg();
4319
4320 const MCOperand &RsRegOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
4321 assert(RsRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
4322 unsigned RsReg = RsRegOp.getReg();
4323
4324 unsigned RtReg;
4325 int64_t ImmValue;
4326
4327 const MCOperand &RtOp = Inst.getOperand(2);
4328 assert((RtOp.isReg() || RtOp.isImm()) &&
4329 "expected register or immediate operand kind");
4330 if (RtOp.isReg())
4331 RtReg = RtOp.getReg();
4332 else
4333 ImmValue = RtOp.getImm();
4334
4335 unsigned DivOp;
4336 unsigned ZeroReg;
4337 unsigned SubOp;
4338
4339 if (IsMips64) {
4340 DivOp = Signed ? Mips::DSDIV : Mips::DUDIV;
4341 ZeroReg = Mips::ZERO_64;
4342 SubOp = Mips::DSUB;
4343 } else {
4344 DivOp = Signed ? Mips::SDIV : Mips::UDIV;
4345 ZeroReg = Mips::ZERO;
4346 SubOp = Mips::SUB;
4347 }
4348
4349 bool UseTraps = useTraps();
4350
4351 unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
4352 bool isDiv = Opcode == Mips::SDivMacro || Opcode == Mips::SDivIMacro ||
4353 Opcode == Mips::UDivMacro || Opcode == Mips::UDivIMacro ||
4354 Opcode == Mips::DSDivMacro || Opcode == Mips::DSDivIMacro ||
4355 Opcode == Mips::DUDivMacro || Opcode == Mips::DUDivIMacro;
4356
4357 bool isRem = Opcode == Mips::SRemMacro || Opcode == Mips::SRemIMacro ||
4358 Opcode == Mips::URemMacro || Opcode == Mips::URemIMacro ||
4359 Opcode == Mips::DSRemMacro || Opcode == Mips::DSRemIMacro ||
4360 Opcode == Mips::DURemMacro || Opcode == Mips::DURemIMacro;
4361
4362 if (RtOp.isImm()) {
4363 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
4364 if (!ATReg)
4365 return true;
4366
4367 if (ImmValue == 0) {
4368 if (UseTraps)
4369 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::TEQ, ZeroReg, ZeroReg, 0x7, IDLoc, STI);
4370 else
4371 TOut.emitII(Mips::BREAK, 0x7, 0, IDLoc, STI);
4372 return false;
4373 }
4374
4375 if (isRem && (ImmValue == 1 || (Signed && (ImmValue == -1)))) {
4376 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::OR, RdReg, ZeroReg, ZeroReg, IDLoc, STI);
4377 return false;
4378 } else if (isDiv && ImmValue == 1) {
4379 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::OR, RdReg, RsReg, Mips::ZERO, IDLoc, STI);
4380 return false;
4381 } else if (isDiv && Signed && ImmValue == -1) {
4382 TOut.emitRRR(SubOp, RdReg, ZeroReg, RsReg, IDLoc, STI);
4383 return false;
4384 } else {
4385 if (loadImmediate(ImmValue, ATReg, Mips::NoRegister, isInt<32>(ImmValue),
4386 false, Inst.getLoc(), Out, STI))
4387 return true;
4388 TOut.emitRR(DivOp, RsReg, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
4389 TOut.emitR(isDiv ? Mips::MFLO : Mips::MFHI, RdReg, IDLoc, STI);
4390 return false;
4391 }
4392 return true;
4393 }
4394
4395 // If the macro expansion of (d)div(u) or (d)rem(u) would always trap or
4396 // break, insert the trap/break and exit. This gives a different result to
4397 // GAS. GAS has an inconsistency/missed optimization in that not all cases
4398 // are handled equivalently. As the observed behaviour is the same, we're ok.
4399 if (RtReg == Mips::ZERO || RtReg == Mips::ZERO_64) {
4400 if (UseTraps) {
4401 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::TEQ, ZeroReg, ZeroReg, 0x7, IDLoc, STI);
4402 return false;
4403 }
4404 TOut.emitII(Mips::BREAK, 0x7, 0, IDLoc, STI);
4405 return false;
4406 }
4407
4408 // (d)rem(u) $0, $X, $Y is a special case. Like div $zero, $X, $Y, it does
4409 // not expand to macro sequence.
4410 if (isRem && (RdReg == Mips::ZERO || RdReg == Mips::ZERO_64)) {
4411 TOut.emitRR(DivOp, RsReg, RtReg, IDLoc, STI);
4412 return false;
4413 }
4414
4415 // Temporary label for first branch traget
4416 MCContext &Context = TOut.getStreamer().getContext();
4417 MCSymbol *BrTarget;
4418 MCOperand LabelOp;
4419
4420 if (UseTraps) {
4421 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::TEQ, RtReg, ZeroReg, 0x7, IDLoc, STI);
4422 } else {
4423 // Branch to the li instruction.
4424 BrTarget = Context.createTempSymbol();
4425 LabelOp = MCOperand::createExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(BrTarget, Context));
4426 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::BNE, RtReg, ZeroReg, LabelOp, IDLoc, STI);
4427 }
4428
4429 TOut.emitRR(DivOp, RsReg, RtReg, IDLoc, STI);
4430
4431 if (!UseTraps)
4432 TOut.emitII(Mips::BREAK, 0x7, 0, IDLoc, STI);
4433
4434 if (!Signed) {
4435 if (!UseTraps)
4436 TOut.getStreamer().EmitLabel(BrTarget);
4437
4438 TOut.emitR(isDiv ? Mips::MFLO : Mips::MFHI, RdReg, IDLoc, STI);
4439 return false;
4440 }
4441
4442 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
4443 if (!ATReg)
4444 return true;
4445
4446 if (!UseTraps)
4447 TOut.getStreamer().EmitLabel(BrTarget);
4448
4449 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ADDiu, ATReg, ZeroReg, -1, IDLoc, STI);
4450
4451 // Temporary label for the second branch target.
4452 MCSymbol *BrTargetEnd = Context.createTempSymbol();
4453 MCOperand LabelOpEnd =
4454 MCOperand::createExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(BrTargetEnd, Context));
4455
4456 // Branch to the mflo instruction.
4457 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::BNE, RtReg, ATReg, LabelOpEnd, IDLoc, STI);
4458
4459 if (IsMips64) {
4460 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ADDiu, ATReg, ZeroReg, 1, IDLoc, STI);
4461 TOut.emitDSLL(ATReg, ATReg, 63, IDLoc, STI);
4462 } else {
4463 TOut.emitRI(Mips::LUi, ATReg, (uint16_t)0x8000, IDLoc, STI);
4464 }
4465
4466 if (UseTraps)
4467 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::TEQ, RsReg, ATReg, 0x6, IDLoc, STI);
4468 else {
4469 // Branch to the mflo instruction.
4470 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::BNE, RsReg, ATReg, LabelOpEnd, IDLoc, STI);
4471 TOut.emitNop(IDLoc, STI);
4472 TOut.emitII(Mips::BREAK, 0x6, 0, IDLoc, STI);
4473 }
4474
4475 TOut.getStreamer().EmitLabel(BrTargetEnd);
4476 TOut.emitR(isDiv ? Mips::MFLO : Mips::MFHI, RdReg, IDLoc, STI);
4477 return false;
4478}
4479
4480bool MipsAsmParser::expandTrunc(MCInst &Inst, bool IsDouble, bool Is64FPU,
4481 SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
4482 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4483 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4484
4485 assert(Inst.getNumOperands() == 3 && "Invalid operand count");
4486 assert(Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() && Inst.getOperand(1).isReg() &&
4487 Inst.getOperand(2).isReg() && "Invalid instruction operand.");
4488
4489 unsigned FirstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
4490 unsigned SecondReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
4491 unsigned ThirdReg = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg();
4492
4493 if (hasMips1() && !hasMips2()) {
4494 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
4495 if (!ATReg)
4496 return true;
4497 TOut.emitRR(Mips::CFC1, ThirdReg, Mips::RA, IDLoc, STI);
4498 TOut.emitRR(Mips::CFC1, ThirdReg, Mips::RA, IDLoc, STI);
4499 TOut.emitNop(IDLoc, STI);
4500 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ORi, ATReg, ThirdReg, 0x3, IDLoc, STI);
4501 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::XORi, ATReg, ATReg, 0x2, IDLoc, STI);
4502 TOut.emitRR(Mips::CTC1, Mips::RA, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
4503 TOut.emitNop(IDLoc, STI);
4504 TOut.emitRR(IsDouble ? (Is64FPU ? Mips::CVT_W_D64 : Mips::CVT_W_D32)
4505 : Mips::CVT_W_S,
4506 FirstReg, SecondReg, IDLoc, STI);
4507 TOut.emitRR(Mips::CTC1, Mips::RA, ThirdReg, IDLoc, STI);
4508 TOut.emitNop(IDLoc, STI);
4509 return false;
4510 }
4511
4512 TOut.emitRR(IsDouble ? (Is64FPU ? Mips::TRUNC_W_D64 : Mips::TRUNC_W_D32)
4513 : Mips::TRUNC_W_S,
4514 FirstReg, SecondReg, IDLoc, STI);
4515
4516 return false;
4517}
4518
4519bool MipsAsmParser::expandUlh(MCInst &Inst, bool Signed, SMLoc IDLoc,
4520 MCStreamer &Out, const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4521 if (hasMips32r6() || hasMips64r6()) {
4522 return Error(IDLoc, "instruction not supported on mips32r6 or mips64r6");
4523 }
4524
4525 const MCOperand &DstRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0);
4526 assert(DstRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
4527 const MCOperand &SrcRegOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
4528 assert(SrcRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
4529 const MCOperand &OffsetImmOp = Inst.getOperand(2);
4530 assert(OffsetImmOp.isImm() && "expected immediate operand kind");
4531
4532 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4533 unsigned DstReg = DstRegOp.getReg();
4534 unsigned SrcReg = SrcRegOp.getReg();
4535 int64_t OffsetValue = OffsetImmOp.getImm();
4536
4537 // NOTE: We always need AT for ULHU, as it is always used as the source
4538 // register for one of the LBu's.
4539 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
4540 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
4541 if (!ATReg)
4542 return true;
4543
4544 bool IsLargeOffset = !(isInt<16>(OffsetValue + 1) && isInt<16>(OffsetValue));
4545 if (IsLargeOffset) {
4546 if (loadImmediate(OffsetValue, ATReg, SrcReg, !ABI.ArePtrs64bit(), true,
4547 IDLoc, Out, STI))
4548 return true;
4549 }
4550
4551 int64_t FirstOffset = IsLargeOffset ? 0 : OffsetValue;
4552 int64_t SecondOffset = IsLargeOffset ? 1 : (OffsetValue + 1);
4553 if (isLittle())
4554 std::swap(FirstOffset, SecondOffset);
4555
4556 unsigned FirstLbuDstReg = IsLargeOffset ? DstReg : ATReg;
4557 unsigned SecondLbuDstReg = IsLargeOffset ? ATReg : DstReg;
4558
4559 unsigned LbuSrcReg = IsLargeOffset ? ATReg : SrcReg;
4560 unsigned SllReg = IsLargeOffset ? DstReg : ATReg;
4561
4562 TOut.emitRRI(Signed ? Mips::LB : Mips::LBu, FirstLbuDstReg, LbuSrcReg,
4563 FirstOffset, IDLoc, STI);
4564 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::LBu, SecondLbuDstReg, LbuSrcReg, SecondOffset, IDLoc, STI);
4565 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SLL, SllReg, SllReg, 8, IDLoc, STI);
4566 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::OR, DstReg, DstReg, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
4567
4568 return false;
4569}
4570
4571bool MipsAsmParser::expandUsh(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
4572 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4573 if (hasMips32r6() || hasMips64r6()) {
4574 return Error(IDLoc, "instruction not supported on mips32r6 or mips64r6");
4575 }
4576
4577 const MCOperand &DstRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0);
4578 assert(DstRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
4579 const MCOperand &SrcRegOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
4580 assert(SrcRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
4581 const MCOperand &OffsetImmOp = Inst.getOperand(2);
4582 assert(OffsetImmOp.isImm() && "expected immediate operand kind");
4583
4584 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4585 unsigned DstReg = DstRegOp.getReg();
4586 unsigned SrcReg = SrcRegOp.getReg();
4587 int64_t OffsetValue = OffsetImmOp.getImm();
4588
4589 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
4590 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
4591 if (!ATReg)
4592 return true;
4593
4594 bool IsLargeOffset = !(isInt<16>(OffsetValue + 1) && isInt<16>(OffsetValue));
4595 if (IsLargeOffset) {
4596 if (loadImmediate(OffsetValue, ATReg, SrcReg, !ABI.ArePtrs64bit(), true,
4597 IDLoc, Out, STI))
4598 return true;
4599 }
4600
4601 int64_t FirstOffset = IsLargeOffset ? 1 : (OffsetValue + 1);
4602 int64_t SecondOffset = IsLargeOffset ? 0 : OffsetValue;
4603 if (isLittle())
4604 std::swap(FirstOffset, SecondOffset);
4605
4606 if (IsLargeOffset) {
4607 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SB, DstReg, ATReg, FirstOffset, IDLoc, STI);
4608 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SRL, DstReg, DstReg, 8, IDLoc, STI);
4609 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SB, DstReg, ATReg, SecondOffset, IDLoc, STI);
4610 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::LBu, ATReg, ATReg, 0, IDLoc, STI);
4611 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SLL, DstReg, DstReg, 8, IDLoc, STI);
4612 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::OR, DstReg, DstReg, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
4613 } else {
4614 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SB, DstReg, SrcReg, FirstOffset, IDLoc, STI);
4615 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SRL, ATReg, DstReg, 8, IDLoc, STI);
4616 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SB, ATReg, SrcReg, SecondOffset, IDLoc, STI);
4617 }
4618
4619 return false;
4620}
4621
4622bool MipsAsmParser::expandUxw(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
4623 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4624 if (hasMips32r6() || hasMips64r6()) {
4625 return Error(IDLoc, "instruction not supported on mips32r6 or mips64r6");
4626 }
4627
4628 const MCOperand &DstRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0);
4629 assert(DstRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
4630 const MCOperand &SrcRegOp = Inst.getOperand(1);
4631 assert(SrcRegOp.isReg() && "expected register operand kind");
4632 const MCOperand &OffsetImmOp = Inst.getOperand(2);
4633 assert(OffsetImmOp.isImm() && "expected immediate operand kind");
4634
4635 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4636 unsigned DstReg = DstRegOp.getReg();
4637 unsigned SrcReg = SrcRegOp.getReg();
4638 int64_t OffsetValue = OffsetImmOp.getImm();
4639
4640 // Compute left/right load/store offsets.
4641 bool IsLargeOffset = !(isInt<16>(OffsetValue + 3) && isInt<16>(OffsetValue));
4642 int64_t LxlOffset = IsLargeOffset ? 0 : OffsetValue;
4643 int64_t LxrOffset = IsLargeOffset ? 3 : (OffsetValue + 3);
4644 if (isLittle())
4645 std::swap(LxlOffset, LxrOffset);
4646
4647 bool IsLoadInst = (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::Ulw);
4648 bool DoMove = IsLoadInst && (SrcReg == DstReg) && !IsLargeOffset;
4649 unsigned TmpReg = SrcReg;
4650 if (IsLargeOffset || DoMove) {
4651 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
4652 TmpReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
4653 if (!TmpReg)
4654 return true;
4655 }
4656
4657 if (IsLargeOffset) {
4658 if (loadImmediate(OffsetValue, TmpReg, SrcReg, !ABI.ArePtrs64bit(), true,
4659 IDLoc, Out, STI))
4660 return true;
4661 }
4662
4663 if (DoMove)
4664 std::swap(DstReg, TmpReg);
4665
4666 unsigned XWL = IsLoadInst ? Mips::LWL : Mips::SWL;
4667 unsigned XWR = IsLoadInst ? Mips::LWR : Mips::SWR;
4668 TOut.emitRRI(XWL, DstReg, TmpReg, LxlOffset, IDLoc, STI);
4669 TOut.emitRRI(XWR, DstReg, TmpReg, LxrOffset, IDLoc, STI);
4670
4671 if (DoMove)
4672 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::OR, TmpReg, DstReg, Mips::ZERO, IDLoc, STI);
4673
4674 return false;
4675}
4676
4677bool MipsAsmParser::expandAliasImmediate(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
4678 MCStreamer &Out,
4679 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4680 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4681
4682 assert(Inst.getNumOperands() == 3 && "Invalid operand count");
4683 assert(Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() &&
4684 Inst.getOperand(1).isReg() &&
4685 Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() && "Invalid instruction operand.");
4686
4687 unsigned ATReg = Mips::NoRegister;
4688 unsigned FinalDstReg = Mips::NoRegister;
4689 unsigned DstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
4690 unsigned SrcReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
4691 int64_t ImmValue = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
4692
4693 bool Is32Bit = isInt<32>(ImmValue) || (!isGP64bit() && isUInt<32>(ImmValue));
4694
4695 unsigned FinalOpcode = Inst.getOpcode();
4696
4697 if (DstReg == SrcReg) {
4698 ATReg = getATReg(Inst.getLoc());
4699 if (!ATReg)
4700 return true;
4701 FinalDstReg = DstReg;
4702 DstReg = ATReg;
4703 }
4704
4705 if (!loadImmediate(ImmValue, DstReg, Mips::NoRegister, Is32Bit, false,
4706 Inst.getLoc(), Out, STI)) {
4707 switch (FinalOpcode) {
4708 default:
4709 llvm_unreachable("unimplemented expansion");
4710 case Mips::ADDi:
4711 FinalOpcode = Mips::ADD;
4712 break;
4713 case Mips::ADDiu:
4714 FinalOpcode = Mips::ADDu;
4715 break;
4716 case Mips::ANDi:
4717 FinalOpcode = Mips::AND;
4718 break;
4719 case Mips::NORImm:
4720 FinalOpcode = Mips::NOR;
4721 break;
4722 case Mips::ORi:
4723 FinalOpcode = Mips::OR;
4724 break;
4725 case Mips::SLTi:
4726 FinalOpcode = Mips::SLT;
4727 break;
4728 case Mips::SLTiu:
4729 FinalOpcode = Mips::SLTu;
4730 break;
4731 case Mips::XORi:
4732 FinalOpcode = Mips::XOR;
4733 break;
4734 case Mips::ADDi_MM:
4735 FinalOpcode = Mips::ADD_MM;
4736 break;
4737 case Mips::ADDiu_MM:
4738 FinalOpcode = Mips::ADDu_MM;
4739 break;
4740 case Mips::ANDi_MM:
4741 FinalOpcode = Mips::AND_MM;
4742 break;
4743 case Mips::ORi_MM:
4744 FinalOpcode = Mips::OR_MM;
4745 break;
4746 case Mips::SLTi_MM:
4747 FinalOpcode = Mips::SLT_MM;
4748 break;
4749 case Mips::SLTiu_MM:
4750 FinalOpcode = Mips::SLTu_MM;
4751 break;
4752 case Mips::XORi_MM:
4753 FinalOpcode = Mips::XOR_MM;
4754 break;
4755 case Mips::ANDi64:
4756 FinalOpcode = Mips::AND64;
4757 break;
4758 case Mips::NORImm64:
4759 FinalOpcode = Mips::NOR64;
4760 break;
4761 case Mips::ORi64:
4762 FinalOpcode = Mips::OR64;
4763 break;
4764 case Mips::SLTImm64:
4765 FinalOpcode = Mips::SLT64;
4766 break;
4767 case Mips::SLTUImm64:
4768 FinalOpcode = Mips::SLTu64;
4769 break;
4770 case Mips::XORi64:
4771 FinalOpcode = Mips::XOR64;
4772 break;
4773 }
4774
4775 if (FinalDstReg == Mips::NoRegister)
4776 TOut.emitRRR(FinalOpcode, DstReg, DstReg, SrcReg, IDLoc, STI);
4777 else
4778 TOut.emitRRR(FinalOpcode, FinalDstReg, FinalDstReg, DstReg, IDLoc, STI);
4779 return false;
4780 }
4781 return true;
4782}
4783
4784bool MipsAsmParser::expandRotation(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
4785 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4786 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4787 unsigned ATReg = Mips::NoRegister;
4788 unsigned DReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
4789 unsigned SReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
4790 unsigned TReg = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg();
4791 unsigned TmpReg = DReg;
4792
4793 unsigned FirstShift = Mips::NOP;
4794 unsigned SecondShift = Mips::NOP;
4795
4796 if (hasMips32r2()) {
4797 if (DReg == SReg) {
4798 TmpReg = getATReg(Inst.getLoc());
4799 if (!TmpReg)
4800 return true;
4801 }
4802
4803 if (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::ROL) {
4804 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::SUBu, TmpReg, Mips::ZERO, TReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4805 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::ROTRV, DReg, SReg, TmpReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4806 return false;
4807 }
4808
4809 if (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::ROR) {
4810 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::ROTRV, DReg, SReg, TReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4811 return false;
4812 }
4813
4814 return true;
4815 }
4816
4817 if (hasMips32()) {
4818 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
4819 default:
4820 llvm_unreachable("unexpected instruction opcode");
4821 case Mips::ROL:
4822 FirstShift = Mips::SRLV;
4823 SecondShift = Mips::SLLV;
4824 break;
4825 case Mips::ROR:
4826 FirstShift = Mips::SLLV;
4827 SecondShift = Mips::SRLV;
4828 break;
4829 }
4830
4831 ATReg = getATReg(Inst.getLoc());
4832 if (!ATReg)
4833 return true;
4834
4835 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::SUBu, ATReg, Mips::ZERO, TReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4836 TOut.emitRRR(FirstShift, ATReg, SReg, ATReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4837 TOut.emitRRR(SecondShift, DReg, SReg, TReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4838 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::OR, DReg, DReg, ATReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4839
4840 return false;
4841 }
4842
4843 return true;
4844}
4845
4846bool MipsAsmParser::expandRotationImm(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
4847 MCStreamer &Out,
4848 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4849 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4850 unsigned ATReg = Mips::NoRegister;
4851 unsigned DReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
4852 unsigned SReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
4853 int64_t ImmValue = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
4854
4855 unsigned FirstShift = Mips::NOP;
4856 unsigned SecondShift = Mips::NOP;
4857
4858 if (hasMips32r2()) {
4859 if (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::ROLImm) {
4860 uint64_t MaxShift = 32;
4861 uint64_t ShiftValue = ImmValue;
4862 if (ImmValue != 0)
4863 ShiftValue = MaxShift - ImmValue;
4864 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ROTR, DReg, SReg, ShiftValue, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4865 return false;
4866 }
4867
4868 if (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::RORImm) {
4869 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::ROTR, DReg, SReg, ImmValue, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4870 return false;
4871 }
4872
4873 return true;
4874 }
4875
4876 if (hasMips32()) {
4877 if (ImmValue == 0) {
4878 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SRL, DReg, SReg, 0, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4879 return false;
4880 }
4881
4882 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
4883 default:
4884 llvm_unreachable("unexpected instruction opcode");
4885 case Mips::ROLImm:
4886 FirstShift = Mips::SLL;
4887 SecondShift = Mips::SRL;
4888 break;
4889 case Mips::RORImm:
4890 FirstShift = Mips::SRL;
4891 SecondShift = Mips::SLL;
4892 break;
4893 }
4894
4895 ATReg = getATReg(Inst.getLoc());
4896 if (!ATReg)
4897 return true;
4898
4899 TOut.emitRRI(FirstShift, ATReg, SReg, ImmValue, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4900 TOut.emitRRI(SecondShift, DReg, SReg, 32 - ImmValue, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4901 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::OR, DReg, DReg, ATReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4902
4903 return false;
4904 }
4905
4906 return true;
4907}
4908
4909bool MipsAsmParser::expandDRotation(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
4910 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4911 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4912 unsigned ATReg = Mips::NoRegister;
4913 unsigned DReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
4914 unsigned SReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
4915 unsigned TReg = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg();
4916 unsigned TmpReg = DReg;
4917
4918 unsigned FirstShift = Mips::NOP;
4919 unsigned SecondShift = Mips::NOP;
4920
4921 if (hasMips64r2()) {
4922 if (TmpReg == SReg) {
4923 TmpReg = getATReg(Inst.getLoc());
4924 if (!TmpReg)
4925 return true;
4926 }
4927
4928 if (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::DROL) {
4929 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::DSUBu, TmpReg, Mips::ZERO, TReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4930 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::DROTRV, DReg, SReg, TmpReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4931 return false;
4932 }
4933
4934 if (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::DROR) {
4935 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::DROTRV, DReg, SReg, TReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4936 return false;
4937 }
4938
4939 return true;
4940 }
4941
4942 if (hasMips64()) {
4943 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
4944 default:
4945 llvm_unreachable("unexpected instruction opcode");
4946 case Mips::DROL:
4947 FirstShift = Mips::DSRLV;
4948 SecondShift = Mips::DSLLV;
4949 break;
4950 case Mips::DROR:
4951 FirstShift = Mips::DSLLV;
4952 SecondShift = Mips::DSRLV;
4953 break;
4954 }
4955
4956 ATReg = getATReg(Inst.getLoc());
4957 if (!ATReg)
4958 return true;
4959
4960 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::DSUBu, ATReg, Mips::ZERO, TReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4961 TOut.emitRRR(FirstShift, ATReg, SReg, ATReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4962 TOut.emitRRR(SecondShift, DReg, SReg, TReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4963 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::OR, DReg, DReg, ATReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
4964
4965 return false;
4966 }
4967
4968 return true;
4969}
4970
4971bool MipsAsmParser::expandDRotationImm(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
4972 MCStreamer &Out,
4973 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
4974 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
4975 unsigned ATReg = Mips::NoRegister;
4976 unsigned DReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
4977 unsigned SReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
4978 int64_t ImmValue = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm() % 64;
4979
4980 unsigned FirstShift = Mips::NOP;
4981 unsigned SecondShift = Mips::NOP;
4982
4983 MCInst TmpInst;
4984
4985 if (hasMips64r2()) {
4986 unsigned FinalOpcode = Mips::NOP;
4987 if (ImmValue == 0)
4988 FinalOpcode = Mips::DROTR;
4989 else if (ImmValue % 32 == 0)
4990 FinalOpcode = Mips::DROTR32;
4991 else if ((ImmValue >= 1) && (ImmValue <= 32)) {
4992 if (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::DROLImm)
4993 FinalOpcode = Mips::DROTR32;
4994 else
4995 FinalOpcode = Mips::DROTR;
4996 } else if (ImmValue >= 33) {
4997 if (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::DROLImm)
4998 FinalOpcode = Mips::DROTR;
4999 else
5000 FinalOpcode = Mips::DROTR32;
5001 }
5002
5003 uint64_t ShiftValue = ImmValue % 32;
5004 if (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::DROLImm)
5005 ShiftValue = (32 - ImmValue % 32) % 32;
5006
5007 TOut.emitRRI(FinalOpcode, DReg, SReg, ShiftValue, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
5008
5009 return false;
5010 }
5011
5012 if (hasMips64()) {
5013 if (ImmValue == 0) {
5014 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::DSRL, DReg, SReg, 0, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
5015 return false;
5016 }
5017
5018 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5019 default:
5020 llvm_unreachable("unexpected instruction opcode");
5021 case Mips::DROLImm:
5022 if ((ImmValue >= 1) && (ImmValue <= 31)) {
5023 FirstShift = Mips::DSLL;
5024 SecondShift = Mips::DSRL32;
5025 }
5026 if (ImmValue == 32) {
5027 FirstShift = Mips::DSLL32;
5028 SecondShift = Mips::DSRL32;
5029 }
5030 if ((ImmValue >= 33) && (ImmValue <= 63)) {
5031 FirstShift = Mips::DSLL32;
5032 SecondShift = Mips::DSRL;
5033 }
5034 break;
5035 case Mips::DRORImm:
5036 if ((ImmValue >= 1) && (ImmValue <= 31)) {
5037 FirstShift = Mips::DSRL;
5038 SecondShift = Mips::DSLL32;
5039 }
5040 if (ImmValue == 32) {
5041 FirstShift = Mips::DSRL32;
5042 SecondShift = Mips::DSLL32;
5043 }
5044 if ((ImmValue >= 33) && (ImmValue <= 63)) {
5045 FirstShift = Mips::DSRL32;
5046 SecondShift = Mips::DSLL;
5047 }
5048 break;
5049 }
5050
5051 ATReg = getATReg(Inst.getLoc());
5052 if (!ATReg)
5053 return true;
5054
5055 TOut.emitRRI(FirstShift, ATReg, SReg, ImmValue % 32, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
5056 TOut.emitRRI(SecondShift, DReg, SReg, (32 - ImmValue % 32) % 32,
5057 Inst.getLoc(), STI);
5058 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::OR, DReg, DReg, ATReg, Inst.getLoc(), STI);
5059
5060 return false;
5061 }
5062
5063 return true;
5064}
5065
5066bool MipsAsmParser::expandAbs(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
5067 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
5068 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5069 unsigned FirstRegOp = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
5070 unsigned SecondRegOp = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
5071
5072 TOut.emitRI(Mips::BGEZ, SecondRegOp, 8, IDLoc, STI);
5073 if (FirstRegOp != SecondRegOp)
5074 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::ADDu, FirstRegOp, SecondRegOp, Mips::ZERO, IDLoc, STI);
5075 else
5076 TOut.emitEmptyDelaySlot(false, IDLoc, STI);
5077 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::SUB, FirstRegOp, Mips::ZERO, SecondRegOp, IDLoc, STI);
5078
5079 return false;
5080}
5081
5082bool MipsAsmParser::expandMulImm(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
5083 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
5084 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5085 unsigned ATReg = Mips::NoRegister;
5086 unsigned DstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
5087 unsigned SrcReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
5088 int32_t ImmValue = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5089
5090 ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
5091 if (!ATReg)
5092 return true;
5093
5094 loadImmediate(ImmValue, ATReg, Mips::NoRegister, true, false, IDLoc, Out,
5095 STI);
5096
5097 TOut.emitRR(Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::MULImmMacro ? Mips::MULT : Mips::DMULT,
5098 SrcReg, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
5099
5100 TOut.emitR(Mips::MFLO, DstReg, IDLoc, STI);
5101
5102 return false;
5103}
5104
5105bool MipsAsmParser::expandMulO(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
5106 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
5107 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5108 unsigned ATReg = Mips::NoRegister;
5109 unsigned DstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
5110 unsigned SrcReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
