5111 unsigned TmpReg = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg();
5112
5113 ATReg = getATReg(Inst.getLoc());
5114 if (!ATReg)
5115 return true;
5116
5117 TOut.emitRR(Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::MULOMacro ? Mips::MULT : Mips::DMULT,
5118 SrcReg, TmpReg, IDLoc, STI);
5119
5120 TOut.emitR(Mips::MFLO, DstReg, IDLoc, STI);
5121
5122 TOut.emitRRI(Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::MULOMacro ? Mips::SRA : Mips::DSRA32,
5123 DstReg, DstReg, 0x1F, IDLoc, STI);
5124
5125 TOut.emitR(Mips::MFHI, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
5126
5127 if (useTraps()) {
5128 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::TNE, DstReg, ATReg, 6, IDLoc, STI);
5129 } else {
5130 MCContext & Context = TOut.getStreamer().getContext();
5131 MCSymbol * BrTarget = Context.createTempSymbol();
5132 MCOperand LabelOp =
5133 MCOperand::createExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(BrTarget, Context));
5134
5135 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::BEQ, DstReg, ATReg, LabelOp, IDLoc, STI);
5136 if (AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder())
5137 TOut.emitNop(IDLoc, STI);
5138 TOut.emitII(Mips::BREAK, 6, 0, IDLoc, STI);
5139
5140 TOut.getStreamer().EmitLabel(BrTarget);
5141 }
5142 TOut.emitR(Mips::MFLO, DstReg, IDLoc, STI);
5143
5144 return false;
5145}
5146
5147bool MipsAsmParser::expandMulOU(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
5148 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
5149 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5150 unsigned ATReg = Mips::NoRegister;
5151 unsigned DstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
5152 unsigned SrcReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
5153 unsigned TmpReg = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg();
5154
5155 ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
5156 if (!ATReg)
5157 return true;
5158
5159 TOut.emitRR(Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::MULOUMacro ? Mips::MULTu : Mips::DMULTu,
5160 SrcReg, TmpReg, IDLoc, STI);
5161
5162 TOut.emitR(Mips::MFHI, ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
5163 TOut.emitR(Mips::MFLO, DstReg, IDLoc, STI);
5164 if (useTraps()) {
5165 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::TNE, ATReg, Mips::ZERO, 6, IDLoc, STI);
5166 } else {
5167 MCContext & Context = TOut.getStreamer().getContext();
5168 MCSymbol * BrTarget = Context.createTempSymbol();
5169 MCOperand LabelOp =
5170 MCOperand::createExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(BrTarget, Context));
5171
5172 TOut.emitRRX(Mips::BEQ, ATReg, Mips::ZERO, LabelOp, IDLoc, STI);
5173 if (AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder())
5174 TOut.emitNop(IDLoc, STI);
5175 TOut.emitII(Mips::BREAK, 6, 0, IDLoc, STI);
5176
5177 TOut.getStreamer().EmitLabel(BrTarget);
5178 }
5179
5180 return false;
5181}
5182
5183bool MipsAsmParser::expandDMULMacro(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
5184 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
5185 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5186 unsigned DstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
5187 unsigned SrcReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
5188 unsigned TmpReg = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg();
5189
5190 TOut.emitRR(Mips::DMULTu, SrcReg, TmpReg, IDLoc, STI);
5191 TOut.emitR(Mips::MFLO, DstReg, IDLoc, STI);
5192
5193 return false;
5194}
5195
5196// Expand 'ld $<reg> offset($reg2)' to 'lw $<reg>, offset($reg2);
5197// lw $<reg+1>>, offset+4($reg2)'
5198// or expand 'sd $<reg> offset($reg2)' to 'sw $<reg>, offset($reg2);
5199// sw $<reg+1>>, offset+4($reg2)'
5200// for O32.
5201bool MipsAsmParser::expandLoadStoreDMacro(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
5202 MCStreamer &Out,
5203 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI,
5204 bool IsLoad) {
5205 if (!isABI_O32())
5206 return true;
5207
5208 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
5209
5210 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5211 unsigned Opcode = IsLoad ? Mips::LW : Mips::SW;
5212 unsigned FirstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
5213 unsigned SecondReg = nextReg(FirstReg);
5214 unsigned BaseReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
5215 if (!SecondReg)
5216 return true;
5217
5218 warnIfRegIndexIsAT(FirstReg, IDLoc);
5219
5220 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() &&
5221 "Offset for load macro is not immediate!");
5222
5223 MCOperand &FirstOffset = Inst.getOperand(2);
5224 signed NextOffset = FirstOffset.getImm() + 4;
5225 MCOperand SecondOffset = MCOperand::createImm(NextOffset);
5226
5227 if (!isInt<16>(FirstOffset.getImm()) || !isInt<16>(NextOffset))
5228 return true;
5229
5230 // For loads, clobber the base register with the second load instead of the
5231 // first if the BaseReg == FirstReg.
5232 if (FirstReg != BaseReg || !IsLoad) {
5233 TOut.emitRRX(Opcode, FirstReg, BaseReg, FirstOffset, IDLoc, STI);
5234 TOut.emitRRX(Opcode, SecondReg, BaseReg, SecondOffset, IDLoc, STI);
5235 } else {
5236 TOut.emitRRX(Opcode, SecondReg, BaseReg, SecondOffset, IDLoc, STI);
5237 TOut.emitRRX(Opcode, FirstReg, BaseReg, FirstOffset, IDLoc, STI);
5238 }
5239
5240 return false;
5241}
5242
5243
5244// Expand 's.d $<reg> offset($reg2)' to 'swc1 $<reg+1>, offset($reg2);
5245// swc1 $<reg>, offset+4($reg2)'
5246// or if little endian to 'swc1 $<reg>, offset($reg2);
5247// swc1 $<reg+1>, offset+4($reg2)'
5248// for Mips1.
5249bool MipsAsmParser::expandStoreDM1Macro(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc,
5250 MCStreamer &Out,
5251 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
5252 if (!isABI_O32())
5253 return true;
5254
5255 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
5256
5257 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5258 unsigned Opcode = Mips::SWC1;
5259 unsigned FirstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
5260 unsigned SecondReg = nextReg(FirstReg);
5261 unsigned BaseReg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
5262 if (!SecondReg)
5263 return true;
5264
5265 warnIfRegIndexIsAT(FirstReg, IDLoc);
5266
5267 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() &&
5268 "Offset for macro is not immediate!");
5269
5270 MCOperand &FirstOffset = Inst.getOperand(2);
5271 signed NextOffset = FirstOffset.getImm() + 4;
5272 MCOperand SecondOffset = MCOperand::createImm(NextOffset);
5273
5274 if (!isInt<16>(FirstOffset.getImm()) || !isInt<16>(NextOffset))
5275 return true;
5276
5277 if (!IsLittleEndian)
5278 std::swap(FirstReg, SecondReg);
5279
5280 TOut.emitRRX(Opcode, FirstReg, BaseReg, FirstOffset, IDLoc, STI);
5281 TOut.emitRRX(Opcode, SecondReg, BaseReg, SecondOffset, IDLoc, STI);
5282
5283 return false;
5284}
5285
5286bool MipsAsmParser::expandSeq(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
5287 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
5288
5289 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
5290 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5291
5292 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() != Mips::ZERO &&
5293 Inst.getOperand(2).getReg() != Mips::ZERO) {
5294 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::XOR, Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(),
5295 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(), Inst.getOperand(2).getReg(),
5296 IDLoc, STI);
5297 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SLTiu, Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(),
5298 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(), 1, IDLoc, STI);
5299 return false;
5300 }
5301
5302 unsigned Reg = 0;
5303 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO) {
5304 Reg = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg();
5305 } else {
5306 Reg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
5307 }
5308 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SLTiu, Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(), Reg, 1, IDLoc, STI);
5309 return false;
5310}
5311
5312bool MipsAsmParser::expandSeqI(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
5313 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
5314 warnIfNoMacro(IDLoc);
5315 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5316
5317 unsigned Opc;
5318 int64_t Imm = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5319 unsigned Reg = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
5320
5321 if (Imm == 0) {
5322 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SLTiu, Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(),
5323 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(), 1, IDLoc, STI);
5324 return false;
5325 } else {
5326
5327 if (Reg == Mips::ZERO) {
5328 Warning(IDLoc, "comparison is always false");
5329 TOut.emitRRR(isGP64bit() ? Mips::DADDu : Mips::ADDu,
5330 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(), Reg, Reg, IDLoc, STI);
5331 return false;
5332 }
5333
5334 if (Imm > -0x8000 && Imm < 0) {
5335 Imm = -Imm;
5336 Opc = isGP64bit() ? Mips::DADDiu : Mips::ADDiu;
5337 } else {
5338 Opc = Mips::XORi;
5339 }
5340 }
5341 if (!isUInt<16>(Imm)) {
5342 unsigned ATReg = getATReg(IDLoc);
5343 if (!ATReg)
5344 return true;
5345
5346 if (loadImmediate(Imm, ATReg, Mips::NoRegister, true, isGP64bit(), IDLoc,
5347 Out, STI))
5348 return true;
5349
5350 TOut.emitRRR(Mips::XOR, Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(),
5351 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(), ATReg, IDLoc, STI);
5352 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SLTiu, Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(),
5353 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(), 1, IDLoc, STI);
5354 return false;
5355 }
5356
5357 TOut.emitRRI(Opc, Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(), Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(),
5358 Imm, IDLoc, STI);
5359 TOut.emitRRI(Mips::SLTiu, Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(),
5360 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(), 1, IDLoc, STI);
5361 return false;
5362}
5363
5364// Map the DSP accumulator and control register to the corresponding gpr
5365// operand. Unlike the other alias, the m(f|t)t(lo|hi|acx) instructions
5366// do not map the DSP registers contigously to gpr registers.
5367static unsigned getRegisterForMxtrDSP(MCInst &Inst, bool IsMFDSP) {
5368 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5369 case Mips::MFTLO:
5370 case Mips::MTTLO:
5371 switch (Inst.getOperand(IsMFDSP ? 1 : 0).getReg()) {
5372 case Mips::AC0:
5373 return Mips::ZERO;
5374 case Mips::AC1:
5375 return Mips::A0;
5376 case Mips::AC2:
5377 return Mips::T0;
5378 case Mips::AC3:
5379 return Mips::T4;
5380 default:
5381 llvm_unreachable("Unknown register for 'mttr' alias!");
5382 }
5383 case Mips::MFTHI:
5384 case Mips::MTTHI:
5385 switch (Inst.getOperand(IsMFDSP ? 1 : 0).getReg()) {
5386 case Mips::AC0:
5387 return Mips::AT;
5388 case Mips::AC1:
5389 return Mips::A1;
5390 case Mips::AC2:
5391 return Mips::T1;
5392 case Mips::AC3:
5393 return Mips::T5;
5394 default:
5395 llvm_unreachable("Unknown register for 'mttr' alias!");
5396 }
5397 case Mips::MFTACX:
5398 case Mips::MTTACX:
5399 switch (Inst.getOperand(IsMFDSP ? 1 : 0).getReg()) {
5400 case Mips::AC0:
5401 return Mips::V0;
5402 case Mips::AC1:
5403 return Mips::A2;
5404 case Mips::AC2:
5405 return Mips::T2;
5406 case Mips::AC3:
5407 return Mips::T6;
5408 default:
5409 llvm_unreachable("Unknown register for 'mttr' alias!");
5410 }
5411 case Mips::MFTDSP:
5412 case Mips::MTTDSP:
5413 return Mips::S0;
5414 default:
5415 llvm_unreachable("Unknown instruction for 'mttr' dsp alias!");
5416 }
5417}
5418
5419// Map the floating point register operand to the corresponding register
5420// operand.
5421static unsigned getRegisterForMxtrFP(MCInst &Inst, bool IsMFTC1) {
5422 switch (Inst.getOperand(IsMFTC1 ? 1 : 0).getReg()) {
5423 case Mips::F0: return Mips::ZERO;
5424 case Mips::F1: return Mips::AT;
5425 case Mips::F2: return Mips::V0;
5426 case Mips::F3: return Mips::V1;
5427 case Mips::F4: return Mips::A0;
5428 case Mips::F5: return Mips::A1;
5429 case Mips::F6: return Mips::A2;
5430 case Mips::F7: return Mips::A3;
5431 case Mips::F8: return Mips::T0;
5432 case Mips::F9: return Mips::T1;
5433 case Mips::F10: return Mips::T2;
5434 case Mips::F11: return Mips::T3;
5435 case Mips::F12: return Mips::T4;
5436 case Mips::F13: return Mips::T5;
5437 case Mips::F14: return Mips::T6;
5438 case Mips::F15: return Mips::T7;
5439 case Mips::F16: return Mips::S0;
5440 case Mips::F17: return Mips::S1;
5441 case Mips::F18: return Mips::S2;
5442 case Mips::F19: return Mips::S3;
5443 case Mips::F20: return Mips::S4;
5444 case Mips::F21: return Mips::S5;
5445 case Mips::F22: return Mips::S6;
5446 case Mips::F23: return Mips::S7;
5447 case Mips::F24: return Mips::T8;
5448 case Mips::F25: return Mips::T9;
5449 case Mips::F26: return Mips::K0;
5450 case Mips::F27: return Mips::K1;
5451 case Mips::F28: return Mips::GP;
5452 case Mips::F29: return Mips::SP;
5453 case Mips::F30: return Mips::FP;
5454 case Mips::F31: return Mips::RA;
5455 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown register for mttc1 alias!");
5456 }
5457}
5458
5459// Map the coprocessor operand the corresponding gpr register operand.
5460static unsigned getRegisterForMxtrC0(MCInst &Inst, bool IsMFTC0) {
5461 switch (Inst.getOperand(IsMFTC0 ? 1 : 0).getReg()) {
5462 case Mips::COP00: return Mips::ZERO;
5463 case Mips::COP01: return Mips::AT;
5464 case Mips::COP02: return Mips::V0;
5465 case Mips::COP03: return Mips::V1;
5466 case Mips::COP04: return Mips::A0;
5467 case Mips::COP05: return Mips::A1;
5468 case Mips::COP06: return Mips::A2;
5469 case Mips::COP07: return Mips::A3;
5470 case Mips::COP08: return Mips::T0;
5471 case Mips::COP09: return Mips::T1;
5472 case Mips::COP010: return Mips::T2;
5473 case Mips::COP011: return Mips::T3;
5474 case Mips::COP012: return Mips::T4;
5475 case Mips::COP013: return Mips::T5;
5476 case Mips::COP014: return Mips::T6;
5477 case Mips::COP015: return Mips::T7;
5478 case Mips::COP016: return Mips::S0;
5479 case Mips::COP017: return Mips::S1;
5480 case Mips::COP018: return Mips::S2;
5481 case Mips::COP019: return Mips::S3;
5482 case Mips::COP020: return Mips::S4;
5483 case Mips::COP021: return Mips::S5;
5484 case Mips::COP022: return Mips::S6;
5485 case Mips::COP023: return Mips::S7;
5486 case Mips::COP024: return Mips::T8;
5487 case Mips::COP025: return Mips::T9;
5488 case Mips::COP026: return Mips::K0;
5489 case Mips::COP027: return Mips::K1;
5490 case Mips::COP028: return Mips::GP;
5491 case Mips::COP029: return Mips::SP;
5492 case Mips::COP030: return Mips::FP;
5493 case Mips::COP031: return Mips::RA;
5494 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown register for mttc0 alias!");
5495 }
5496}
5497
5498/// Expand an alias of 'mftr' or 'mttr' into the full instruction, by producing
5499/// an mftr or mttr with the correctly mapped gpr register, u, sel and h bits.
5500bool MipsAsmParser::expandMXTRAlias(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out,
5501 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI) {
5502 MipsTargetStreamer &TOut = getTargetStreamer();
5503 unsigned rd = 0;
5504 unsigned u = 1;
5505 unsigned sel = 0;
5506 unsigned h = 0;
5507 bool IsMFTR = false;
5508 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5509 case Mips::MFTC0:
5510 IsMFTR = true;
5511 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5512 case Mips::MTTC0:
5513 u = 0;
5514 rd = getRegisterForMxtrC0(Inst, IsMFTR);
5515 sel = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5516 break;
5517 case Mips::MFTGPR:
5518 IsMFTR = true;
5519 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5520 case Mips::MTTGPR:
5521 rd = Inst.getOperand(IsMFTR ? 1 : 0).getReg();
5522 break;
5523 case Mips::MFTLO:
5524 case Mips::MFTHI:
5525 case Mips::MFTACX:
5526 case Mips::MFTDSP:
5527 IsMFTR = true;
5528 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5529 case Mips::MTTLO:
5530 case Mips::MTTHI:
5531 case Mips::MTTACX:
5532 case Mips::MTTDSP:
5533 rd = getRegisterForMxtrDSP(Inst, IsMFTR);
5534 sel = 1;
5535 break;
5536 case Mips::MFTHC1:
5537 h = 1;
5538 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5539 case Mips::MFTC1:
5540 IsMFTR = true;
5541 rd = getRegisterForMxtrFP(Inst, IsMFTR);
5542 sel = 2;
5543 break;
5544 case Mips::MTTHC1:
5545 h = 1;
5546 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5547 case Mips::MTTC1:
5548 rd = getRegisterForMxtrFP(Inst, IsMFTR);
5549 sel = 2;
5550 break;
5551 case Mips::CFTC1:
5552 IsMFTR = true;
5553 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5554 case Mips::CTTC1:
5555 rd = getRegisterForMxtrFP(Inst, IsMFTR);
5556 sel = 3;
5557 break;
5558 }
5559 unsigned Op0 = IsMFTR ? Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() : rd;
5560 unsigned Op1 =
5561 IsMFTR ? rd
5562 : (Inst.getOpcode() != Mips::MTTDSP ? Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()
5563 : Inst.getOperand(0).getReg());
5564
5565 TOut.emitRRIII(IsMFTR ? Mips::MFTR : Mips::MTTR, Op0, Op1, u, sel, h, IDLoc,
5566 STI);
5567 return false;
5568}
5569
5570unsigned
5571MipsAsmParser::checkEarlyTargetMatchPredicate(MCInst &Inst,
5572 const OperandVector &Operands) {
5573 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5574 default:
5575 return Match_Success;
5576 case Mips::DATI:
5577 case Mips::DAHI:
5578 if (static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[1])
5579 .isValidForTie(static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[2])))
5580 return Match_Success;
5581 return Match_RequiresSameSrcAndDst;
5582 }
5583}
5584
5585unsigned MipsAsmParser::checkTargetMatchPredicate(MCInst &Inst) {
5586 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
5587 // As described by the MIPSR6 spec, daui must not use the zero operand for
5588 // its source operand.
5589 case Mips::DAUI:
5590 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
5591 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
5592 return Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister;
5593 return Match_Success;
5594 // As described by the Mips32r2 spec, the registers Rd and Rs for
5595 // jalr.hb must be different.
5596 // It also applies for registers Rt and Rs of microMIPSr6 jalrc.hb instruction
5597 // and registers Rd and Base for microMIPS lwp instruction
5598 case Mips::JALR_HB:
5599 case Mips::JALR_HB64:
5600 case Mips::JALRC_HB_MMR6:
5601 case Mips::JALRC_MMR6:
5602 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(1).getReg())
5603 return Match_RequiresDifferentSrcAndDst;
5604 return Match_Success;
5605 case Mips::LWP_MM:
5606 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(2).getReg())
5607 return Match_RequiresDifferentSrcAndDst;
5608 return Match_Success;
5609 case Mips::SYNC:
5610 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getImm() != 0 && !hasMips32())
5611 return Match_NonZeroOperandForSync;
5612 return Match_Success;
5613 case Mips::MFC0:
5614 case Mips::MTC0:
5615 case Mips::MTC2:
5616 case Mips::MFC2:
5617 if (Inst.getOperand(2).getImm() != 0 && !hasMips32() && !isCheri() && STI->getCPU() != "beri")
5618 return Match_NonZeroOperandForMTCX;
5619 return Match_Success;
5620 // As described the MIPSR6 spec, the compact branches that compare registers
5621 // must:
5622 // a) Not use the zero register.
5623 // b) Not use the same register twice.
5624 // c) rs < rt for bnec, beqc.
5625 // NB: For this case, the encoding will swap the operands as their
5626 // ordering doesn't matter. GAS performs this transformation too.
5627 // Hence, that constraint does not have to be enforced.
5628 //
5629 // The compact branches that branch iff the signed addition of two registers
5630 // would overflow must have rs >= rt. That can be handled like beqc/bnec with
5631 // operand swapping. They do not have restriction of using the zero register.
5632 case Mips::BLEZC: case Mips::BLEZC_MMR6:
5633 case Mips::BGEZC: case Mips::BGEZC_MMR6:
5634 case Mips::BGTZC: case Mips::BGTZC_MMR6:
5635 case Mips::BLTZC: case Mips::BLTZC_MMR6:
5636 case Mips::BEQZC: case Mips::BEQZC_MMR6:
5637 case Mips::BNEZC: case Mips::BNEZC_MMR6:
5638 case Mips::BLEZC64:
5639 case Mips::BGEZC64:
5640 case Mips::BGTZC64:
5641 case Mips::BLTZC64:
5642 case Mips::BEQZC64:
5643 case Mips::BNEZC64:
5644 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
5645 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
5646 return Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister;
5647 return Match_Success;
5648 case Mips::BGEC: case Mips::BGEC_MMR6:
5649 case Mips::BLTC: case Mips::BLTC_MMR6:
5650 case Mips::BGEUC: case Mips::BGEUC_MMR6:
5651 case Mips::BLTUC: case Mips::BLTUC_MMR6:
5652 case Mips::BEQC: case Mips::BEQC_MMR6:
5653 case Mips::BNEC: case Mips::BNEC_MMR6:
5654 case Mips::BGEC64:
5655 case Mips::BLTC64:
5656 case Mips::BGEUC64:
5657 case Mips::BLTUC64:
5658 case Mips::BEQC64:
5659 case Mips::BNEC64:
5660 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
5661 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
5662 return Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister;
5663 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO ||
5664 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == Mips::ZERO_64)
5665 return Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister;
5666 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(1).getReg())
5667 return Match_RequiresDifferentOperands;
5668 return Match_Success;
5669 case Mips::DINS: {
5670 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() && Inst.getOperand(3).isImm() &&
5671 "Operands must be immediates for dins!");
5672 const signed Pos = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5673 const signed Size = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm();
5674 if ((0 > (Pos + Size)) || ((Pos + Size) > 32))
5675 return Match_RequiresPosSizeRange0_32;
5676 return Match_Success;
5677 }
5678 case Mips::DINSM:
5679 case Mips::DINSU: {
5680 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() && Inst.getOperand(3).isImm() &&
5681 "Operands must be immediates for dinsm/dinsu!");
5682 const signed Pos = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5683 const signed Size = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm();
5684 if ((32 >= (Pos + Size)) || ((Pos + Size) > 64))
5685 return Match_RequiresPosSizeRange33_64;
5686 return Match_Success;
5687 }
5688 case Mips::DEXT: {
5689 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() && Inst.getOperand(3).isImm() &&
5690 "Operands must be immediates for DEXTM!");
5691 const signed Pos = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5692 const signed Size = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm();
5693 if ((1 > (Pos + Size)) || ((Pos + Size) > 63))
5694 return Match_RequiresPosSizeUImm6;
5695 return Match_Success;
5696 }
5697 case Mips::DEXTM:
5698 case Mips::DEXTU: {
5699 assert(Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() && Inst.getOperand(3).isImm() &&
5700 "Operands must be immediates for dextm/dextu!");
5701 const signed Pos = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
5702 const signed Size = Inst.getOperand(3).getImm();
5703 if ((32 > (Pos + Size)) || ((Pos + Size) > 64))
5704 return Match_RequiresPosSizeRange33_64;
5705 return Match_Success;
5706 }
5707 case Mips::CRC32B: case Mips::CRC32CB:
5708 case Mips::CRC32H: case Mips::CRC32CH:
5709 case Mips::CRC32W: case Mips::CRC32CW:
5710 case Mips::CRC32D: case Mips::CRC32CD:
5711 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() != Inst.getOperand(2).getReg())
5712 return Match_RequiresSameSrcAndDst;
5713 return Match_Success;
5714 }
5715
5716 uint64_t TSFlags = getInstDesc(Inst.getOpcode()).TSFlags;
5717 if ((TSFlags & MipsII::HasFCCRegOperand) &&
5718 (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() != Mips::FCC0) && !hasEightFccRegisters())
5719 return Match_NoFCCRegisterForCurrentISA;
5720
5721 return Match_Success;
5722
5723}
5724
5725static SMLoc RefineErrorLoc(const SMLoc Loc, const OperandVector &Operands,
5726 uint64_t ErrorInfo) {
5727 if (ErrorInfo != ~0ULL && ErrorInfo < Operands.size()) {
5728 SMLoc ErrorLoc = Operands[ErrorInfo]->getStartLoc();
5729 if (ErrorLoc == SMLoc())
5730 return Loc;
5731 return ErrorLoc;
5732 }
5733 return Loc;
5734}
5735
5736bool MipsAsmParser::MatchAndEmitInstruction(SMLoc IDLoc, unsigned &Opcode,
5737 OperandVector &Operands,
5738 MCStreamer &Out,
5739 uint64_t &ErrorInfo,
5740 bool MatchingInlineAsm) {
5741 MCInst Inst;
5742 unsigned MatchResult =
5743 MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, ErrorInfo, MatchingInlineAsm);
5744
5745 switch (MatchResult) {
5746 case Match_Success:
5747 if (processInstruction(Inst, IDLoc, Out, STI))
5748 return true;
5749 return false;
5750 case Match_MissingFeature:
5751 Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires a CPU feature not currently enabled");
5752 return true;
5753 case Match_InvalidOperand: {
5754 SMLoc ErrorLoc = IDLoc;
5755 if (ErrorInfo != ~0ULL) {
5756 if (ErrorInfo >= Operands.size())
5757 return Error(IDLoc, "too few operands for instruction");
5758
5759 ErrorLoc = Operands[ErrorInfo]->getStartLoc();
5760 if (ErrorLoc == SMLoc())
5761 ErrorLoc = IDLoc;
5762 }
5763
5764 return Error(ErrorLoc, "invalid operand for instruction");
5765 }
5766 case Match_NonZeroOperandForSync:
5767 return Error(IDLoc,
5768 "s-type must be zero or unspecified for pre-MIPS32 ISAs");
5769 case Match_NonZeroOperandForMTCX:
5770 return Error(IDLoc, "selector must be zero for pre-MIPS32 ISAs / non-BERI CPUs");
5771 case Match_MnemonicFail:
5772 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid instruction");
5773 case Match_RequiresDifferentSrcAndDst:
5774 return Error(IDLoc, "source and destination must be different");
5775 case Match_RequiresDifferentOperands:
5776 return Error(IDLoc, "registers must be different");
5777 case Match_RequiresNoZeroRegister:
5778 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid operand ($zero) for instruction");
5779 case Match_RequiresSameSrcAndDst:
5780 return Error(IDLoc, "source and destination must match");
5781 case Match_NoFCCRegisterForCurrentISA:
5782 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5783 "non-zero fcc register doesn't exist in current ISA level");
5784 case Match_Immz:
5785 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo), "expected '0'");
5786 case Match_UImm1_0:
5787 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5788 "expected 1-bit unsigned immediate");
5789 case Match_UImm2_0:
5790 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5791 "expected 2-bit unsigned immediate");
5792 case Match_UImm2_1:
5793 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5794 "expected immediate in range 1 .. 4");
5795 case Match_UImm3_0:
5796 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5797 "expected 3-bit unsigned immediate");
5798 case Match_UImm4_0:
5799 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5800 "expected 4-bit unsigned immediate");
5801 case Match_SImm4_0:
5802 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5803 "expected 4-bit signed immediate");
5804 case Match_UImm5_0:
5805 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5806 "expected 5-bit unsigned immediate");
5807 case Match_SImm5_0:
5808 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5809 "expected 5-bit signed immediate");
5810 case Match_UImm5_1:
5811 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5812 "expected immediate in range 1 .. 32");
5813 case Match_UImm5_32:
5814 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5815 "expected immediate in range 32 .. 63");
5816 case Match_UImm5_33:
5817 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5818 "expected immediate in range 33 .. 64");
5819 case Match_UImm5_0_Report_UImm6:
5820 // This is used on UImm5 operands that have a corresponding UImm5_32
5821 // operand to avoid confusing the user.
5822 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5823 "expected 6-bit unsigned immediate");
5824 case Match_UImm5_Lsl2:
5825 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5826 "expected both 7-bit unsigned immediate and multiple of 4");
5827 case Match_UImmRange2_64:
5828 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5829 "expected immediate in range 2 .. 64");
5830 case Match_UImm6_0:
5831 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5832 "expected 6-bit unsigned immediate");
5833 case Match_UImm6_Lsl2:
5834 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5835 "expected both 8-bit unsigned immediate and multiple of 4");
5836 case Match_SImm6_0:
5837 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5838 "expected 6-bit signed immediate");
5839 case Match_UImm7_0:
5840 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5841 "expected 7-bit unsigned immediate");
5842 case Match_UImm7_N1:
5843 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5844 "expected immediate in range -1 .. 126");
5845 case Match_SImm7_Lsl2:
5846 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5847 "expected both 9-bit signed immediate and multiple of 4");
5848 case Match_SImm8_Lsl0:
5849 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5850 "expected 8-bit signed immediate");
5851 case Match_SImm8_Lsl1:
5852 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5853 "expected both 9-bit signed immediate and multiple of 2");
5854 case Match_SImm8_Lsl2:
5855 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5856 "expected both 10-bit signed immediate and multiple of 4");
5857 case Match_SImm8_Lsl3:
5858 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5859 "expected both 11-bit signed immediate and multiple of 8");
5860 case Match_UImm8_0:
5861 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5862 "expected 8-bit unsigned immediate");
5863 case Match_UImm10_0:
5864 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5865 "expected 10-bit unsigned immediate");
5866 case Match_UImm11_Lsl0:
5867 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5868 "expected 11-bit unsigned immediate");
5869 case Match_SImm10_0:
5870 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5871 "expected 10-bit signed immediate");
5872 case Match_SImm11_0:
5873 case Match_SImm11_Lsl0:
5874 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5875 "expected 11-bit signed immediate");
5876 case Match_SImm11_Lsl4:
5877 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5878 "expected both 15-bit signed immediate and multiple of 16");
5879 case Match_UImm16:
5880 case Match_UImm16_Relaxed:
5881 case Match_UImm16_AltRelaxed:
5882 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5883 "expected 16-bit unsigned immediate");
5884 case Match_SImm16:
5885 case Match_SImm16_Relaxed:
5886 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5887 "expected 16-bit signed immediate");
5888 case Match_SImm16_Lsl4:
5889 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5890 "expected both 20-bit signed immediate and multiple of 16");
5891 case Match_SImm19_Lsl2:
5892 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5893 "expected both 19-bit signed immediate and multiple of 4");
5894 case Match_UImm20_0:
5895 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5896 "expected 20-bit unsigned immediate");
5897 case Match_UImm26_0:
5898 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5899 "expected 26-bit unsigned immediate");
5900 case Match_SImm32:
5901 case Match_SImm32_Relaxed:
5902 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5903 "expected 32-bit signed immediate");
5904 case Match_UImm32_Coerced:
5905 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5906 "expected 32-bit immediate");
5907 case Match_MemSImm9:
5908 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5909 "expected memory with 9-bit signed offset");
5910 case Match_MemSImm10:
5911 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5912 "expected memory with 10-bit signed offset");
5913 case Match_MemSImm10Lsl1:
5914 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5915 "expected memory with 11-bit signed offset and multiple of 2");
5916 case Match_MemSImm10Lsl2:
5917 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5918 "expected memory with 12-bit signed offset and multiple of 4");
5919 case Match_MemSImm10Lsl3:
5920 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5921 "expected memory with 13-bit signed offset and multiple of 8");
5922 case Match_MemSImm11:
5923 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5924 "expected memory with 11-bit signed offset");
5925 case Match_MemSImm12:
5926 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5927 "expected memory with 12-bit signed offset");
5928 case Match_MemSImm16:
5929 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5930 "expected memory with 16-bit signed offset");
5931 case Match_CheriAsmReg:
5932 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5933 "expected general-purpose CHERI register operand or $cnull");
5934 case Match_CheriAsmReg0IsDDC:
5935 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5936 "expected general-purpose CHERI register operand or $ddc");
5937 case Match_MemSImmPtr:
5938 return Error(RefineErrorLoc(IDLoc, Operands, ErrorInfo),
5939 "expected memory with 32-bit signed offset");
5940 case Match_RequiresPosSizeRange0_32: {
5941 SMLoc ErrorStart = Operands[3]->getStartLoc();
5942 SMLoc ErrorEnd = Operands[4]->getEndLoc();
5943 return Error(ErrorStart, "size plus position are not in the range 0 .. 32",
5944 SMRange(ErrorStart, ErrorEnd));
5945 }
5946 case Match_RequiresPosSizeUImm6: {
5947 SMLoc ErrorStart = Operands[3]->getStartLoc();
5948 SMLoc ErrorEnd = Operands[4]->getEndLoc();
5949 return Error(ErrorStart, "size plus position are not in the range 1 .. 63",
5950 SMRange(ErrorStart, ErrorEnd));
5951 }
5952 case Match_RequiresPosSizeRange33_64: {
5953 SMLoc ErrorStart = Operands[3]->getStartLoc();
5954 SMLoc ErrorEnd = Operands[4]->getEndLoc();
5955 return Error(ErrorStart, "size plus position are not in the range 33 .. 64",
5956 SMRange(ErrorStart, ErrorEnd));
5957 }
5958 }
5959
5960 llvm_unreachable("Implement any new match types added!");
5961}
5962
5963void MipsAsmParser::warnIfRegIndexIsAT(unsigned RegIndex, SMLoc Loc) {
5964 if (RegIndex != 0 && AssemblerOptions.back()->getATRegIndex() == RegIndex)
5965 Warning(Loc, "used $at (currently $" + Twine(RegIndex) +
5966 ") without \".set noat\"");
5967}
5968
5969void MipsAsmParser::warnIfNoMacro(SMLoc Loc) {
5970 if (!AssemblerOptions.back()->isMacro())
5971 Warning(Loc, "macro instruction expanded into multiple instructions");
5972}
5973
5974void MipsAsmParser::ConvertXWPOperands(MCInst &Inst,
5975 const OperandVector &Operands) {
5976 assert(
5977 (Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::LWP_MM || Inst.getOpcode() == Mips::SWP_MM) &&
5978 "Unexpected instruction!");
5979 ((MipsOperand &)*Operands[1]).addGPR32ZeroAsmRegOperands(Inst, 1);
5980 int NextReg = nextReg(((MipsOperand &)*Operands[1]).getGPR32Reg());
5981 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(NextReg));
5982 ((MipsOperand &)*Operands[2]).addMemOperands(Inst, 2);
5983}

5985void
5986MipsAsmParser::printWarningWithFixIt(const Twine &Msg, const Twine &FixMsg,
5987 SMRange Range, bool ShowColors) {
5988 getSourceManager().PrintMessage(Range.Start, SourceMgr::DK_Warning, Msg,
5989 Range, SMFixIt(Range, FixMsg),
5990 ShowColors);
5991}
5992
5993int MipsAsmParser::matchCPURegisterName(StringRef Name) {
5994 int CC;
5995
5996 CC = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
5997 .Case("zero", 0)
5998 .Cases("at", "AT", 1)
5999 .Case("a0", 4)
6000 .Case("a1", 5)
6001 .Case("a2", 6)
6002 .Case("a3", 7)
6003 .Case("v0", 2)
6004 .Case("v1", 3)
6005 .Case("s0", 16)
6006 .Case("s1", 17)
6007 .Case("s2", 18)
6008 .Case("s3", 19)
6009 .Case("s4", 20)
6010 .Case("s5", 21)
6011 .Case("s6", 22)
6012 .Case("s7", 23)
6013 .Case("k0", 26)
6014 .Case("k1", 27)
6015 .Case("gp", 28)
6016 .Case("sp", 29)
6017 .Case("fp", 30)
6018 .Case("s8", 30)
6019 .Case("ra", 31)
6020 .Case("t0", 8)
6021 .Case("t1", 9)
6022 .Case("t2", 10)
6023 .Case("t3", 11)
6024 .Case("t4", 12)
6025 .Case("t5", 13)
6026 .Case("t6", 14)
6027 .Case("t7", 15)
6028 .Case("t8", 24)
6029 .Case("t9", 25)
6030 .Default(-1);
6031
6032 if (!(isABI_N32() || isABI_N64()))
6033 return CC;
6034
6035 if (12 <= CC && CC <= 15) {
6036 // Name is one of t4-t7
6037 AsmToken RegTok = getLexer().peekTok();
6038 SMRange RegRange = RegTok.getLocRange();
6039
6040 StringRef FixedName = StringSwitch<StringRef>(Name)
6041 .Case("t4", "t0")
6042 .Case("t5", "t1")
6043 .Case("t6", "t2")
6044 .Case("t7", "t3")
6045 .Default("");
6046 assert(FixedName != "" && "Register name is not one of t4-t7.");
6047
6048 printWarningWithFixIt("register names $t4-$t7 are only available in O32.",
6049 "Did you mean $" + FixedName + "?", RegRange);
6050 }
6051
6052 // Although SGI documentation just cuts out t0-t3 for n32/n64,
6053 // GNU pushes the values of t0-t3 to override the o32/o64 values for t4-t7
6054 // We are supporting both cases, so for t0-t3 we'll just push them to t4-t7.
6055 if (8 <= CC && CC <= 11)
6056 CC += 4;
6057
6058 if (CC == -1)
6059 CC = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
6060 .Case("a4", 8)
6061 .Case("a5", 9)
6062 .Case("a6", 10)
6063 .Case("a7", 11)
6064 .Case("kt0", 26)
6065 .Case("kt1", 27)
6066 .Default(-1);
6067
6068 return CC;
6069}
6070
6071int MipsAsmParser::matchHWRegsRegisterName(StringRef Name) {
6072 int CC;
6073
6074 CC = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
6075 .Case("hwr_cpunum", 0)
6076 .Case("hwr_synci_step", 1)
6077 .Case("hwr_cc", 2)
6078 .Case("hwr_ccres", 3)
6079 .Case("hwr_ulr", 29)
6080 .Default(-1);
6081
6082 return CC;
6083}
6084
6085int MipsAsmParser::matchFPURegisterName(StringRef Name) {
6086 if (Name[0] == 'f') {
6087 StringRef NumString = Name.substr(1);
6088 unsigned IntVal;
6089 if (NumString.getAsInteger(10, IntVal))
6090 return -1; // This is not an integer.
6091 if (IntVal > 31) // Maximum index for fpu register.
6092 return -1;
6093 return IntVal;
6094 }
6095 return -1;
6096}
6097
6098// Check whether this instruction accepts the given spelling for Register 0
6099// Some instructions (cfromptr + loads/stores, clc, cld) accept $c0 and $ddc
6100// for references to DDC but in other instructions we would like to have $c0
6101// be a NULL register (e.g. cincoffset)
6102// TODO: would be nice if we could generate these checks from tablegen (0 == $ddc vs 0 == NULL)
6103static bool isCRegZeroDDC(const OperandVector &Operands,
6104 StringRef RegSpelling) {
6105 if (Operands.empty())
6106 return false;
6107 const auto& FirstOp = Operands[0];
6108 if (!FirstOp->isToken()) {
6109 LLVM_DEBUG(
6110 dbgs() << "Access to $c0 not allowed since mnemonic is not known\n");
6111 return false;
6112 }
6113 MipsOperand* MipsOp = static_cast<MipsOperand*>(FirstOp.get());
6114 StringRef Mnemonic = MipsOp->getToken();
6115 size_t OperandIndex = Operands.size();
6116 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Checking if " << Mnemonic << " accepts register $"
6117 << RegSpelling << " as operand " << OperandIndex << ": ");
6118 assert(RegSpelling == "c0" || RegSpelling == "ddc" || RegSpelling == "cnull");
6119 // TODO: can I somehow get this information from the tablegen'd code?
6120 size_t AllowedIndex =
6121 StringSwitch<size_t>(Mnemonic)
6122 .Cases("clc", "clb", "clbu", "clh", "clhu", "clw", "clwu", "cld", 5)
6123 .Cases("csc", "csb", "csh", "csw", "csd", 5)
6124 .Cases("clcbi", "cscbi", 4)
6125 .Cases("cllc", "cllb", "cllbu", "cllh", "cllhu", "cllw", "cllwu",
6126 "clld", 2)
6127 .Cases("cscc", "cscb", "csch", "cscw", "cscd", 3)
6128 .Cases("cfromptr", "cbuildcap", "ctestsubset", 2)
6129 .Case("ctoptr", 3) // XXXAR: inconsisten with the insns above
6130 .Default(std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max());
6131 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (OperandIndex == AllowedIndex ? "true" : "false")
6132 << " ");
6133 LLVM_DEBUG(for (auto &&X
6134 : enumerate(Operands)) {
6135 dbgs() << " Op" << X.index() << "=" << *(X.value());
6136 });
6137 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n");
6138
6139 return OperandIndex == AllowedIndex;
6140}
6141
6142int MipsAsmParser::matchCheriRegisterName(StringRef Name,
6143 const OperandVector &Operands) {
6144 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6145
6146 int CC = -1;
6147 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "DECODING '" << Name << "' (ABI.IsCheriPureCap()="
6148 << ABI.IsCheriPureCap() << ")\n");
6149 CC = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
6150 .Case("cbp", ABI.GetBasePtr())
6151 .Case("cfp", ABI.GetFramePtr())
6152 .Case("cgp", ABI.GetGlobalCapability())
6153 .Case("cra", ABI.GetReturnAddress())
6154 .Case("csp", ABI.GetStackPtr())
6155 .Case("ddc", ABI.GetDefaultDataCapability())
6156 .Default(-1);
6157 if (!ABI.IsCheriPureCap() && CC != -1) {
6158 // symbolic capability register names other than $ddc are not available
6159 // when targeting hybrid mode.
6160 if ((unsigned)CC != ABI.GetDefaultDataCapability()) {
6161 ErrorIfNotPending(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
6162 "Register name $" + Name +
6163 " can only be used in the pure-capability ABI");
6164 return -1;
6165 }
6166 }
6167
6168 if (CC == -1) {
6169 if (Name[0] == 'c') {
6170 if (Name == "cnull") {
6171 CC = Mips::CNULL;
6172 } else {
6173 StringRef NumString = Name.substr(1);
6174 int IntVal;
6175 if (NumString.getAsInteger(10, IntVal))
6176 return -1; // This is not an integer.
6177 if (IntVal < 0 || IntVal > 31) // Maximum index for CHERI register.
6178 return -1;
6179 if (IntVal == 0)
6180 CC = 0; // $c0 is special -> handled further down
6181 else
6182 CC = Mips::C1 + IntVal - 1;
6183 }
6184 } else {
6185 int InvalidReg = StringSwitch<int>(Name)
6186 .Case("kr1c", 27)
6187 .Case("kr2c", 28)
6188 .Case("kcc", 29)
6189 .Case("kdc", 30)
6190 .Case("epcc", 31)
6191 .Default(0);
6192 if (InvalidReg) {
6193 ErrorIfNotPending(
6194 Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
6195 "Register $" + Name +
6196 " is no longer a general-purpose CHERI register. If you want "
6197 "to access the special register use c{get,set}" +
6198 Name + " instead. If you really want to access $c" +
6199 Twine(InvalidReg) +
6200 " (which is ABI-reserved for kernel use and may be clobbered "
6201 "at any time), use that instead.",
6202 Parser.getTok().getLocRange());
6203 return -1;
6204 }
6205 CC = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
6206 .Case("ddc", Mips::DDC)
6207 .Case("idc", Mips::C26)
6208 .Default(-1);
6209 }
6210 }
6211 if (CC == 0) {
6212 // special handling for register zero (some instructions treat it as NULL
6213 // and other use it for $ddc)
6214 bool RegZeroIsDDC = isCRegZeroDDC(Operands, Name);
6215 if (Name == "c0") {
6216 if (!RegZeroIsDDC) {
6217 StringRef ErrMsg =
6218 "register name $c0 is invalid as this operand. It will no longer "
6219 "refer to $ddc but instead be NULL. If this is what you want use "
6220 "$cnull, otherwise use CGetDefault/CSetDefault to manipulate $ddc.";
6221 if (CheriStrictC0) {
6222 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), ErrMsg, Parser.getTok().getLocRange());
6223 return -2;
6224 } else {
6225 Warning(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), ErrMsg);
6226 return Mips::CNULL;
6227 }
6228 }
6229 // Otherwise $c0 means $ddc so just print a deprecation warning
6230 Warning(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
6231 "register name $c0 is deprecated. Use $ddc instead.");
6232 return Mips::DDC;
6233 }
6234 errs() << "REGISTER NAME " << Name << "not handled?\n";
6235 llvm_unreachable("Bad register name?");
6236 }
6237 auto ABIReservedReg = [&]() {
6238 if (AreCheriSysRegsAccessible)
6239 return CC;
6240 Warning(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
6241 "Registers $c27 to $c31 are ABI-reserved for kernel use and may be "
6242 "clobbered at any time. If you are writing kernel code and really "
6243 "meant to access $" +
6244 Name +
6245 " you can use "
6246 "`.set cheri_sysregs_accessible` to silence this warning.");
6247 return CC;
6248 };
6249 assert(CC != 0);
6250 switch (CC) {
6251 case Mips::C27:
6252 return ABIReservedReg();
6253 case Mips::C28:
6254 return ABIReservedReg();
6255 case Mips::C29:
6256 return ABIReservedReg();
6257 case Mips::C30:
6258 return ABIReservedReg();
6259 case Mips::C31:
6260 return ABIReservedReg();
6261 default:
6262 break;
6263 }
6264 return CC;
6265}
6266
6267int MipsAsmParser::matchCheriHWRegsRegisterName(StringRef Name) {
6268 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "matchCheriHWRegsRegisterName(" << Name << ")\n");
6269 if (!Name.startswith("chwr_"))
6270 return -1;
6271
6272 int Result = -1;
6273 for (int Reg = Mips::CAPHWR0; Reg <= Mips::CAPHWR31; Reg++) {
6274 StringRef RegName = MipsInstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg);
6275 if (RegName.startswith("chwr_") && Name == RegName) {
6276 Result = Reg - Mips::CAPHWR0;
6277 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "-> CheriHWReg " << Result << ")\n");
6278 break;
6279 }
6280 }
6281 return Result;
6282}
6283
6284
6285
6286int MipsAsmParser::matchFCCRegisterName(StringRef Name) {
6287 if (Name.startswith("fcc")) {
6288 StringRef NumString = Name.substr(3);
6289 unsigned IntVal;
6290 if (NumString.getAsInteger(10, IntVal))
6291 return -1; // This is not an integer.
6292 if (IntVal > 7) // There are only 8 fcc registers.
6293 return -1;
6294 return IntVal;
6295 }
6296 return -1;
6297}
6298
6299int MipsAsmParser::matchACRegisterName(StringRef Name) {
6300 if (Name.startswith("ac")) {
6301 StringRef NumString = Name.substr(2);
6302 unsigned IntVal;
6303 if (NumString.getAsInteger(10, IntVal))
6304 return -1; // This is not an integer.
6305 if (IntVal > 3) // There are only 3 acc registers.
6306 return -1;
6307 return IntVal;
6308 }
6309 return -1;
6310}

6312int MipsAsmParser::matchMSA128RegisterName(StringRef Name) {
6313 unsigned IntVal;
6314
6315 if (Name.front() != 'w' || Name.drop_front(1).getAsInteger(10, IntVal))
6316 return -1;
6317
6318 if (IntVal > 31)
6319 return -1;
6320
6321 return IntVal;
6322}
6323
6324int MipsAsmParser::matchMSA128CtrlRegisterName(StringRef Name) {
6325 int CC;
6326
6327 CC = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
6328 .Case("msair", 0)
6329 .Case("msacsr", 1)
6330 .Case("msaaccess", 2)
6331 .Case("msasave", 3)
6332 .Case("msamodify", 4)
6333 .Case("msarequest", 5)
6334 .Case("msamap", 6)
6335 .Case("msaunmap", 7)
6336 .Default(-1);
6337
6338 return CC;
6339}

6341bool MipsAsmParser::canUseATReg() {
6342 return AssemblerOptions.back()->getATRegIndex() != 0;
6343}
6344
6345unsigned MipsAsmParser::getATReg(SMLoc Loc) {
6346 unsigned ATIndex = AssemblerOptions.back()->getATRegIndex();
6347 if (ATIndex == 0) {
6348 reportParseError(Loc,
6349 "pseudo-instruction requires $at, which is not available");
6350 return 0;
6351 }
6352 unsigned AT = getReg(
6353 (isGP64bit()) ? Mips::GPR64RegClassID : Mips::GPR32RegClassID, ATIndex);
6354 return AT;
6355}
6356
6357unsigned MipsAsmParser::getReg(int RC, int RegNo) {
6358 return *(getContext().getRegisterInfo()->getRegClass(RC).begin() + RegNo);
6359}
6360
6361bool MipsAsmParser::parseOperand(OperandVector &Operands, StringRef Mnemonic) {
6362 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6363 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "parseOperand\n");
6364
6365 // Check if the current operand has a custom associated parser, if so, try to
6366 // custom parse the operand, or fallback to the general approach.
6367 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = MatchOperandParserImpl(Operands, Mnemonic);
6368 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success)
6369 return false;
6370 // If there wasn't a custom match, try the generic matcher below. Otherwise,
6371 // there was a match, but an error occurred, in which case, just return that
6372 // the operand parsing failed.
6373 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail)
6374 return true;
6375
6376 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. Generic Parser\n");
6377
6378 switch (getLexer().getKind()) {
6379 case AsmToken::Dollar: {
6380 // Parse the register.
6381 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6382
6383 // Almost all registers have been parsed by custom parsers. There is only
6384 // one exception to this. $zero (and it's alias $0) will reach this point
6385 // for div, divu, and similar instructions because it is not an operand
6386 // to the instruction definition but an explicit register. Special case
6387 // this situation for now.
6388 if (parseAnyRegister(Operands) != MatchOperand_NoMatch)
6389 return false;
6390
6391 // Maybe it is a symbol reference.
6392 StringRef Identifier;
6393 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(Identifier))
6394 return true;
6395
6396 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6397 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol("$" + Identifier);
6398 // Otherwise create a symbol reference.
6399 const MCExpr *Res =
6400 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext());
6401
6402 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateImm(Res, S, E, *this));
6403 return false;
6404 }
6405 default: {
6406 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. generic integer expression\n");
6407
6408 const MCExpr *Expr;
6409 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); // Start location of the operand.
6410 if (getParser().parseExpression(Expr))
6411 return true;
6412
6413 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6414
6415 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateImm(Expr, S, E, *this));
6416 return false;
6417 }
6418 } // switch(getLexer().getKind())
6419 return true;
6420}
6421
6422bool MipsAsmParser::isEvaluated(const MCExpr *Expr) {
6423 switch (Expr->getKind()) {
6424 case MCExpr::Constant:
6425 return true;
6426 case MCExpr::SymbolRef:
6427 return (cast<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Expr)->getKind() != MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None);
6428 case MCExpr::Binary: {
6429 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast<MCBinaryExpr>(Expr);
6430 if (!isEvaluated(BE->getLHS()))
6431 return false;
6432 return isEvaluated(BE->getRHS());
6433 }
6434 case MCExpr::Unary:
6435 return isEvaluated(cast<MCUnaryExpr>(Expr)->getSubExpr());
6436 case MCExpr::Target:
6437 return true;
6438 }
6439 return false;
6440}
6441
6442bool MipsAsmParser::ParseRegister(unsigned &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc,
6443 SMLoc &EndLoc) {
6444 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 1> Operands;
6445 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(Operands);
6446 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success) {
6447 assert(Operands.size() == 1);
6448 MipsOperand &Operand = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands.front());
6449 StartLoc = Operand.getStartLoc();
6450 EndLoc = Operand.getEndLoc();
6451
6452 // AFAIK, we only support numeric registers and named GPR's in CFI
6453 // directives.
6454 // Don't worry about eating tokens before failing. Using an unrecognised
6455 // register is a parse error.
6456 RegNo = -1;
6457 if (Operand.isGPRAsmReg()) {
6458 // Resolve to GPR32 or GPR64 appropriately.
6459 RegNo = isGP64bit() ? Operand.getGPR64Reg() : Operand.getGPR32Reg();
6460 } else if (Operand.isCheriAsmReg()) {
6461 RegNo = Operand.getCheriReg();
6462 } else {
6463 llvm_unreachable("Got non-GPR register in .cfi directive!");
6464 }
6465
6466 return (RegNo == (unsigned)-1);
6467 }
6468
6469 assert(Operands.size() == 0);
6470 return (RegNo == (unsigned)-1);
6471}
6472
6473bool MipsAsmParser::parseMemOffset(const MCExpr *&Res, bool isParenExpr) {
6474 SMLoc S;
6475
6476 if (isParenExpr)
6477 return getParser().parseParenExprOfDepth(0, Res, S);
6478 return getParser().parseExpression(Res);
6479}
6480
6481OperandMatchResultTy
6482MipsAsmParser::parseMemOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
6483 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6484 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "parseMemOperand\n");
6485 const MCExpr *IdVal = nullptr;
6486 SMLoc S;
6487 bool isParenExpr = false;
6488 OperandMatchResultTy Res = MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6489 // First operand is the offset.
6490 S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6491
6492 if (getLexer().getKind() == AsmToken::LParen) {
6493 Parser.Lex();
6494 isParenExpr = true;
6495 }
6496
6497 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Dollar) {
6498 if (parseMemOffset(IdVal, isParenExpr))
6499 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6500
6501 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok(); // Get the next token.
6502 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::LParen)) {
6503 MipsOperand &Mnemonic = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Operands[0]);
6504 if (Mnemonic.getToken() == "la" || Mnemonic.getToken() == "dla") {
6505 SMLoc E =
6506 SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6507 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateImm(IdVal, S, E, *this));
6508 return MatchOperand_Success;
6509 }
6510 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6511 SMLoc E =
6512 SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6513
6514 // Zero register assumed, add a memory operand with ZERO as its base.
6515 // "Base" will be managed by k_Memory.
6516 auto Base = MipsOperand::createGPRReg(
6517 0, "0", getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S, E, *this);
6518 Operands.push_back(
6519 MipsOperand::CreateMem(std::move(Base), IdVal, S, E, *this));
6520 return MatchOperand_Success;
6521 }
6522 MCBinaryExpr::Opcode Opcode;
6523 // GAS and LLVM treat comparison operators different. GAS will generate -1
6524 // or 0, while LLVM will generate 0 or 1. Since a comparsion operator is
6525 // highly unlikely to be found in a memory offset expression, we don't
6526 // handle them.
6527 switch (Tok.getKind()) {
6528 case AsmToken::Plus:
6529 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Add;
6530 Parser.Lex();
6531 break;
6532 case AsmToken::Minus:
6533 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Sub;
6534 Parser.Lex();
6535 break;
6536 case AsmToken::Star:
6537 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Mul;
6538 Parser.Lex();
6539 break;
6540 case AsmToken::Pipe:
6541 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Or;
6542 Parser.Lex();
6543 break;
6544 case AsmToken::Amp:
6545 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::And;
6546 Parser.Lex();
6547 break;
6548 case AsmToken::LessLess:
6549 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Shl;
6550 Parser.Lex();
6551 break;
6552 case AsmToken::GreaterGreater:
6553 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::LShr;
6554 Parser.Lex();
6555 break;
6556 case AsmToken::Caret:
6557 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Xor;
6558 Parser.Lex();
6559 break;
6560 case AsmToken::Slash:
6561 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Div;
6562 Parser.Lex();
6563 break;
6564 case AsmToken::Percent:
6565 Opcode = MCBinaryExpr::Mod;
6566 Parser.Lex();
6567 break;
6568 default:
6569 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'(' or expression expected");
6570 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6571 }
6572 const MCExpr * NextExpr;
6573 if (getParser().parseExpression(NextExpr))
6574 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6575 IdVal = MCBinaryExpr::create(Opcode, IdVal, NextExpr, getContext());
6576 }
6577
6578 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '(' token.
6579 }
6580
6581 Res = parseAnyRegister(Operands);
6582 if (Res != MatchOperand_Success)
6583 return Res;
6584
6585 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RParen)) {
6586 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "')' expected");
6587 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6588 }
6589
6590 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6591
6592 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the ')' token.
6593
6594 if (!IdVal)
6595 IdVal = MCConstantExpr::create(0, getContext());
6596
6597 // Replace the register operand with the memory operand.
6598 std::unique_ptr<MipsOperand> op(
6599 static_cast<MipsOperand *>(Operands.back().release()));
6600 // Remove the register from the operands.
6601 // "op" will be managed by k_Memory.
6602 Operands.pop_back();
6603 // Add the memory operand.
6604 if (const MCBinaryExpr *BE = dyn_cast<MCBinaryExpr>(IdVal)) {
6605 int64_t Imm;
6606 if (IdVal->evaluateAsAbsolute(Imm, getStreamer()))
6607 IdVal = MCConstantExpr::create(Imm, getContext());
6608 else if (BE->getLHS()->getKind() != MCExpr::SymbolRef)
6609 IdVal = MCBinaryExpr::create(BE->getOpcode(), BE->getRHS(), BE->getLHS(),
6610 getContext());
6611 }
6612
6613 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateMem(std::move(op), IdVal, S, E, *this));
6614 return MatchOperand_Success;
6615}
6616
6617bool MipsAsmParser::searchSymbolAlias(OperandVector &Operands) {
6618 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6619 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().lookupSymbol(Parser.getTok().getIdentifier());
6620 if (!Sym)
6621 return false;
6622
6623 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6624 if (Sym->isVariable()) {
6625 const MCExpr *Expr = Sym->getVariableValue();
6626 if (Expr->getKind() == MCExpr::SymbolRef) {
6627 const MCSymbolRefExpr *Ref = static_cast<const MCSymbolRefExpr *>(Expr);
6628 StringRef DefSymbol = Ref->getSymbol().getName();
6629 if (DefSymbol.startswith("$")) {
6630 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy =
6631 matchAnyRegisterNameWithoutDollar(Operands, DefSymbol.substr(1), S);
6632 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success) {
6633 Parser.Lex();
6634 return true;
6635 }
6636 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail)
6637 llvm_unreachable("Should never ParseFail");
6638 }
6639 }
6640 } else if (Sym->isUnset()) {
6641 // If symbol is unset, it might be created in the `parseSetAssignment`
6642 // routine as an alias for a numeric register name.
6643 // Lookup in the aliases list.
6644 auto Entry = RegisterSets.find(Sym->getName());
6645 if (Entry != RegisterSets.end()) {
6646 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy =
6647 matchAnyRegisterWithoutDollar(Operands, Entry->getValue(), S);
6648 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success) {
6649 Parser.Lex();
6650 return true;
6651 }
6652 }
6653 }
6654
6655 return false;
6656}
6657
6658OperandMatchResultTy
6659MipsAsmParser::matchAnyRegisterNameWithoutDollar(OperandVector &Operands,
6660 StringRef Identifier,
6661 SMLoc S) {
6662 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "matchAnyRegisterNameWithoutDollar\n");
6663 int Index = matchCPURegisterName(Identifier);
6664 if (Index != -1) {
6665 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createGPRReg(
6666 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6667 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6668 return MatchOperand_Success;
6669 }
6670
6671 Index = matchHWRegsRegisterName(Identifier);
6672 if (Index != -1) {
6673 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createHWRegsReg(
6674 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6675 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6676 return MatchOperand_Success;
6677 }
6678
6679 Index = matchFPURegisterName(Identifier);
6680 if (Index != -1) {
6681 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createFGRReg(
6682 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6683 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6684 return MatchOperand_Success;
6685 }
6686
6687 Index = matchFCCRegisterName(Identifier);
6688 if (Index != -1) {
6689 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createFCCReg(
6690 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6691 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6692 return MatchOperand_Success;
6693 }
6694
6695 Index = matchACRegisterName(Identifier);
6696 if (Index != -1) {
6697 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createACCReg(
6698 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6699 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6700 return MatchOperand_Success;
6701 }
6702
6703 Index = matchMSA128RegisterName(Identifier);
6704 if (Index != -1) {
6705 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createMSA128Reg(
6706 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6707 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6708 return MatchOperand_Success;
6709 }
6710
6711 Index = matchMSA128CtrlRegisterName(Identifier);
6712 if (Index != -1) {
6713 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createMSACtrlReg(
6714 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6715 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6716 return MatchOperand_Success;
6717 }
6718
6719 Index = matchCheriRegisterName(Identifier, Operands);
6720 if (Index != -1) {
6721 if (Index == -2)
6722 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6723 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateCheriReg(
6724 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S, getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6725 return MatchOperand_Success;
6726 }
6727
6728 Index = matchCheriHWRegsRegisterName(Identifier);
6729 if (Index != -1) {
6730 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateCheriHWRegsReg(
6731 Index, Identifier, getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6732 getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6733 return MatchOperand_Success;
6734 }
6735
6736 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6737}
6738
6739OperandMatchResultTy
6740MipsAsmParser::matchAnyRegisterWithoutDollar(OperandVector &Operands,
6741 const AsmToken &Token, SMLoc S) {
6742 if (Token.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
6743 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. identifier\n");
6744 StringRef Identifier = Token.getIdentifier();
6745 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy =
6746 matchAnyRegisterNameWithoutDollar(Operands, Identifier, S);
6747 return ResTy;
6748 } else if (Token.is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
6749 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. integer\n");
6750 int64_t RegNum = Token.getIntVal();
6751 if (RegNum < 0 || RegNum > 31) {
6752 // Show the error, but treat invalid register
6753 // number as a normal one to continue parsing
6754 // and catch other possible errors.
6755 Error(getLexer().getLoc(), "invalid register number");
6756 }
6757 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::createNumericReg(
6758 RegNum, Token.getString(), getContext().getRegisterInfo(), S,
6759 Token.getLoc(), *this));
6760 return MatchOperand_Success;
6761 }
6762
6763 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Token.getKind() << "\n");
6764
6765 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6766}
6767
6768OperandMatchResultTy
6769MipsAsmParser::matchAnyRegisterWithoutDollar(OperandVector &Operands, SMLoc S) {
6770 auto Token = getLexer().peekTok(false);
6771 return matchAnyRegisterWithoutDollar(Operands, Token, S);
6772}
6773
6774OperandMatchResultTy
6775MipsAsmParser::parseAnyRegister(OperandVector &Operands) {
6776 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6777 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "parseAnyRegister\n");
6778
6779 auto Token = Parser.getTok();
6780
6781 SMLoc S = Token.getLoc();
6782
6783 if (Token.isNot(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
6784 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. !$ -> try sym aliasing\n");
6785 if (Token.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
6786 if (searchSymbolAlias(Operands))
6787 return MatchOperand_Success;
6788 }
6789 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. !symalias -> NoMatch\n");
6790 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6791 }
6792 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ".. $\n");
6793
6794 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = matchAnyRegisterWithoutDollar(Operands, S);
6795 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success) {
6796 Parser.Lex(); // $
6797 Parser.Lex(); // identifier
6798 }
6799 return ResTy;
6800}
6801
6802OperandMatchResultTy
6803MipsAsmParser::parseJumpTarget(OperandVector &Operands) {
6804 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6805 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "parseJumpTarget\n");
6806
6807 SMLoc S = getLexer().getLoc();
6808
6809 // Registers are a valid target and have priority over symbols.
6810 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(Operands);
6811 if (ResTy != MatchOperand_NoMatch)
6812 return ResTy;
6813
6814 // Integers and expressions are acceptable
6815 const MCExpr *Expr = nullptr;
6816 if (Parser.parseExpression(Expr)) {
6817 // We have no way of knowing if a symbol was consumed so we must ParseFail
6818 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6819 }
6820 Operands.push_back(
6821 MipsOperand::CreateImm(Expr, S, getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6822 return MatchOperand_Success;
6823}
6824
6825OperandMatchResultTy
6826MipsAsmParser::parseInvNum(OperandVector &Operands) {
6827 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6828 const MCExpr *IdVal;
6829 // If the first token is '$' we may have register operand. We have to reject
6830 // cases where it is not a register. Complicating the matter is that
6831 // register names are not reserved across all ABIs.
6832 // Peek past the dollar to see if it's a register name for this ABI.
6833 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6834 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
6835 return matchCPURegisterName(Parser.getLexer().peekTok().getString()) == -1
6836 ? MatchOperand_ParseFail
6837 : MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6838 }
6839 if (getParser().parseExpression(IdVal))
6840 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6841 const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(IdVal);
6842 if (!MCE)
6843 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6844 int64_t Val = MCE->getValue();
6845 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Parser.getTok().getLoc().getPointer() - 1);
6846 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateImm(
6847 MCConstantExpr::create(0 - Val, getContext()), S, E, *this));
6848 return MatchOperand_Success;
6849}
6850
6851OperandMatchResultTy
6852MipsAsmParser::parseRegisterList(OperandVector &Operands) {
6853 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6854 SmallVector<unsigned, 10> Regs;
6855 unsigned RegNo;
6856 unsigned PrevReg = Mips::NoRegister;
6857 bool RegRange = false;
6858 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 8> TmpOperands;
6859
6860 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar))
6861 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6862
6863 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6864 while (parseAnyRegister(TmpOperands) == MatchOperand_Success) {
6865 SMLoc E = getLexer().getLoc();
6866 MipsOperand &Reg = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*TmpOperands.back());
6867 RegNo = isGP64bit() ? Reg.getGPR64Reg() : Reg.getGPR32Reg();
6868 if (RegRange) {
6869 // Remove last register operand because registers from register range
6870 // should be inserted first.
6871 if ((isGP64bit() && RegNo == Mips::RA_64) ||
6872 (!isGP64bit() && RegNo == Mips::RA)) {
6873 Regs.push_back(RegNo);
6874 } else {
6875 unsigned TmpReg = PrevReg + 1;
6876 while (TmpReg <= RegNo) {
6877 if ((((TmpReg < Mips::S0) || (TmpReg > Mips::S7)) && !isGP64bit()) ||
6878 (((TmpReg < Mips::S0_64) || (TmpReg > Mips::S7_64)) &&
6879 isGP64bit())) {
6880 Error(E, "invalid register operand");
6881 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6882 }
6883
6884 PrevReg = TmpReg;
6885 Regs.push_back(TmpReg++);
6886 }
6887 }
6888
6889 RegRange = false;
6890 } else {
6891 if ((PrevReg == Mips::NoRegister) &&
6892 ((isGP64bit() && (RegNo != Mips::S0_64) && (RegNo != Mips::RA_64)) ||
6893 (!isGP64bit() && (RegNo != Mips::S0) && (RegNo != Mips::RA)))) {
6894 Error(E, "$16 or $31 expected");
6895 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6896 } else if (!(((RegNo == Mips::FP || RegNo == Mips::RA ||
6897 (RegNo >= Mips::S0 && RegNo <= Mips::S7)) &&
6898 !isGP64bit()) ||
6899 ((RegNo == Mips::FP_64 || RegNo == Mips::RA_64 ||
6900 (RegNo >= Mips::S0_64 && RegNo <= Mips::S7_64)) &&
6901 isGP64bit()))) {
6902 Error(E, "invalid register operand");
6903 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6904 } else if ((PrevReg != Mips::NoRegister) && (RegNo != PrevReg + 1) &&
6905 ((RegNo != Mips::FP && RegNo != Mips::RA && !isGP64bit()) ||
6906 (RegNo != Mips::FP_64 && RegNo != Mips::RA_64 &&
6907 isGP64bit()))) {
6908 Error(E, "consecutive register numbers expected");
6909 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6910 }
6911
6912 Regs.push_back(RegNo);
6913 }
6914
6915 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Minus))
6916 RegRange = true;
6917
6918 if (!Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Minus) &&
6919 !Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6920 Error(E, "',' or '-' expected");
6921 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6922 }
6923
6924 Lex(); // Consume comma or minus
6925 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar))
6926 break;
6927
6928 PrevReg = RegNo;
6929 }
6930
6931 SMLoc E = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
6932 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateRegList(Regs, S, E, *this));
6933 parseMemOperand(Operands);
6934 return MatchOperand_Success;
6935}
6936
6937/// Sometimes (i.e. load/stores) the operand may be followed immediately by
6938/// either this.
6939/// ::= '(', register, ')'
6940/// handle it before we iterate so we don't get tripped up by the lack of
6941/// a comma.
6942bool MipsAsmParser::parseParenSuffix(StringRef Name, OperandVector &Operands) {
6943 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6944 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LParen)) {
6945 Operands.push_back(
6946 MipsOperand::CreateToken("(", getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6947 Parser.Lex();
6948 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
6949 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6950 return ErrorIfNotPending(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
6951 }
6952 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RParen)) {
6953 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6954 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token, expected ')'");
6955 }
6956 Operands.push_back(
6957 MipsOperand::CreateToken(")", getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6958 Parser.Lex();
6959 }
6960 return false;
6961}
6962
6963/// Sometimes (i.e. in MSA) the operand may be followed immediately by
6964/// either one of these.
6965/// ::= '[', register, ']'
6966/// ::= '[', integer, ']'
6967/// handle it before we iterate so we don't get tripped up by the lack of
6968/// a comma.
6969bool MipsAsmParser::parseBracketSuffix(StringRef Name,
6970 OperandVector &Operands) {
6971 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6972 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LBrac)) {
6973 Operands.push_back(
6974 MipsOperand::CreateToken("[", getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6975 Parser.Lex();
6976 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
6977 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6978 return ErrorIfNotPending(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
6979 }
6980 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RBrac)) {
6981 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
6982 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token, expected ']'");
6983 }
6984 Operands.push_back(
6985 MipsOperand::CreateToken("]", getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
6986 Parser.Lex();
6987 }
6988 return false;
6989}
6990
6991static std::string MipsMnemonicSpellCheck(StringRef S, const FeatureBitset &FBS,
6992 unsigned VariantID = 0);
6993
6994bool MipsAsmParser::ParseInstruction(ParseInstructionInfo &Info, StringRef Name,
6995 SMLoc NameLoc, OperandVector &Operands) {
6996 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
6997 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ParseInstruction\n");
6998
6999 // We have reached first instruction, module directive are now forbidden.
7000 getTargetStreamer().forbidModuleDirective();
7001
7002 // Check if we have valid mnemonic
7003 if (!mnemonicIsValid(Name, 0)) {
7004 FeatureBitset FBS = ComputeAvailableFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits());
7005 std::string Suggestion = MipsMnemonicSpellCheck(Name, FBS);
7006 return Error(NameLoc, "unknown instruction" + Suggestion);
7007 }
7008 // First operand in MCInst is instruction mnemonic.
7009 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateToken(Name, NameLoc, *this));
7010
7011 // Read the remaining operands.
7012 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7013 // Read the first operand.
7014 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
7015 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7016 return ErrorIfNotPending(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
7017 }
7018 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LBrac) && parseBracketSuffix(Name, Operands))
7019 return true;
7020 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LParen) && parseParenSuffix(Name, Operands))
7021 return true;
7022
7023 // If this is a capability load / store, then we parse operands in the
7024 // following form:
7025 // $rt + offset($cb)
7026 // We have already parsed the $rt
7027 if (StringSwitch<bool>(Name).Case("clb", true).Case("clh", true)
7028 .Case("clbu", true).Case("clhu", true).Case("clwu", true)
7029 .Case("clw", true).Case("cld", true).Case("clc", true)
7030 .Case("csb", true).Case("csh", true)
7031 .Case("csw", true).Case("csd", true).Case("csc", true)
7032 .Case("cldc1", true).Case("clwc1", true).Case("csdc1", true)
7033 .Case("cswc1", true).Default(false)) {
7034 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
7035 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7036 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
7037 return Error(Loc,
7038 "expecting comma when parsing capability-relative address");
7039 }
7040 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
7041 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
7042 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7043 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
7044 return ErrorIfNotPending(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
7045 }
7046 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
7047 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7048 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
7049 return Error(Loc,
7050 "expecting offset when parsing capability-relative address");
7051 }
7052 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
7053 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
7054 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7055 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
7056 return ErrorIfNotPending(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
7057 }
7058 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::LParen)) {
7059 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7060 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
7061 return Error(Loc,
7062 "expecting capability register when parsing capability-relative address");
7063 }
7064 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateToken("(", getLexer().getLoc(),
7065 *this));
7066 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the left paren.
7067 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
7068 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7069 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
7070 return ErrorIfNotPending(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
7071 }
7072 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::RParen)) {
7073 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7074 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
7075 return Error(Loc,
7076 "expecting right parenthesis when parsing capability-relative address");
7077 }
7078 Operands.push_back(MipsOperand::CreateToken(")", getLexer().getLoc(), *this));
7079 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the right paren.
7080 }
7081 else while (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma)) {
7082 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
7083
7084 // Parse and remember the operand.
7085 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) {
7086 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7087 return ErrorIfNotPending(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
7088 }
7089 // Parse bracket and parenthesis suffixes before we iterate
7090 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LBrac)) {
7091 if (parseBracketSuffix(Name, Operands))
7092 return true;
7093 } else if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LParen) &&
7094 parseParenSuffix(Name, Operands))
7095 return true;
7096 }
7097 }
7098 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7099 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7100 return ErrorIfNotPending(Loc, "unexpected token in argument list");
7101 }
7102 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
7103 return false;
7104}
7105
7106// FIXME: Given that these have the same name, these should both be
7107// consistent on affecting the Parser.
7108bool MipsAsmParser::reportParseError(Twine ErrorMsg) {
7109 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7110 return Error(Loc, ErrorMsg);
7111}
7112
7113bool MipsAsmParser::reportParseError(SMLoc Loc, Twine ErrorMsg) {
7114 return Error(Loc, ErrorMsg);
7115}
7116
7117bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetNoAtDirective() {
7118 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7119 // Line should look like: ".set noat".
7120
7121 // Set the $at register to $0.
7122 AssemblerOptions.back()->setATRegIndex(0);
7123
7124 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "noat".
7125
7126 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7127 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7128 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7129 return false;
7130 }
7131
7132 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetNoAt();
7133 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
7134 return false;
7135}
7136
7137bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetAtDirective() {
7138 // Line can be: ".set at", which sets $at to $1
7139 // or ".set at=$reg", which sets $at to $reg.
7140 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7141 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "at".
7142
7143 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7144 // No register was specified, so we set $at to $1.
7145 AssemblerOptions.back()->setATRegIndex(1);
7146
7147 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetAt();
7148 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
7149 return false;
7150 }
7151
7152 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Equal)) {
7153 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected equals sign");
7154 return false;
7155 }
7156 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "=".
7157
7158 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
7159 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7160 reportParseError("no register specified");
7161 return false;
7162 } else {
7163 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected dollar sign '$'");
7164 return false;
7165 }
7166 }
7167 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "$".
7168
7169 // Find out what "reg" is.
7170 unsigned AtRegNo;
7171 const AsmToken &Reg = Parser.getTok();
7172 if (Reg.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
7173 AtRegNo = matchCPURegisterName(Reg.getIdentifier());
7174 } else if (Reg.is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
7175 AtRegNo = Reg.getIntVal();
7176 } else {
7177 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected identifier or integer");
7178 return false;
7179 }
7180
7181 // Check if $reg is a valid register. If it is, set $at to $reg.
7182 if (!AssemblerOptions.back()->setATRegIndex(AtRegNo)) {
7183 reportParseError("invalid register");
7184 return false;
7185 }
7186 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "reg".
7187
7188 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7189 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7190 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7191 return false;
7192 }
7193
7194 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetAtWithArg(AtRegNo);
7195
7196 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
7197 return false;
7198}
7199
7200bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetReorderDirective() {
7201 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();

7206 return false;

7212}

7333bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetFpDirective() {
7334 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7335 MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind FpAbiVal;
7336 // Line can be: .set fp=32
7337 // .set fp=xx
7338 // .set fp=64
7339 Parser.Lex(); // Eat fp token
7340 AsmToken Tok = Parser.getTok();
7341 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Equal)) {
7342 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected equals sign '='");
7343 return false;
7344 }
7345 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '=' token.
7346 Tok = Parser.getTok();
7347
7348 if (!parseFpABIValue(FpAbiVal, ".set"))
7349 return false;
7350
7351 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7352 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7353 return false;
7354 }
7355 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetFp(FpAbiVal);
7356 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
7357 return false;
7358}

7420
7421bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetNoCRCDirective() {
7422 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7423 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "nocrc".
7424
7425 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7426 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7427 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7428 return false;
7429 }
7430
7431 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureCRC, "crc");
7432
7433 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetNoCRC();
7434 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
7435 return false;
7436}
7437

7439 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7440 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "novirt".
7441
7442 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7443 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7444 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7445 return false;

7471
7472bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetPopDirective() {
7473 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7474 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7475
7476 Parser.Lex();
7477 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
7478 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7479
7480 // Always keep an element on the options "stack" to prevent the user
7481 // from changing the initial options. This is how we remember them.
7482 if (AssemblerOptions.size() == 2)
7483 return reportParseError(Loc, ".set pop with no .set push");
7484
7485 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
7486 AssemblerOptions.pop_back();
7487 setAvailableFeatures(
7488 ComputeAvailableFeatures(AssemblerOptions.back()->getFeatures()));
7489 STI.setFeatureBits(AssemblerOptions.back()->getFeatures());
7490
7491 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetPop();
7492 return false;
7493}
7494
7495bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetPushDirective() {
7496 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7497 Parser.Lex();
7498 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
7499 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7500
7501 // Create a copy of the current assembler options environment and push it.
7502 AssemblerOptions.push_back(
7503 llvm::make_unique<MipsAssemblerOptions>(AssemblerOptions.back().get()));
7504
7505 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetPush();
7506 return false;
7507}

7513 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7514

7516 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetSoftFloat();
7517 return false;
7518}

7520bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetHardFloatDirective() {
