7530
7531bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetAssignment() {
7532 StringRef Name;
7533 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7534
7535 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(Name))
7536 return reportParseError("expected identifier after .set");
7537
7538 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma))
7539 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected comma");
7540 Lex(); // Eat comma
7541
7542 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Dollar) &&
7543 getLexer().peekTok().is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
7544 // Parse assignment of a numeric register:
7545 // .set r1,$1
7546 Parser.Lex(); // Eat $.
7547 RegisterSets[Name] = Parser.getTok();
7548 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier.
7549 getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
7550 return false;
7551 }
7552
7553 MCSymbol *Sym;
7554 const MCExpr *Value;
7555 if (MCParserUtils::parseAssignmentExpression(Name, /* allow_redef */ true,
7556 Parser, Sym, Value))
7557 return true;
7558 Sym->setVariableValue(Value);
7559
7560 return false;
7561}
7562
7563bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetMips0Directive() {
7564 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7565 Parser.Lex();
7566 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
7567 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7568
7569 // Reset assembler options to their initial values.
7570 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
7571 setAvailableFeatures(
7572 ComputeAvailableFeatures(AssemblerOptions.front()->getFeatures()));
7573 STI.setFeatureBits(AssemblerOptions.front()->getFeatures());
7574 AssemblerOptions.back()->setFeatures(AssemblerOptions.front()->getFeatures());
7575
7576 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips0();
7577 return false;
7578}
7579
7580bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetArchDirective() {
7581 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7582 Parser.Lex();
7583 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Equal))
7584 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected equals sign");
7585
7586 Parser.Lex();
7587 StringRef Arch;
7588 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(Arch))
7589 return reportParseError("expected arch identifier");
7590
7591 StringRef ArchFeatureName =
7592 StringSwitch<StringRef>(Arch)
7593 .Case("mips1", "mips1")
7594 .Case("mips2", "mips2")
7595 .Case("mips3", "mips3")
7596 .Case("mips4", "mips4")
7597 .Case("mips5", "mips5")
7598 .Case("mips32", "mips32")
7599 .Case("mips32r2", "mips32r2")
7600 .Case("mips32r3", "mips32r3")
7601 .Case("mips32r5", "mips32r5")
7602 .Case("mips32r6", "mips32r6")
7603 .Case("mips64", "mips64")
7604 .Case("mips64r2", "mips64r2")
7605 .Case("mips64r3", "mips64r3")
7606 .Case("mips64r5", "mips64r5")
7607 .Case("mips64r6", "mips64r6")
7608 .Case("octeon", "cnmips")
7609 .Case("beri", "beri") // BERI supports all of Mips4
7610 .Case("r4000", "mips3") // This is an implementation of Mips3.
7611 .Default("");
7612
7613 if (ArchFeatureName.empty())
7614 return reportParseError("unsupported architecture");
7615
7616 if (ArchFeatureName == "mips64r6" && inMicroMipsMode())
7617 return reportParseError("mips64r6 does not support microMIPS");
7618
7619 selectArch(ArchFeatureName);
7620 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetArch(Arch);
7621 return false;
7622}
7623
7624bool MipsAsmParser::parseSetFeature(uint64_t Feature) {
7625 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7626 Parser.Lex();
7627 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
7628 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7629
7630 switch (Feature) {
7631 default:
7632 llvm_unreachable("Unimplemented feature");
7633 case Mips::FeatureDSP:
7634 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureDSP, "dsp");
7635 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetDsp();
7636 break;
7637 case Mips::FeatureDSPR2:
7638 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureDSPR2, "dspr2");
7639 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetDspr2();
7640 break;
7641 case Mips::FeatureMicroMips:
7642 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureMicroMips, "micromips");
7643 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMicroMips();
7644 break;
7645 case Mips::FeatureMips1:
7646 selectArch("mips1");
7647 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips1();
7648 break;
7649 case Mips::FeatureMips2:
7650 selectArch("mips2");
7651 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips2();
7652 break;
7653 case Mips::FeatureMips3:
7654 selectArch("mips3");
7655 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips3();
7656 break;
7657 case Mips::FeatureMips4:
7658 selectArch("mips4");
7659 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips4();
7660 break;
7661 case Mips::FeatureMips5:
7662 selectArch("mips5");
7663 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips5();
7664 break;
7665 case Mips::FeatureMips32:
7666 selectArch("mips32");
7667 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips32();
7668 break;
7669 case Mips::FeatureMips32r2:
7670 selectArch("mips32r2");
7671 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips32R2();
7672 break;
7673 case Mips::FeatureMips32r3:
7674 selectArch("mips32r3");
7675 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips32R3();
7676 break;
7677 case Mips::FeatureMips32r5:
7678 selectArch("mips32r5");
7679 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips32R5();
7680 break;
7681 case Mips::FeatureMips32r6:
7682 selectArch("mips32r6");
7683 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips32R6();
7684 break;
7685 case Mips::FeatureMips64:
7686 selectArch("mips64");
7687 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips64();
7688 break;
7689 case Mips::FeatureMips64r2:
7690 selectArch("mips64r2");
7691 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips64R2();
7692 break;
7693 case Mips::FeatureMips64r3:
7694 selectArch("mips64r3");
7695 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips64R3();
7696 break;
7697 case Mips::FeatureMips64r5:
7698 selectArch("mips64r5");
7699 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips64R5();
7700 break;
7701 case Mips::FeatureMips64r6:
7702 selectArch("mips64r6");
7703 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetMips64R6();
7704 break;
7705 case Mips::FeatureCRC:
7706 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureCRC, "crc");
7707 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetCRC();
7708 break;
7709 case Mips::FeatureVirt:
7710 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureVirt, "virt");
7711 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetVirt();
7712 break;
7713 case Mips::FeatureGINV:
7714 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureGINV, "ginv");
7715 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetGINV();
7716 break;
7717 }
7718 return false;
7719}
7720
7721bool MipsAsmParser::eatComma(StringRef ErrorStr) {
7722 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7723 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
7724 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7725 return Error(Loc, ErrorStr);
7726 }
7727
7728 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
7729 return true;
7730}
7731
7732// Used to determine if .cpload, .cprestore, and .cpsetup have any effect.
7733// In this class, it is only used for .cprestore.
7734// FIXME: Only keep track of IsPicEnabled in one place, instead of in both
7735// MipsTargetELFStreamer and MipsAsmParser.
7736bool MipsAsmParser::isPicAndNotNxxAbi() {
7737 return inPicMode() && !(isABI_N32() || isABI_N64());
7738}
7739
7740bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveCpLoad(SMLoc Loc) {
7741 if (AssemblerOptions.back()->isReorder())
7742 Warning(Loc, ".cpload should be inside a noreorder section");
7743
7744 if (inMips16Mode()) {
7745 reportParseError(".cpload is not supported in Mips16 mode");
7746 return false;
7747 }
7748
7749 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 1> Reg;
7750 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(Reg);
7751 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch || ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail) {
7752 reportParseError("expected register containing function address");
7753 return false;
7754 }
7755
7756 MipsOperand &RegOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*Reg[0]);
7757 if (!RegOpnd.isGPRAsmReg()) {
7758 reportParseError(RegOpnd.getStartLoc(), "invalid register");
7759 return false;
7760 }
7761
7762 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7763 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7764 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7765 return false;
7766 }
7767
7768 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveCpLoad(RegOpnd.getGPR32Reg());
7769 return false;
7770}
7771
7772bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveCpRestore(SMLoc Loc) {
7773 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7774
7775 // Note that .cprestore is ignored if used with the N32 and N64 ABIs or if it
7776 // is used in non-PIC mode.
7777
7778 if (inMips16Mode()) {
7779 reportParseError(".cprestore is not supported in Mips16 mode");
7780 return false;
7781 }
7782
7783 // Get the stack offset value.
7784 const MCExpr *StackOffset;
7785 int64_t StackOffsetVal;
7786 if (Parser.parseExpression(StackOffset)) {
7787 reportParseError("expected stack offset value");
7788 return false;
7789 }
7790
7791 if (!StackOffset->evaluateAsAbsolute(StackOffsetVal, getStreamer())) {
7792 reportParseError("stack offset is not an absolute expression");
7793 return false;
7794 }
7795
7796 if (StackOffsetVal < 0) {
7797 Warning(Loc, ".cprestore with negative stack offset has no effect");
7798 IsCpRestoreSet = false;
7799 } else {
7800 IsCpRestoreSet = true;
7801 CpRestoreOffset = StackOffsetVal;
7802 }
7803
7804 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
7805 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7806 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
7807 return false;
7808 }
7809
7810 if (!getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveCpRestore(
7811 CpRestoreOffset, [&]() { return getATReg(Loc); }, Loc, STI))
7812 return true;
7813 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
7814 return false;
7815}
7816
7817bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveCPSetup() {
7818 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7819 unsigned FuncReg;
7820 unsigned Save;
7821 bool SaveIsReg = true;
7822
7823 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 1> TmpReg;
7824 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(TmpReg);
7825 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch) {
7826 reportParseError("expected register containing function address");
7827 return false;
7828 }
7829
7830 MipsOperand &FuncRegOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*TmpReg[0]);
7831 if (!FuncRegOpnd.isGPRAsmReg()) {
7832 reportParseError(FuncRegOpnd.getStartLoc(), "invalid register");
7833 return false;
7834 }
7835
7836 FuncReg = FuncRegOpnd.getGPR32Reg();
7837 TmpReg.clear();
7838
7839 if (!eatComma("unexpected token, expected comma"))
7840 return true;
7841
7842 ResTy = parseAnyRegister(TmpReg);
7843 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch) {
7844 const MCExpr *OffsetExpr;
7845 int64_t OffsetVal;
7846 SMLoc ExprLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
7847
7848 if (Parser.parseExpression(OffsetExpr) ||
7849 !OffsetExpr->evaluateAsAbsolute(OffsetVal, getStreamer())) {
7850 reportParseError(ExprLoc, "expected save register or stack offset");
7851 return false;
7852 }
7853
7854 Save = OffsetVal;
7855 SaveIsReg = false;
7856 } else {
7857 MipsOperand &SaveOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*TmpReg[0]);
7858 if (!SaveOpnd.isGPRAsmReg()) {
7859 reportParseError(SaveOpnd.getStartLoc(), "invalid register");
7860 return false;
7861 }
7862 Save = SaveOpnd.getGPR32Reg();
7863 }
7864
7865 if (!eatComma("unexpected token, expected comma"))
7866 return true;
7867
7868 const MCExpr *Expr;
7869 if (Parser.parseExpression(Expr)) {
7870 reportParseError("expected expression");
7871 return false;
7872 }
7873
7874 if (Expr->getKind() != MCExpr::SymbolRef) {
7875 reportParseError("expected symbol");
7876 return false;
7877 }
7878 const MCSymbolRefExpr *Ref = static_cast<const MCSymbolRefExpr *>(Expr);
7879
7880 CpSaveLocation = Save;
7881 CpSaveLocationIsRegister = SaveIsReg;
7882
7883 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveCpsetup(FuncReg, Save, Ref->getSymbol(),
7884 SaveIsReg);
7885 return false;
7886}
7887
7888bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveCPReturn() {
7889 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveCpreturn(CpSaveLocation,
7890 CpSaveLocationIsRegister);
7891 return false;
7892}
7893
7894bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveNaN() {
7895 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
7896 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
7897 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
7898
7899 if (Tok.getString() == "2008") {
7900 Parser.Lex();
7901 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveNaN2008();
7902 return false;
7903 } else if (Tok.getString() == "legacy") {
7904 Parser.Lex();
7905 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveNaNLegacy();
7906 return false;
7907 }
7908 }
7909 // If we don't recognize the option passed to the .nan
7910 // directive (e.g. no option or unknown option), emit an error.
7911 reportParseError("invalid option in .nan directive");
7912 return false;
7913}
7914
7915bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveSet() {
7916 const AsmToken &Tok = getParser().getTok();
7917 StringRef IdVal = Tok.getString();
7918 SMLoc Loc = Tok.getLoc();
7919
7920 if (IdVal == "noat")
7921 return parseSetNoAtDirective();
7922 if (IdVal == "at")
7923 return parseSetAtDirective();
7924 if (IdVal == "arch")
7925 return parseSetArchDirective();
7926 if (IdVal == "bopt") {
7927 Warning(Loc, "'bopt' feature is unsupported");
7928 getParser().Lex();
7929 return false;
7930 }
7931 if (IdVal == "nobopt") {
7932 // We're already running in nobopt mode, so nothing to do.
7933 getParser().Lex();
7934 return false;
7935 }
7936 if (IdVal == "fp")
7937 return parseSetFpDirective();
7938 if (IdVal == "oddspreg")
7939 return parseSetOddSPRegDirective();
7940 if (IdVal == "nooddspreg")
7941 return parseSetNoOddSPRegDirective();
7942 if (IdVal == "pop")
7943 return parseSetPopDirective();
7944 if (IdVal == "push")
7945 return parseSetPushDirective();
7946 if (IdVal == "reorder")
7947 return parseSetReorderDirective();
7948 if (IdVal == "noreorder")
7949 return parseSetNoReorderDirective();
7950 if (IdVal == "macro")
7951 return parseSetMacroDirective();
7952 if (IdVal == "nomacro")
7953 return parseSetNoMacroDirective();
7954 if (IdVal == "mips16")
7955 return parseSetMips16Directive();
7956 if (IdVal == "nomips16")
7957 return parseSetNoMips16Directive();
7958 if (IdVal == "nomicromips") {
7959 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureMicroMips, "micromips");
7960 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveSetNoMicroMips();
7961 getParser().eatToEndOfStatement();
7962 return false;
7963 }
7964 if (IdVal == "micromips") {
7965 if (hasMips64r6()) {
7966 Error(Loc, ".set micromips directive is not supported with MIPS64R6");
7967 return false;
7968 }
7969 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMicroMips);
7970 }
7971 if (IdVal == "mips0")
7972 return parseSetMips0Directive();
7973 if (IdVal == "mips1")
7974 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips1);
7975 if (IdVal == "mips2")
7976 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips2);
7977 if (IdVal == "mips3")
7978 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips3);
7979 if (IdVal == "mips4")
7980 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips4);
7981 if (IdVal == "mips5")
7982 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips5);
7983 if (IdVal == "mips32")
7984 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips32);
7985 if (IdVal == "mips32r2")
7986 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips32r2);
7987 if (IdVal == "mips32r3")
7988 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips32r3);
7989 if (IdVal == "mips32r5")
7990 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips32r5);
7991 if (IdVal == "mips32r6")
7992 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips32r6);
7993 if (IdVal == "mips64")
7994 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips64);
7995 if (IdVal == "mips64r2")
7996 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips64r2);
7997 if (IdVal == "mips64r3")
7998 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips64r3);
7999 if (IdVal == "mips64r5")
8000 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips64r5);
8001 if (IdVal == "mips64r6") {
8002 if (inMicroMipsMode()) {
8003 Error(Loc, "MIPS64R6 is not supported with microMIPS");
8004 return false;
8005 }
8006 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureMips64r6);
8007 }
8008 if (IdVal == "dsp")
8009 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureDSP);
8010 if (IdVal == "dspr2")
8011 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureDSPR2);
8012 if (IdVal == "nodsp")
8013 return parseSetNoDspDirective();
8014 if (IdVal == "msa")
8015 return parseSetMsaDirective();
8016 if (IdVal == "nomsa")
8017 return parseSetNoMsaDirective();
8018 if (IdVal == "mt")
8019 return parseSetMtDirective();
8020 if (IdVal == "nomt")
8021 return parseSetNoMtDirective();
8022 if (IdVal == "softfloat")
8023 return parseSetSoftFloatDirective();
8024 if (IdVal == "hardfloat")
8025 return parseSetHardFloatDirective();
8026 if (IdVal == "cheri_sysregs_accessible" || IdVal == "nocheri_sysregs_accessible") {
8027 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8028 Parser.Lex();
8029 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
8030 return reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8031 AreCheriSysRegsAccessible = IdVal == "cheri_sysregs_accessible";
8032 return false;
8033 }
8034 if (IdVal == "crc")
8035 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureCRC);
8036 if (IdVal == "nocrc")
8037 return parseSetNoCRCDirective();
8038 if (IdVal == "virt")
8039 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureVirt);
8040 if (IdVal == "novirt")
8041 return parseSetNoVirtDirective();
8042 if (IdVal == "ginv")
8043 return parseSetFeature(Mips::FeatureGINV);
8044 if (IdVal == "noginv")
8045 return parseSetNoGINVDirective();
8046
8047 // It is just an identifier, look for an assignment.
8048 return parseSetAssignment();
8049}
8050
8051/// parseDirectiveGpWord
8052/// ::= .gpword local_sym
8053bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveGpWord() {
8054 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8055 const MCExpr *Value;
8056 // EmitGPRel32Value requires an expression, so we are using base class
8057 // method to evaluate the expression.
8058 if (getParser().parseExpression(Value))
8059 return true;
8060 getParser().getStreamer().EmitGPRel32Value(Value);
8061
8062 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
8063 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(),
8064 "unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8065 Parser.Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
8066 return false;
8067}
8068
8069/// parseDirectiveGpDWord
8070/// ::= .gpdword local_sym
8071bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveGpDWord() {
8072 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8073 const MCExpr *Value;
8074 // EmitGPRel64Value requires an expression, so we are using base class
8075 // method to evaluate the expression.
8076 if (getParser().parseExpression(Value))
8077 return true;
8078 getParser().getStreamer().EmitGPRel64Value(Value);
8079
8080 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
8081 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(),
8082 "unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8083 Parser.Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
8084 return false;
8085}
8086

8089bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveDtpRelWord() {
8090 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8091 const MCExpr *Value;
8092 // EmitDTPRel32Value requires an expression, so we are using base class
8093 // method to evaluate the expression.
8094 if (getParser().parseExpression(Value))
8095 return true;
8096 getParser().getStreamer().EmitDTPRel32Value(Value);
8097
8098 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
8099 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(),
8100 "unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8101 Parser.Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
8102 return false;
8103}

8158
8159bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveOption() {
8160 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8161 // Get the option token.
8162 AsmToken Tok = Parser.getTok();
8163 // At the moment only identifiers are supported.
8164 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
8165 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
8166 "unexpected token, expected identifier");
8167 }
8168
8169 StringRef Option = Tok.getIdentifier();
8170
8171 if (Option == "pic0") {
8172 // MipsAsmParser needs to know if the current PIC mode changes.
8173 IsPicEnabled = false;
8174
8175 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionPic0();
8176 Parser.Lex();
8177 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8178 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
8179 "unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8180 }
8181 return false;
8182 }
8183
8184 if (Option == "pic2") {
8185 // MipsAsmParser needs to know if the current PIC mode changes.
8186 IsPicEnabled = true;
8187
8188 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveOptionPic2();
8189 Parser.Lex();
8190 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8191 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
8192 "unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8193 }
8194 return false;
8195 }
8196
8197 // Unknown option.
8198 Warning(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
8199 "unknown option, expected 'pic0' or 'pic2'");
8200 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
8201 return false;
8202}
8203
8204/// parseInsnDirective
8205/// ::= .insn
8206bool MipsAsmParser::parseInsnDirective() {
8207 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8208 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8209 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8210 return false;
8211 }
8212
8213 // The actual label marking happens in
8214 // MipsELFStreamer::createPendingLabelRelocs().
8215 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveInsn();
8216
8217 getParser().Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
8218 return false;
8219}
8220
8221/// parseRSectionDirective
8222/// ::= .rdata
8223bool MipsAsmParser::parseRSectionDirective(StringRef Section) {
8224 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8225 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8226 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8227 return false;
8228 }
8229
8230 MCSection *ELFSection = getContext().getELFSection(
8231 Section, ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, ELF::SHF_ALLOC);
8232 getParser().getStreamer().SwitchSection(ELFSection);
8233
8234 getParser().Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
8235 return false;
8236}

8238/// parseSSectionDirective
8239/// ::= .sbss
8240/// ::= .sdata
8241bool MipsAsmParser::parseSSectionDirective(StringRef Section, unsigned Type) {
8242 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8243 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8244 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8245 return false;
8246 }
8247
8248 MCSection *ELFSection = getContext().getELFSection(
8249 Section, Type, ELF::SHF_WRITE | ELF::SHF_ALLOC | ELF::SHF_MIPS_GPREL);
8250 getParser().getStreamer().SwitchSection(ELFSection);
8251
8252 getParser().Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
8253 return false;
8254}

8256/// parseDirectiveModule
8257/// ::= .module oddspreg
8258/// ::= .module nooddspreg
8259/// ::= .module fp=value
8260/// ::= .module softfloat
8261/// ::= .module hardfloat
8262/// ::= .module mt
8263/// ::= .module crc
8264/// ::= .module nocrc
8265/// ::= .module virt
8266/// ::= .module novirt
8267/// ::= .module ginv
8268/// ::= .module noginv
8269bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveModule() {
8270 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8271 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer();
8272 SMLoc L = Lexer.getLoc();
8273
8274 if (!getTargetStreamer().isModuleDirectiveAllowed()) {
8275 // TODO : get a better message.
8276 reportParseError(".module directive must appear before any code");
8277 return false;
8278 }
8279
8280 StringRef Option;
8281 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(Option)) {
8282 reportParseError("expected .module option identifier");
8283 return false;
8284 }
8285
8286 if (Option == "oddspreg") {
8287 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureNoOddSPReg, "nooddspreg");
8288
8289 // Synchronize the abiflags information with the FeatureBits information we
8290 // changed above.
8291 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8292
8293 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated abiflags information.
8294 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8295 // emitted at the end).
8296 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleOddSPReg();
8297
8298 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8299 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8300 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8301 return false;
8302 }
8303
8304 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8305 } else if (Option == "nooddspreg") {
8306 if (!isABI_O32()) {
8307 return Error(L, "'.module nooddspreg' requires the O32 ABI");
8308 }
8309
8310 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureNoOddSPReg, "nooddspreg");
8311
8312 // Synchronize the abiflags information with the FeatureBits information we
8313 // changed above.
8314 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8315
8316 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated abiflags information.
8317 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8318 // emitted at the end).
8319 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleOddSPReg();
8320
8321 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8322 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8323 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8324 return false;
8325 }
8326
8327 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8328 } else if (Option == "fp") {
8329 return parseDirectiveModuleFP();
8330 } else if (Option == "softfloat") {
8331 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureSoftFloat, "soft-float");
8332
8333 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8334 // updated above.
8335 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8336
8337 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8338 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8339 // emitted later).
8340 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleSoftFloat();
8341
8342 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8343 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8344 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8345 return false;
8346 }
8347
8348 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8349 } else if (Option == "hardfloat") {
8350 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureSoftFloat, "soft-float");
8351
8352 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8353 // updated above.
8354 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8355
8356 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8357 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8358 // emitted later).
8359 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleHardFloat();
8360
8361 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8362 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8363 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8364 return false;
8365 }
8366
8367 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8368 } else if (Option == "mt") {
8369 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureMT, "mt");
8370
8371 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8372 // updated above.
8373 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8374
8375 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8376 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8377 // emitted later).
8378 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleMT();
8379
8380 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8381 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8382 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8383 return false;
8384 }
8385
8386 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8387 } else if (Option == "crc") {
8388 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureCRC, "crc");
8389
8390 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8391 // updated above.
8392 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8393
8394 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8395 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8396 // emitted later).
8397 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleCRC();
8398
8399 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8400 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8401 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8402 return false;
8403 }
8404
8405 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8406 } else if (Option == "nocrc") {
8407 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureCRC, "crc");
8408
8409 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8410 // updated above.
8411 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8412
8413 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8414 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8415 // emitted later).
8416 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleNoCRC();
8417
8418 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8419 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8420 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8421 return false;
8422 }
8423
8424 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8425 } else if (Option == "virt") {
8426 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureVirt, "virt");
8427
8428 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8429 // updated above.
8430 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8431
8432 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8433 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8434 // emitted later).
8435 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleVirt();
8436
8437 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8438 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8439 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8440 return false;
8441 }
8442
8443 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8444 } else if (Option == "novirt") {
8445 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureVirt, "virt");
8446
8447 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8448 // updated above.
8449 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8450
8451 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8452 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8453 // emitted later).
8454 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleNoVirt();
8455
8456 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8457 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8458 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8459 return false;
8460 }
8461
8462 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8463 } else if (Option == "ginv") {
8464 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureGINV, "ginv");
8465
8466 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8467 // updated above.
8468 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8469
8470 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8471 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8472 // emitted later).
8473 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleGINV();
8474
8475 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8476 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8477 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8478 return false;
8479 }
8480
8481 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8482 } else if (Option == "noginv") {
8483 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureGINV, "ginv");
8484
8485 // Synchronize the ABI Flags information with the FeatureBits information we
8486 // updated above.
8487 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8488
8489 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated ABI Flags information.
8490 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8491 // emitted later).
8492 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleNoGINV();
8493
8494 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8495 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8496 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8497 return false;
8498 }
8499
8500 return false; // parseDirectiveModule has finished successfully.
8501 } else {
8502 return Error(L, "'" + Twine(Option) + "' is not a valid .module option.");
8503 }
8504}
8505
8506/// parseDirectiveModuleFP
8507/// ::= =32
8508/// ::= =xx
8509/// ::= =64
8510bool MipsAsmParser::parseDirectiveModuleFP() {
8511 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8512 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer();
8513
8514 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Equal)) {
8515 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected equals sign '='");
8516 return false;
8517 }
8518 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '=' token.
8519
8520 MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind FpABI;
8521 if (!parseFpABIValue(FpABI, ".module"))
8522 return false;
8523
8524 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8525 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8526 return false;
8527 }
8528
8529 // Synchronize the abiflags information with the FeatureBits information we
8530 // changed above.
8531 getTargetStreamer().updateABIInfo(*this);
8532
8533 // If printing assembly, use the recently updated abiflags information.
8534 // If generating ELF, don't do anything (the .MIPS.abiflags section gets
8535 // emitted at the end).
8536 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveModuleFP();
8537
8538 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement.
8539 return false;
8540}
8541
8542bool MipsAsmParser::parseFpABIValue(MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind &FpABI,
8543 StringRef Directive) {
8544 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8545 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer();
8546 bool ModuleLevelOptions = Directive == ".module";
8547
8548 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
8549 StringRef Value = Parser.getTok().getString();
8550 Parser.Lex();
8551
8552 if (Value != "xx") {
8553 reportParseError("unsupported value, expected 'xx', '32' or '64'");
8554 return false;
8555 }
8556
8557 if (!isABI_O32()) {
8558 reportParseError("'" + Directive + " fp=xx' requires the O32 ABI");
8559 return false;
8560 }
8561
8562 FpABI = MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind::XX;
8563 if (ModuleLevelOptions) {
8564 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8565 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8566 } else {
8567 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8568 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8569 }
8570 return true;
8571 }
8572
8573 if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
8574 unsigned Value = Parser.getTok().getIntVal();
8575 Parser.Lex();
8576
8577 if (Value != 32 && Value != 64) {
8578 reportParseError("unsupported value, expected 'xx', '32' or '64'");
8579 return false;
8580 }
8581
8582 if (Value == 32) {
8583 if (!isABI_O32()) {
8584 reportParseError("'" + Directive + " fp=32' requires the O32 ABI");
8585 return false;
8586 }
8587
8588 FpABI = MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind::S32;
8589 if (ModuleLevelOptions) {
8590 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8591 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8592 } else {
8593 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8594 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8595 }
8596 } else {
8597 FpABI = MipsABIFlagsSection::FpABIKind::S64;
8598 if (ModuleLevelOptions) {
8599 clearModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8600 setModuleFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8601 } else {
8602 clearFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFPXX, "fpxx");
8603 setFeatureBits(Mips::FeatureFP64Bit, "fp64");
8604 }
8605 }
8606
8607 return true;
8608 }
8609
8610 return false;
8611}
8612
8613bool MipsAsmParser::ParseDirective(AsmToken DirectiveID) {
8614 // This returns false if this function recognizes the directive
8615 // regardless of whether it is successfully handles or reports an
8616 // error. Otherwise it returns true to give the generic parser a
8617 // chance at recognizing it.
8618
8619 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
8620 StringRef IDVal = DirectiveID.getString();
8621
8622 if (IDVal == ".cpload") {
8623 parseDirectiveCpLoad(DirectiveID.getLoc());
8624 return false;
8625 }
8626 if (IDVal == ".cprestore") {
8627 parseDirectiveCpRestore(DirectiveID.getLoc());
8628 return false;
8629 }
8630 if (IDVal == ".ent") {
8631 StringRef SymbolName;
8632
8633 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(SymbolName)) {
8634 reportParseError("expected identifier after .ent");
8635 return false;
8636 }
8637
8638 // There's an undocumented extension that allows an integer to
8639 // follow the name of the procedure which AFAICS is ignored by GAS.
8640 // Example: .ent foo,2
8641 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8642 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
8643 // Even though we accept this undocumented extension for compatibility
8644 // reasons, the additional integer argument does not actually change
8645 // the behaviour of the '.ent' directive, so we would like to discourage
8646 // its use. We do this by not referring to the extended version in
8647 // error messages which are not directly related to its use.
8648 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8649 return false;
8650 }
8651 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
8652 const MCExpr *DummyNumber;
8653 int64_t DummyNumberVal;
8654 // If the user was explicitly trying to use the extended version,
8655 // we still give helpful extension-related error messages.
8656 if (Parser.parseExpression(DummyNumber)) {
8657 reportParseError("expected number after comma");
8658 return false;
8659 }
8660 if (!DummyNumber->evaluateAsAbsolute(DummyNumberVal, getStreamer())) {
8661 reportParseError("expected an absolute expression after comma");
8662 return false;
8663 }
8664 }
8665
8666 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8667 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8668 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8669 return false;
8670 }
8671
8672 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(SymbolName);
8673
8674 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveEnt(*Sym);
8675 CurrentFn = Sym;
8676 IsCpRestoreSet = false;
8677 return false;
8678 }
8679
8680 if (IDVal == ".end") {
8681 StringRef SymbolName;
8682
8683 if (Parser.parseIdentifier(SymbolName)) {
8684 reportParseError("expected identifier after .end");
8685 return false;
8686 }
8687
8688 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8689 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8690 return false;
8691 }
8692
8693 if (CurrentFn == nullptr) {
8694 reportParseError(".end used without .ent");
8695 return false;
8696 }
8697
8698 if ((SymbolName != CurrentFn->getName())) {
8699 reportParseError(".end symbol does not match .ent symbol");
8700 return false;
8701 }
8702
8703 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveEnd(SymbolName);
8704 CurrentFn = nullptr;
8705 IsCpRestoreSet = false;
8706 return false;
8707 }
8708
8709 if (IDVal == ".frame") {
8710 // .frame $stack_reg, frame_size_in_bytes, $return_reg
8711 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 1> TmpReg;
8712 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseAnyRegister(TmpReg);
8713 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch || ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail) {
8714 reportParseError("expected stack register");
8715 return false;
8716 }
8717
8718 MipsOperand &StackRegOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*TmpReg[0]);
8719 if (!StackRegOpnd.isGPRAsmReg() && !StackRegOpnd.isCheriAsmReg()) {
8720 reportParseError(StackRegOpnd.getStartLoc(),
8721 "expected general purpose register");
8722 return false;
8723 }
8724 unsigned StackReg = StackRegOpnd.isCheriAsmReg()
8725 ? StackRegOpnd.getCheriReg()
8726 : StackRegOpnd.getGPR32Reg();
8727
8728 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Comma))
8729 Parser.Lex();
8730 else {
8731 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected comma");
8732 return false;
8733 }
8734
8735 // Parse the frame size.
8736 const MCExpr *FrameSize;
8737 int64_t FrameSizeVal;
8738
8739 if (Parser.parseExpression(FrameSize)) {
8740 reportParseError("expected frame size value");
8741 return false;
8742 }
8743
8744 if (!FrameSize->evaluateAsAbsolute(FrameSizeVal, getStreamer())) {
8745 reportParseError("frame size not an absolute expression");
8746 return false;
8747 }
8748
8749 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Comma))
8750 Parser.Lex();
8751 else {
8752 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected comma");
8753 return false;
8754 }
8755
8756 // Parse the return register.
8757 TmpReg.clear();
8758 ResTy = parseAnyRegister(TmpReg);
8759 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch || ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail) {
8760 reportParseError("expected return register");
8761 return false;
8762 }
8763
8764 MipsOperand &ReturnRegOpnd = static_cast<MipsOperand &>(*TmpReg[0]);
8765 if (!ReturnRegOpnd.isGPRAsmReg() && !ReturnRegOpnd.isCheriAsmReg()) {
8766 reportParseError(ReturnRegOpnd.getStartLoc(),
8767 "expected general purpose register");
8768 return false;
8769 }
8770
8771 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8772 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8773 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8774 return false;
8775 }
8776
8777 unsigned ReturnReg = ReturnRegOpnd.isCheriAsmReg()
8778 ? ReturnRegOpnd.getCheriReg()
8779 : ReturnRegOpnd.getGPR32Reg();
8780
8781 getTargetStreamer().emitFrame(StackReg, FrameSizeVal, ReturnReg);
8782 IsCpRestoreSet = false;
8783 return false;
8784 }
8785
8786 if (IDVal == ".set") {
8787 parseDirectiveSet();
8788 return false;
8789 }
8790
8791 if (IDVal == ".mask" || IDVal == ".fmask") {
8792 // .mask bitmask, frame_offset
8793 // bitmask: One bit for each register used.
8794 // frame_offset: Offset from Canonical Frame Address ($sp on entry) where
8795 // first register is expected to be saved.
8796 // Examples:
8797 // .mask 0x80000000, -4
8798 // .fmask 0x80000000, -4
8799 //
8800
8801 // Parse the bitmask
8802 const MCExpr *BitMask;
8803 int64_t BitMaskVal;
8804
8805 if (Parser.parseExpression(BitMask)) {
8806 reportParseError("expected bitmask value");
8807 return false;
8808 }
8809
8810 if (!BitMask->evaluateAsAbsolute(BitMaskVal, getStreamer())) {
8811 reportParseError("bitmask not an absolute expression");
8812 return false;
8813 }
8814
8815 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Comma))
8816 Parser.Lex();
8817 else {
8818 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected comma");
8819 return false;
8820 }
8821
8822 // Parse the frame_offset
8823 const MCExpr *FrameOffset;
8824 int64_t FrameOffsetVal;
8825
8826 if (Parser.parseExpression(FrameOffset)) {
8827 reportParseError("expected frame offset value");
8828 return false;
8829 }
8830
8831 if (!FrameOffset->evaluateAsAbsolute(FrameOffsetVal, getStreamer())) {
8832 reportParseError("frame offset not an absolute expression");
8833 return false;
8834 }
8835
8836 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8837 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8838 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8839 return false;
8840 }
8841
8842 if (IDVal == ".mask")
8843 getTargetStreamer().emitMask(BitMaskVal, FrameOffsetVal);
8844 else
8845 getTargetStreamer().emitFMask(BitMaskVal, FrameOffsetVal);
8846 return false;
8847 }
8848
8849 if (IDVal == ".nan")
8850 return parseDirectiveNaN();
8851
8852 if (IDVal == ".gpword") {
8853 parseDirectiveGpWord();
8854 return false;
8855 }
8856
8857 if (IDVal == ".gpdword") {
8858 parseDirectiveGpDWord();
8859 return false;
8860 }
8861
8862 if (IDVal == ".dtprelword") {
8863 parseDirectiveDtpRelWord();
8864 return false;
8865 }
8866
8867 if (IDVal == ".dtpreldword") {
8868 parseDirectiveDtpRelDWord();
8869 return false;
8870 }
8871
8872 if (IDVal == ".tprelword") {
8873 parseDirectiveTpRelWord();
8874 return false;
8875 }
8876
8877 if (IDVal == ".tpreldword") {
8878 parseDirectiveTpRelDWord();
8879 return false;
8880 }
8881
8882 if (IDVal == ".option") {
8883 parseDirectiveOption();
8884 return false;
8885 }
8886
8887 if (IDVal == ".abicalls") {
8888 getTargetStreamer().emitDirectiveAbiCalls();
8889 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8890 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
8891 "unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8892 }
8893 return false;
8894 }
8895
8896 if (IDVal == ".cpsetup") {
8897 parseDirectiveCPSetup();
8898 return false;
8899 }
8900 if (IDVal == ".cpreturn") {
8901 parseDirectiveCPReturn();
8902 return false;
8903 }
8904 if (IDVal == ".module") {
8905 parseDirectiveModule();
8906 return false;
8907 }
8908 if (IDVal == ".llvm_internal_mips_reallow_module_directive") {
8909 parseInternalDirectiveReallowModule();
8910 return false;
8911 }
8912 if (IDVal == ".insn") {
8913 parseInsnDirective();
8914 return false;
8915 }
8916 if (IDVal == ".rdata") {
8917 parseRSectionDirective(".rodata");
8918 return false;
8919 }
8920 if (IDVal == ".sbss") {
8921 parseSSectionDirective(IDVal, ELF::SHT_NOBITS);
8922 return false;
8923 }
8924 if (IDVal == ".sdata") {
8925 parseSSectionDirective(IDVal, ELF::SHT_PROGBITS);
8926 return false;
8927 }
8928
8929 return true;
8930}
8931
8932bool MipsAsmParser::parseInternalDirectiveReallowModule() {
8933 // If this is not the end of the statement, report an error.
8934 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
8935 reportParseError("unexpected token, expected end of statement");
8936 return false;
8937 }
8938
8939 getTargetStreamer().reallowModuleDirective();
8940
8941 getParser().Lex(); // Eat EndOfStatement token.
8942 return false;
8943}
8944
8945extern "C" void LLVMInitializeMipsAsmParser() {
8946 RegisterMCAsmParser<MipsAsmParser> X(getTheMipsTarget());
8947 RegisterMCAsmParser<MipsAsmParser> Y(getTheMipselTarget());
8948 RegisterMCAsmParser<MipsAsmParser> A(getTheMips64Target());
8949 RegisterMCAsmParser<MipsAsmParser> B(getTheMips64elTarget());
8950 RegisterMCAsmParser<MipsAsmParser> C(getTheMipsCheriTarget());
8951}
8952
8953#define GET_REGISTER_MATCHER
8954#define GET_MATCHER_IMPLEMENTATION
8955#define GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER
8956#include "MipsGenAsmMatcher.inc"
8957
8958bool MipsAsmParser::mnemonicIsValid(StringRef Mnemonic, unsigned VariantID) {
8959 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
8960 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
8961 switch (VariantID) {
8962 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
8963 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
8964 }
8965 // Search the table.
8966 auto MnemonicRange = std::equal_range(Start, End, Mnemonic, LessOpcode());
8967 return MnemonicRange.first != MnemonicRange.second;
8968}
